text: By far thee best breakfast cafe in Vegas. Prices are reasonable, atmosphere is friendly, and the service is great. Love, love the different variety of pancakes and the Nutella crepes is my favorite. The portions are always more than enough. Recommending this place to everyone!!!!

Decent food. Love the concept of having a breakfast place that has the general American breakfast options as well as a few hawaiian/Filipino options. 

Love that you can get a side of specialty pancakes so that you can enjoy your savory and sweet breakfast. 

Generally a burn em and turn em place. Quick service.
Great family breakfast place and the red velvet pancakes are the best. Love the staff and they are very friendly.
Really good food but every time we try to go here way busy the need to open it up in a bigger place or another one but its worth the wait great food

We absolutely love the food,  the reason for the poor review is because of the service at the front counter. As people have already mentioned, it's always packed here so we always order food to go. Maybe I don't understand what exactly a tip is for but last time I checked a tip is for when you are being seated,  served/waited on... When paying at the counter they give you a tab to fill out for the tip before they proceed with the transaction... At that point I cross out the tip(because I don't feel I have a reason to leave tip due to not being seated and served) and return the receipt to the person at the register. No matter who I am dealing with I ALWAYS get nasty or disturbed looks when I don't leave a tip... Unless the tip is going to the cooks I honestly don't feel as I should be leaving a tip for the person who bagged my food or the cashier.  Maybe the process should be alerted or the workers at the front counter should be talked to about putting on a better face when they are displeased.

The only thing appealing about this place is the restaurant name. My wife ordered the skillet with "chili verde" and it was horrendous!  Initial cup of coffee was cold. Pancakes tasted like metal. Waitress was rude. Nothing spectacular about this place. Mechanics garage cabinet by register?  Very disappointed and will not return.

Great combination of flavored pancakes and hawaiian/filipino fusion comfort food like adobo fried rice. You better try the red velvet pancake as it is their best pancake with their signature sauce. Short stacks comes with 3 smaller pancakes.  Egg benedicts with hawaiian flavors like kalua pig will be on my list to order next time. Adobo fried rice wrapped in egg is huge for those who have big appetite.

I really want to love this place, but the two times I've been here was rather disappointing.  The red velvet pancakes was ok, the adobo fried rice lack flavor, 2 eggs, rice and 4 links for almost $9 is a bit overprice. Overall the food and service is just okay. I think the hype got my expectation high.

The red velvet pancake is a MUST! I got this as a side order with the adobo fried rice. The adobo fried rice is also amazing. Definitely one of my favorite places to grab brunch I really hope the branch out here to Los Angeles. I would probably go out here way too much.
Food was excellent, the service left a tiny bit to be desired but it was a Sunday. Recommend to anyone who enjoys a good filling breakfast.

ZERO STARS is more appropriate in today's visit to this location. We were looking forward to this breakfast BUT got a server name SHAWNI who got to our table with a sour face with no good morning greetings whatsoever. You felt right away she's not friendly figured having a bad day already so I let it go.  

She took our order with attitude, fine ... she punched our order on a kiosk annex to us literally few feet away and I had to make sure the order we got had the famous red velvet Babystacks pancakes. So I asked , " Excuse me could you please check the pancakes we ordered are the red velvet." She didn't even come address us back to the table just her head turned and said with an attitude, " you got the buttermilk so do you want the red velvet? With such contemptuous attitude ... really?!?!? and came back to our table flailing her hands to us and said "next time you order you need to say you want the red velvet." Are you effing kidding me?! I let go of her attitude initially but this time I couldn't and shouldn't let this one go!!!! I had to ask, " are you having a bad day? Cz you are not friendly at all from the get go? If we were first time customers and not know the difference it is your job to explain your menu & any upgrade." I had to ask for a Manager because she was just plain RUDE !!!!

Is this what this place represents? Are their employees not trained properly on simple customer service?!?! 

A manager name Blanca came and tried to appease us, but it was too late, our morning already ruined what supposed to be a good birthday breakfast.

It was VERY DISAPPOINTING to get a HORRIBLE server because they are the forefront of the establishment and gives you a negative vibe of the place. Customer Service is so important and this SHAWNI so lacks of it and shame goes with the management as well to tolerate and keep people with no business waitressing if they don't want to serve then they shouldn't be in hospitality job!

CUSTOMER SERVICE breaks or makes a business and I highly suggest to the owner of this establishment to work on that and make it a priority to train their employees well.

NEEDLESS TO SAY WE WILL NEVER COME BACK TO THIS PLACE AND DEFINITELY MAKE SURE TO TELL PEOPLE & FRIENDS TO GO TO THE BUFFALO LOCATION instead who has excellent customer Service and much better tasting food than this Durango branch.
I don't love the atmosphere, it's not very cozy but the food is great. I love the Hawaiian selection here. Definitely would recommend the loco moco.

I was bummed out about this place.  Service was slow,  and people seated after us got their food before us. All around me people were enjoying their meal,  so I was hopeful. I got the red velvet pancakes,  my mom got the rocky road pancakes.  They took a long time,  and when we finally got them,  they were cold and dry. The rocky road pancakes had barely any syrup on them. The Portuguese sausage was lukewarm and ok, but not great.  We were starving, so we ate it,  but I won't be coming back. Oh well,  we tried it.

First time here with hubby and it's one of the best breakfast we had. We ordered the adobo fried rice and the skillet chicken (it had spinach, potato, cheese, herbs) both dish was amazing! Recommended and the staff is so nice..

Giving this business one star because they refuse to seat incomplete parties even when there are over 10 tables open. I am on here all the time so I asked for the owner as I was attempting to have a business meeting, the hostess told me the owner was there. Blanca (who is not the owner, just a waitstaff) comes out and presents herself as the owner. They precede to tell me that they are not allowed to seat people even with 10 tables and the bar open. Know at this point I was less upset about the seating and more about the lies. They still refuse to give a phone number for the owner. What kind of business owner does not give a complaint number?

Place is close to where I live so breakfast here is very convenient. My wife and I eat here about once every few weeks. They have gotten our to-go orders wrong multiple times. They have one dish that has spam with eggs and spam in the eggs. I am not a huge stickler, but they seem to get this mixed up themselves when preparing it. Food is good and hostess are nice.

I used to go to weekly meetings at this Mimi's location and I loved it from the start. The food is ALWAYS great, I'm in love with the Buttermilk Spice muffin! They employees are always really nice and the food always turns out amazing!

Me and a couple coworkers came here after a busy graveyard shift. Our server Miley was amazing.  They had a special pancakes called cookies and cream that were delicious. The banana cream pie pancakes just as delicious. They carrot cake pancakes were like eating a fluffy piece of carrot cake. There was 7 of us and only a short stack of pancakes make it out of that place. I will be back here
Amazing! Everyone is so friendly and helpful and the food is amazing. Best pancakes of my life!!!!

Hey, it's a Hawaiian Denny's!

I've been here more than enough to know that this place, this specific location, is the worst. Every time I come here, I have to wait 20-25 minutes. And every time I come here, the hostess responds rudely to me when I return to ask if a table has opened up.  Last time, convo went something like this:

Rude hostess: "I called your name already." 
Me: "I heard you say 20 minutes and it's been 20 minutes." 
Rude hostess: "I said ABOUT!"

Woman, I'm not deaf, and what crawled up your ass? I always arrive before or on time. That's the point of setting a timer. Duh. Besides, there's no reason to respond to customers like that. Damn. 

I've tried to order take-out from here to avoid the long wait, but from what I've been told this location doesn't do that on the weekends....or so they say. I showed up on a Sunday for brunch and saw a few customers walking out with take-out. WTF?

I feel like the food isn't up to par like it used to be. I was hoping Lola Cora's Corned Beef Hash would be like a taste of home cookin', but it was dry and unbearable to eat. The Adobo Fried Rice...meh, unimpressed. The Country Fried Steak is pretty good, and the Red Velvet Pancakes aren't bad. 

What doesn't suck about this place? The waitstaff is great, and I've never had an issue. Rock on, waitstaff.
Service is spotty but food is really good. I've like everything I've tried. Always a wait to get a table but I only go on the weekend so I expect that.

I have eaten here a total of 2 times (and almost a 3rd if I had of stayed today) each time I have came with friends or family the taste and quality of the food has been great. The proportion sizes were nice for the price asked and the restaurant has always smelled great from the good food. 

The complaint I have is each time there has been long wait times you should practically eat before you come. They say right from the start 30 mins to 45 min wait (which is some how a secrete code for an hour plus). I heard great reviews so each time I waited but it always left me with a tinge of angst before eating there. 

The last and final straw for me was today when I was told the 30 to 45 min story from the hostess who to me makes a poor hostess (absolute horrible attitude for paying customers willing to wait an hour) after I wait the entire 45 minutes (I was counting). I asked how much longer before I'm seated (party of 3). She said there are 2 people in front of me. 

After 6 parties are seated before me including 3 different parties of 3 I go to ask what gives. She sharply replies your coming up, internally my wheels are moving and I'm resistant to let this go! I ask her to explain what makes the other parties of 3 any different? She replies out of frustration and ask do I want to put a high chair at a bar. 

Even if that is the case it has been an hour, as my family was being seated we looked at each other and thought we can not spend our money here today or any other day for that matter. Considering we waited an hour to eat just to  leave is a good indication of our level of frustration. Perhaps the hostess should go apply at the post office or DMV where you are not required nor expected to have a bearing on good customer service. 

Sunday is a very relaxing day that I enjoy and I can not spend it at a place that had bad service and good food or vice versa for that matter. I'll pay extra for both they fall short here in the service and wait times.  But I can not discredit the food (every time I have eaten here was delicious) as it is the only reason for the 2 stars.

Love love love ! I have heard so many great things about this place and finally stopped in to try it out! Our waiter was great! Helped us out a lot, we had so many questions about the menu but she was very patient with us. Food was great, pancakes were delicious. I will definitely be coming back !

My gf and I love Babystacks she actually introduced me to it. I was born and raised in Hawaii so going somewhere with local 808 influences are always a plus. 

We basically go to this location because it is the closest to our house. We avoid sitting at the bar  because they tend to forget about you there. Both times we sat there we literally waited 10 minutes just go get drink orders. 

We have had a nice Asian girl (who is pregnant) twice in a row now and she is awesome! I have never had to ask for refils. I wanted kalbi and eggs and she checked to make sure it was ready instead of just telling me no they didn't have it because it is not listed on the menu. 

I usually get the Portuguese sausage and eggs with garlic rice or the chilli moco with Mac salad.

I ordered ahead for pick up the first time I was put on hold for 10 minutes and nobody picked up!!! I hung up and called a second time and finally got some service put my order in and they said it would be about 30-35 minutes!!!! Totally understandable... I live about 20 minutes away anyway showed up and they didn't even put my order in or nothing!!!! It's like they didn't even care or anything!!! Never going back there again!!! Didn't even offer me a free meal or anything for there mess up!!!

This place is horrible! Let me first say that I have gone to the babystacks on buffalo too many times to count and I love it. The food was always exceptional, as was the staff. I didn't like how cramped it was, however, so I was happy when they built this one. So let me tell you why I despise this location. The first time my fiancé and I went here he ordered a coffee that had been forgotten for a good 20 minutes so we had to request another and didn't receive so much as an apology. Then I ordered the Cinnabon pancakes, which I've had many times, without pecans because I am allergic. The waitress said oh okay no problem. Guess what came on top of my pancakes? Yep, you guessed it, pecans!! So that right there did not make me fall in love. BUT...I decided to give it another chance. We went again a few weeks later. I ordered the cookies and cream pancakes and made sure it didn't come with any nuts. I was assured it didn't. When my pancakes came out I saw a stray nut sitting on too of the pancakes...it wasn't exactly hidden folks. The waiter apologized and took them to get remade. Let me just let you know that I  am deathly allergic to all nuts; like throat closing, hospital going allergic. The manager came by to apologize and promise me that my pancakes were being remade and she would supervise. They finally come out after my fiancé was done with his meal. I start eating them, and they are pretty darn good, then I just decide to flip my pancake over and what do I see?!?! Another freaking nut on the bottom of the freaking pancake!!! Are you kidding me?! At this point I'm almost in tears. This is my life, like it's kind of serious. The waiter kind of laughed and took them away again. I'm sorry, is the possibility of me becoming seriously ill or even dying funny to you?! The manager gave me some bs and just kind of danced around it. I don't really know all I heard was wah wah wah. I wasn't just some disgruntled customer who didn't like something. This should have been taken a lot more serious than it was. Needless to say I will never set foot In this building again. Their pancakes are pretty freaking good, but not good enough to be my last meal!!

What do you do when you are waiting for a table for two and there are 5 tables of 2 and 3 tables of 4 empty? Well, the explanation was the kitchen was backed up. Not good enough. They still could have seated you and gave you coffee, especially to the customers who were standing. I left, so I can't rate the food.

I have been anticipating to eat breakfast at this place but after having some HAIR strands on my eggs, it just ruined my appetite and my experience. I will never go here ever again or any of their other establishments.  Me and the wife just stood up with disgust facial expressions and excused ourselves, my wife felt bad because she can see that I was really disappointed....

My boyfriend and visit here often. The service is always fast and friendly. You can't go wrong when you order their red velvet pancakes, the best you'll ever have! If you don't have a sweet tooth they also have amazing skillets, my personal fav is the babychick.

Had a great breakfast here Saturday. Walked in about 8:45, still lots of tables free. But by 9:15 the place was jamming and folks waiting for tables. Server was prompt & friendly.  
   We did not have to wait long for the short stack strawberry pancakes and lemon pancakes. Great light textures and flavors.  Twice our coffee was just warm but the third time was just right. This was our first visit and we are coming back for sure!  Anxious to try crepes and some other items.  The menu has several varieties of pancakes and egg dishes, including the chocolate chip pancakes I plan on trying soon.  
   My only complaint was acoustics....it was so loud conversation was hard to carry on.

Friendly staff!
Clean environment!
And YUMMY food! I will definitely come back to this location!

The food and plate for breakfast was warm at best. The server apologized and replaced with a hotmeal. The other people in the party were done while I was still eating! I will never go back there! This was not my first cold plate there.

Service was ok. Wait was long. Their coffee is great! But the pancakes were mediocre. Red velvet pancakes were just regular pancakes with food dye and chocolate chips. The cinnamon roll pancakes were regular pancakes with a pinch of cinnamon sugar on top and (what tasted like) dominos cinnastix icing drizzled on top. The hash brown were a little mushy and bland. The place is pretty clean. Very noisy. Overall I could have made a better breakfast at home.
Has the ranchero omelette and it was awesome!! The wife had the country fried steak and was one of the best I've had. Will be back

I recently went to this location and seeing there was room at the counter, asked if my wife and I could sit there.  The hostess told us to wait until she could check to see if anyone else wanted to sit there first.  She then got busy taking care of customers paying their checks, then seating guests at tables but ignoring us.  No one else was seated at the counter.  After many minutes of being ignored, we left.  This hostess never smiled or appeared gracious towards customers, whether taking their names for the waiting list for taking payments. Definitely not good customer service!
Feels like a nice home cooked meal. Everyone was real friendly. Food is affordable and their selection is bigger than normal. Definitely a place to try if you live in Centennial Hills.
The cinnabon pancakes are off the hook son! My family loves this place. Go early to avoid the looooong wait. This place gets stupid busy on the weekend.

We had a mediocre visit.  On my first visit, the coffee was weak. It took longer than usual to get our coffee and water.  The banana pancakes did not have a robust flavor.  My husband liked his omelette.  The cafe is loud because it is an open room. Our experience was just 'meh'.  However, I would go back again to give it another chance.
Great pancakes.The downside is that their traditional egg breakfasts are really sub par. Also a bit pricey for breakfast.

Ya know, this was my favorite place in Vegas until today. We are frequent customers but I won't be back to this location after the way I was treated today. My husband and I are celebrating our 15th anniversary and this is where I wanted to go for lunch. I ordered my usual, rocky road pancakes. When they came, they weren't right. They had chocolate chips on them instead of the normal marshmallows. I sent it back and was sure to be nice to the server...after all, it wasn't his fault. 25 mins later, I STILL hadn't gotten my pancakes. My husband had eaten his entire meal while I sat there and watched numerous tables get their orders. I've worked in restaurants, the common practice is to fix a customer's order before working on new orders. I complained to the manager and all she could say was "there's a health inspector here and she's not letting us work." Really? Because other people have gotten their food, no problem. Then she offered to take it off my bill. Gee, how generous of you...SINCE I NEVER EVEN GOT THE FOOD! I walked out extremely pissed and will not be back

We walked in the morning and were immediately sat. The service is amazing! Austin was very attentive and quick. We ordered the Mexican skillet and Lolo Rick's Adobo Fried Rice! Absolutely amazing and will be back for more! Highly recommend.

Have not eaten here and wouldn't. Walked in early on a Sunday morning and had to exit as quickly as we entered. There was plenty of seating available but the odor of grease was so nauseating we had to leave. My husband kept smelling his clothes hoping the odor hadn't stuck to him.

Can we say delicious?!  There isn't one thing I've had here that I haven't liked. The garlic rice taste just like my mother-in-laws and that is my favorite anytime of the day. 
The locations are a little small but the wait is never too long. Recently opened location by my house is convenient but I would go to any of them just to get a taste of heavenly goodness.
This place is awesome. Food is delicious. Its a ma and pop feel. Great service. Every person so far has been very nice and quick.

Every Sunday there's always a long wait (20-30 mins) so we always opt to go elsewhere... This time we stayed and it was so worth the wait!!!!! The service was fast and the food delicious. Our server remembered exactly what we ordered and how and didn't forget a special request. 

I had the Loco Moco which was superb! Only change I would made would be to have 2 egg yolks because I love over easy eggs and the yolk mixed with the rice. If you're not big on gravy, ask for it on the side although it's delicious! 

Had the German chocolate pancakes- so sweet, chocolatey and yummy. Paired with chocolate milk :P

I have been to this Babystacks two times now. I assumed that my first time coming was a fluke and that maybe they were understaffed that day, but today I returned to find exactly the same scenario.

When we (party of 2) arrived, there was only one person at the front counter ringing people out and no host/hostess. We stood there for about 2 minutes until another patron walked in front of us and signed herself on the sheet. As she was finishing up, someone else walked up and took our names down. We asked if the counter was first-come, first-serve or if you also had to wait for that. The host told us he had to ask the other parties on the list wanted the seats or not first. He never asked anyone and the seats remained empty, along with several other empty 2-person tables. About 10 minutes into our wait, a group of 3 guys came in and sat themselves at the counter. Nobody stopped them or even glanced their way. 

When we finally got seated, they seated us and the party before us, which was also a group of 2, in two separate 4-seater tables. There were at least two smaller tables on the other side of the restaurant, and I am certain they were already cleaned, because we watched them clean them. Why seat us in the bigger tables and perpetuate the incredibly long wait this place always seems to have?

The only saving grace of this place is the quality of the food. It is very good. If it wasn't, nobody would wait as long as you have to at this place. However, they need to make some serious changes to the way they send out orders. 

When we finally got our food, about 20 minutes after we ordered, neither of our sides were included. They were going to be a few extra minutes. After we had both completed our main breakfast, still no sides. I got chocolate chip pancakes (which are just chocolate chips on TOP of pancakes, by the way) and the other person got toast. When they finally came out, the toast had definitely been sitting out. The first time I came, the situation was exactly the same, but the waiter had apologized and said the kitchen was behind. Understandable, but apparently their kitchen is ALWAYS behind. They seem to need more staff.  

All the while, I never got a refill. The table behind us was seated after us, had their order taken before us, had paid, left, and been reseated well before we were able to leave. 

This location really needs to learn how to manage their volume. It's never NOT busy. They need to staff accordingly. 

Speaking of staff, everyone is very friendly and nice, but it's not enough to make me want to go back when there's Rachel's Kitchen in the same parking lot and a plethora of other breakfast joints just 5 minutes away.

The menu itself is no joke and neither is their food! Breakfast is my favorite meal of the day and these guys nail it. Probably my favorite place in Vegas to serve eggs benedict. The price is a little higher than average but the kind service makes up for it. The place is a tad bit small so may feel crammed at times with the layout. All in all if you're an early riser go check this spot out!

AMAZING!!! Sooooo good. Hubby and I took the kiddies and we all got something different and there wasn't a bad bite in the bunch. Seriously, red velvet pancakes are to die for. I am drooling now just thinking about it. PANCAKES PLEASE!
My only issue with this place is that it is quite hot in the restaurant and the service was a tad bit slow. But the food is worth it

We came here on a Saturday afternoon and there was a short wait, but we didn't mind because we have heard great things about this place. All of the food on the menu looked great. My husband I ordered omelets and pancakes. When we got our food, my omelet was not correct. I asked for no peppers. I flagged down our server and let her know what was wrong. She immediately ran to the back and within 5-10 minutes I had a new omelet. I didn't mind waiting because the omelet was great! The only negative part of our experience here was cashing out. We were at the register for a little over 5 minutes before we got cashed out. The host told us it would be a minute, but it took a lot longer than we expected. Overall, we will definitely eat here again.

Food is so delicious!

-Cookie and Cream Pancakes are amazing!  -Also tried the Kalua Pig Benedict and that was very tasty.
-Adobo fried rice was good (per husband)
-Service was mediocre, our server messed up our bill because it was split.
-Didn't bring out the kid's meals first and my youngest got his meal last.

A $10 meal is a fair trade to finally be rid of Babystacks in my restaurant wheelhouse. My family and friends have suckered me into eating here so many times. Simply an epic fail on making over medium or poached medium eggs. Service is always polite and personable even when missing the mark on attention to detail.

I preface this review by stating that my main complaint, and the reason I shall never return to this business is based on one policy (well and other than the pancakes I find there food to be underwhelming).  Babystacks, at all locations, has a policy that they will not seat any customer until their entire party arrives. Under certain circumstances I could possibly understand this but I was so appalled by my experience this weekend and their response that I just can't go back there. So the first time this happened to me was approximately two years ago at the Rampart location.  I was meeting a friend there for lunch, they were busy, there was just two of us. She was literally about five minutes away. I went up to the counter and they refused to seat me until she arrived I was told "we don't seat large parties until every one is here" to which I stated "two people is a large party?".  By the time she arrived there was a wait, although there wouldn't have been had they let me be seated. But we waited and ate there.  

Two years pass... till now, I admit I went back once about a year and half ago since then  friends wanted to go there. Last Friday I went there to meet a friend and her daughter who is 18 mo. old. It was about 10:00. There were a couple of people in the restaurant but it was not busy by any means and practically the whole place was empty. When I got there my friend was waiting, with her 18 mo old in hand. She didn't have to say anything to me I knew why they handn't seated her but I inquired of the host nontheless and was told we don't seat parties until everyone has arrived. Bad business policy, no one in the restaurant, you have a mother with a toddler (who anyone with kids nows is hard to do in a restaurant in the first place) and they are not busy by any means. I complained and the host asked if I wanted to talk to the manager, I said yes and this other female walked over. I thought she seemed pretty young to be a manager, maybe around 20 but it could happen so I proceed to tell  her I thought that was poor service. Only to find out (after I finished talking to her for about five minutes) that she wasn't the manager either and the entire time she was smirking without apology which again just made me more livid. By the time I finished talking to her and was told she wasn't the manager I was just too disgusted and tired to discuss this yet a third time with a party. In my opinion they should have a little common sense, if there is no one in the restaurant and it is unlikely there will be a rush of people i.e. it's not a weekend morning then why upset your customers by making them wait. So what if I went in and said it was a party of one - was seated right away and then hey I "run into" a friend who wants to sit with me - what then. This won't happen as I am not going back. 

Okay enough of my rant - you get the picture. I will not be returning, nor will my friend who promptly left with me.  As to the food, the pancakes are good, however the rest of the food is just "meh" to me. They do have fresh brewed tea. Their potatoes are frozen, I asked and the waiter when I previously dined was refreshingly honest. So it's not like there is going to be a hole in life by not going back there. So from there we went over to Lulu's - which leads me to my next review...

I have been looking on yelp for new places to go and eat, being that we are fairly new to the area. I seen the pictures of all the different pancakes and had to come and try for myself! AMAZING! I had steak and eggs and banana cream pie shirt stack Great food friendly staff and decent prices ! We will definitely return

I will never eat here again. I got corn beef and hashand it was like eating cat food. My friends toast came out burnt and 20 minutes after we ordered. The butter on the toast was just a squeeze butter. The chicken fried steak was absolutely horrible. It was just bread. Then to top it off as we were checking out the hostess didn't understand the fact that I wanted to do half cash half card. She just charged it's all on to my card. Every one was VERY disorganized.  I've heard some great things about this place. But my experience was very shitty. I will not be returning.
This place is worth their long wait. It's a small place and the food is great so what do you expect? Everything I've ever had here tasted great and the servers are always sweet as pie :)
The red velvet pancakes and the Rick's Adobo fried rice omelette are amazing! This place can be extremely busy on Sundays.

Always a long line... so be prepared bit it's worth it in my opinion. I love all the different kinds of breakfasts they offer. Hawaiian, american and filipino.  The red velvet pancakes are amazing, spam, eggs and rice is a winner... haven't had anything bad except a couple times my pancakes were a little tough and over cooked
This place is so good!!! Caution on the weekends as the wait can be 45 minutes minimum but it is worth it. Food comes out fast and is always delicious!!! Definitely worth a try if nothing else.

This place was so bad, from the time we walked in, threw our breakfast, till the time we left.

We walked in, busy and I expected that, didn't take our name down or how many in our party, forgot who was first and going where....it was so freakin hot.

Waiter came over, he was really sweet and funny, but our food came out and it was a train wreck! My friend ordered crispy bacon and it came out soggy, my husbands egg Benedict came out and the biscuits were soggy so we asked for new ones and those were soggy too, his breakfast was so bad he didn't even want to finish it. I got the country fried steak breakfast and I enjoyed it up until my husband decided he wanted to eat the eggs, I don't like eggs, he was so excited and hungry to eat them, he got them all dressed up and ready to eat and then when he went to go take a bite there is a whole corner of a plastic cut off in the eggs.

We ask for a manager and they came over and said that they had no idea where the plastic came from because all their stuff is organic and not packaged, which is bull crap, because when I walked in I could see the shelves with the cans in the back in the kitchen. And I find it disturbing that a manager would say that they have no idea where it came from instead of making us as guests feel comfortable.

It was a bad experience, it was disgusting, we will never go back there.

Man babystacks Is just amazing !!!!! :) that guy chris with the glasses and the amazing smile was leaning tables like crazy today I dined in and had a cookie butter French toast and the service was great my coffee was always full Vincent was so nice to us 

I also came backed placed a to go order and that young man with the nice hair is always on the rush and gives everybody a nice smile and attitude 

The place is organized and way bigger than the other locations I will be back :)
Delicious food. Great service. Something on the menu for everyone. Less then $10 a person. Very laidback. Will definitely be back.

The food is so good here that I get babystacks every time I go to Las Vegas. I got the turkey avocado sandwich (sorry if I didn't say the exact name of the sandwich) and it never disappoints. My usual go to is the carrot cake pancakes but I decided to change it up. The fries don't come with that much seasoning so if you like the flavor you should ask for some extra. The sandwich is fresh and especially good on sourdough toast. The meal comes with a pickle so if that isn't your thing then I suggest you ask them to not include it on your plate. Waiting time to get seated is a little much sometimes usually around 30 minutes but can go over very quickly. Food is served around 15-20 minutes. Worth it though!!

Love this place! My breakfast was delicious once again :-) I had the chicken fried steak which is never a disappointment! Fast service and great staff! Plus, the blueberry pancakes were a total bonus too ;-)

The food was good; the service and policy leave a lot to be desired. Mind-numbingly stupid staff.

I asked for milk for our coffee and was charged $2.25 for it; that's definitely a first. I asked the cashier if the policy was to charge for milk for coffee. I was told no, the server must not have understood; she continued to charge me instead of correcting it or asking a manager for assistance.

We also asked if a short stack of pancakes could be made into silver dollar sized (kid sized) pancakes. Not for extra pancakes, syrup, etc. Sure, but it's $2 extra. For the exact same amount of batter on the same exact plate. WTF?

Check your bill carefully.

This place always takes so long to seat you, the service is never on point. If you go, make sure you have a ton of time to wait. On the up side, that food is actually pretty good, if you have all afternoon to wait for it that is...

Best bananas foster pancakes! Friendly service and great food! Carrot cake pancakes and the red velvet are also awesome! Very accommodating if you'd like changes or substitutes. 
I've been there twice so far and received excellent service each time :) the food comes out fast !

This is a Sunday regular for us. The food is absolutely delicious. And the service is nice. It's a bit crowded because they are so popular, but that doesn't bother us any.
Tip: They are very busy Sunday mornings so expect a wait, and they won't seat you until all the members of your pay are present.

I come here a lot and this time I was a little bit upset at the kitchen more then waitstaff. The cashier and our server was super friendly and the cashier joked with us. But I ordered an extra side of crispy potatoes and the came out not only soggy but cold, like they were old potatoes. When i asked for them to be made crispier the next ones she brought out tasted like they just refried the other ones. This place used to be one of my favorites and now it's slowly becoming more mediocre.

Babystacks is where its at and is by far the best place for breakfast on a sunday. The worst part is everyone knows it and its long waits to get food
But the wait is well worth it because the food is awesome

Got the Kalua pig eggs benedict. It was very good! Wife got the adobo fried rice omelette that was good too. We are definitely going back again to try other items on the menu. We're gonna bring the kids next time.

Finally a good islander spot to eat. They even play island reggae music too!

Great breakfast and lunch place!  The Ranchero Skillet is my favorite!  They make their green sauce there and it's amazing!!  Pancakes are really good too. The wooden benches are cute, but definitely not the most comfortable after a while. Try to get there early for breakfast, unless you don't mind waiting.
Been to all 3 places multiple times. Rice always mushy. Mac salad no taste. Pancakes awesome!

This morning the food was really good.  Babystacks was starting to become a hit or miss restaurant but this morning which was around 8am, we had a chance to sit down immediately and was greeted right away.  Bianca took our orders and answered all the questions that I had regarding the menu.  (I always have questions.) The presentation and portion was beautiful and the food tasted really good.  The restaurant was clean and it us reaffirmed this restaurant as a good place for breakfast.
Got to the place around 1015am and it was busy (a good sign). Walt was only 30 minutes. Food was out in about 15 minutes and the selection was great. All in all the food was delicious!

Hawaiian style breakfast. Spam and eggs, spam sliders. Not bad at all. Don't come with groups larger than 4. There is only one table for groups 4+ and they will sit everybody else before that one table clears.

I'm still trying to figure out the hype. This was our second time going and my second time being less than satisfied. 

Their unique-ness comes from their huge variety of pancakes (everything from savory, like bacon pancakes to sweet, like Nutella pancakes, bananas foster, etc). 

The good:
The honey French toast was amazing! Homemade whipped cream, huge slices. Delicious. My husband really liked the bananas foster pancakes, the skillet meal, and the huevos rancheros (ordered over the two trips). The sausage patties & links were both good, though I'd only order the patties again. 

The okay: The Nutella crêpes I ordered were fine, but I didn't think anything special. 

The disappointing: Besides being pretty pricey for such a small, home style establishment (the menu is almost a la carte style), the service was definitely lacking. If I'm going to pay $25+ for a breakfast meal for two people, I expect either a lot of food (enough to be VERY filling or leftovers) OR great customer service OR even absolutely fantastic food. This place had none of the above. The entire time we ate, the previous tables' tip was at the table. We reminded the server SEVERAL times to tell the other server. It was STILL there when we left. Unprofessional. The bacon pancakes were disappointing. They boast pancakes filled with bacon. More like, a few bacon crumbs on top and maybe one or two "inside" the pancake (laying in the middle of two). 

I don't think we'll be back anytime soon.

Love the breakfast.

Family place run by a hard working, friendly family!

Great food & great atmosphere!

Always enjoy it!

I recommend a visit!

OMG that was the best French toast I have ever had. We need one of these in Tucson. They put the whip cream on the side which was good. Service is great. Everyone helps each other out. My coffee was never empty. All drinks were filled all the time. . My grandson got the pumpkin pancakes they were wonderful. The bacon is great. We will make this a regular place every time we are in Las Vegas.
Amazingggggg breakfast spot! Two egg breakfast with a side of banana foster pancakes! Amazing food and amazing service!

Before I lived in Vegas, I always made sure to come here whenever I'd visit. Now I go any time I want Hawaiian breakfast, or pretty much any time I am in the area and am hungry. So I guess I come here often. The service is always amazing, and of course the food is always great. I'm from Hawaii so whenever I eat here, it seriously is like I am back home.

My go to at home, and here in the mainland, has always been portuguese sausage, eggs, and rice. However, when I bring friends here I always tell them that anything and everything is good because I have never had anything here that I would not have again. Whether it's the pancakes, crepes, meals with rice, omelets, ANYTHING! Also make sure to try their strawberry lemonade. It is also delicious!

agreed to have a little lunch date with my best friend today and drove all the way from summerlin to try this place out. wow! this place has an at-home feel to it and a modern look on the inside that i loved. the menu consisted of many options from pancakes to crepes to omelets. was most impressed with how patient the staff was when my friend chuckled and told me this cafe closes at 3...& it was 2:25! always hate being 'that customer' but the server was a delight the whole time.
10/10 would recommend!

Awesome ! 
Pancakes are bomb. The kalua grilled cheese is fire. Highly recommend the red velvet and Cinnabon ones. I added strawberries to add some tartness on the Cinnabon for an additional fee. I recommend this location because I went to another and the pancakes were on the dry side. Only downside is that there's usually a wait and after ordering it takes a while to get your food.

I'm here a lot. Julie and Cora that work in the front are amazing. They stay busy so be prepared for a wait, but they turn tables fast and bring your food just as fast. I work in the parking lot so I go a lot ... I have not had a bad dish yet. I mean where can you get German chocolate pancakes like this?!!!

Love their breaskfast.   I could eat everyday here since is just less than a mile from my house.  They're  pancakes are divine .  When we have bras fast here we prefer to go on weekdays ,  weekends are just too full maybe an hour or more wait.
I love the warm and the atmosphere here. It is always busy during lunch hour but it's worth the wait. My favorite is always the loco moco. I always upgrade to garlic rice and with upgrade pancakes!

Waited 20 min to be seated on a very busy Easter Sunday, but once we were, our food came out fast and hot.  The waiter suggested the bananas foster pancakes when I asked what was the best one there, and he wasnt wrong! It was a specialty not on the menu and it was really good.  My son had the white chocolate chip pancake and my daughter had the red velvet pancakes.  They both loved them.  This was my 2nd time here and I will definitely come again!

Food there is always delicious  BUT I went with my sisters and one ordered carrot cake pancakes. They came out burnt so she sent them back and a girl came back WITH THE OLD ONES and says "see they are meant to be this color" to try and prove my sister (the customer!) Wrong. My sister even explained it's not the color, it's the taste. I don't know if I will return after that stupidity.

I went here to eat on two occasions, with the last being this morning.  Today, I waited half an hour to be seated as it was quite busy, which was a great sign.  Once seated, we waited about 25 minutes for our waiter to come to our table to take our orders.  Once he took our orders, it took an hour for our food to come.  Now, the previous time we came, it took a while for our food to come, but not that long.  Once thing I noticed was that the servers (three of them) were all busy doing something, but it wasn't serving folks.  It almost seemed as if the kitchen was at a stand-still, and food would just creep out one order every 10 to 15 minutes.  Once the food did come, the portions seemed small for the price we paid.  Now, this is comparing the food to the other well known "local" breakfast chain we frequent.  The food wasn't terrible in quality, it just took FOREVER to come out, and was overpriced.  I can't recommend them at all.

I really enjoy their food but the overall service could be better. On three separate occasions our order has been wrong, usually having to do with the potatoes (we order hashbrowns but will get seasoned potatoes, not a huge deal to me). Also, when I order "over medium eggs" I expect the whites to be cooked and not runny which they are always runny here so I just order scrambled. Other than that I love their selection of food!

A really good place for early morning breakfast. We got there around 7:30am craving breakfast food. 

HIS & HERs: We had random cravings so we ordered a few things to share. We ordered the WHITE CHOCOLATE MACADAMIA NUT PANCAKES, the ADOBO FRIED RICE OMLETTE, & the CHICKEN SKILLET w/ a side of CINNABON PANCAKES. We're fat, I know.

Everything was extremely good... My only qualm was that there weren't really white chocolate chips infused into the pancakes. Previously we ordered the red velvet pancakes, which were perfectly infused and I still highly recommend! The adobo fried rice was also really rich and satisfying. Wasn't too fond of the skillet personally... not as flavorful, but wasn't bad. And if you're into it, they also have sugar free syrup, which we were really happy about! Overall, definitely will return when we have an early morning sweet tooth! :)

There's a lot of hype about this place but I found it crowded, noisy and the decor was dull. I ordered a standard breakfast of eggs, bacon, potatoes and of course pancakes. Unfortunately, they were completely average. There's nothing special about this place and it's certainly not worth waiting more than 10 minutes to be seated. 

You can get this kind of food any where and probably for less money.

This place is amazing!  We went today for the first time, it is clean, friendly, and the food is delish!  Our waitress was fantastic, and we will for sure be back! I suggest you go, be prepared for a wait if it is on the weekend, because it was packed at 11 am on a Thursday!  Yum Yum Yum!

Visiting North Las Vegas to see the fam and they suggested to have the Adobo Fried Rice.

Got there just in time without any wait.  The staff is super friendly and very helpful.  I shared an order of the Adobo Fried Rice and side order of the Red Velvet Pancake with my cousin's girlfriend.  We didn't wait long for our order to arrive.

Everything was onolicious, it was much better than expected and I am glad we shared because I wouldn't have the room to eat the deelish Red Velvet Pancake. It was so fluffy and cooked thoroughly.

My husband and I had breakfast here this morning and the food was exceptional, great customer service, decent prices and very clean environment. We definitely plan on coming back here for breakfast. Also, come early! They get really busy.
Great costumer service, food and pancake are delicious!! Place is very clean they offer military discount!!!

Stopped in for a quick breakfast. My husband had the country fried steak with garlic rice. He loved it !! My choice was egg white garden omelet. It arrived wayyyy too greasy but our lovely waitress named Felicia was very receptive to taking it back and having the kitchen make a new one. The second time it was perfect. If you're looking for a less greasy omelet make sure you order it dry.

Good breakfast food. Was so excited to get a breakfast place in our neighborhood and was happy this place had more seating than the other location. We typically do our family breakfast thing on the weekend which is always packed so we started doing our orders to go. Worked great until they stopped taking takeout orders until after 12pm! Completely ridiculous that a restaurant which is only breakfast fare would limit their hours like that. I have small kids so it is difficult to take them to crowded places and wait 30 minutes for food. Guess we will just have to take our business to Mimi's Cafe who hires enough staff to handle their rush periods.

We stopped in for brunch to celebrate a birthday. The omelets were very good and the potatoes were not too greasy. 
Love the reggae theme music and the server was friendly.
This is a great informal  place to meet friends and have a meal.

Amazing! I don't know if words can do this place justice! You must go and try it. Great food, great service,great prices, and great atmosphere. The staff are so friendly and fast, we walked in and were seated immediately but wouldn't mind waiting if it were a busy day. Our waitress came right over got our drinks within seconds and once we ordered our food we waited under five minutes for our food and it was delicious.

I just want to start by saying I love babystacks cafe! Their red velvet pancakes are out of this world!  I was so excited for the centennial location to open, but what a disappointment:-(. I understand being overwhelmed but making people wait for 30-40 minutes on a Sunday at 12, when not even half of the restaurant had people seated was crazy.  At one point there were more employees in there than customers, and they just could not get it together.  There were at least 6 people standing at the food pass window.  And when we witnessed a girl pick food up off the counter (with no gloves on) and put it back on the plate, I really thought I was gonna be sick.  
My advice, if your not staffed, and properly trained, then don't open.  And clearly they were not ready.  I can't promise I will or won't go back. My favorite is the smoke ranch location, so I may just keep driving there, or I will go back to the cracked egg.

Great place to bring the family for breakfast. My kids love the pancakes. The Kalua Pig Benedict taste like kalua pig back in Hawaii. The breakfast burrito was large, cheesy and very filling. The corned beef hash was good. We also had cinnabun pancakes, rocky road pancakes, and smores pancakes. All were yummy.

A variety of pancakes to choose from. 

The prices are very good for the quality and quantity of food. 

The coffee is okay. I prefer 100% Kona coffee, so I'm pretty particular about my coffee. I drink my coffee black, so the taste and strength is good.

Food and service was impeccable pancakes of every flavor imaginable.. lemon ricotta pancakes were delicious.. I had the Lolo Rick's adobo fried rice wrapped up in an omelet. I added the green sauce that they make in house, and Hollandaise sauce was off the hook. I highly recommend adding those two, to kick it up a notch.

This place is the bomb!!! I would go back again and again and again. I love there red velvet pancakes you have to order the red velvet pancakes. I also get the garlic rice and Portuguese sausage and eggs. It's the bomb!!! Some days I crave this place. Service is top notch and waiters are friendly. Again I love this place!!!

One star because my meal rocked. I had the Hawaiian sliders. 

The wait was 30 min at 10:15 am. We waited 10 min at our table before we received water and coffee. We then had to ask 4 times for coffee refills which took about 10 minutes each time to get. That's another 40 min. I don't want to EVER have to ask. "Our" waiter never actually refilled it. Mikey was too busy. Another female waitress overheard us complaining and she refilled it once. One of the meals that came out was cold. I mean cold... The cheese wasn't even trying to melt. It was not good. We sent it back with little apology from our "waiter."  I had to ask for a coke refill. Again why am I having to do this? We then asked for butter for the pancakes. I swear to you 7 minutes passes and he comes back and says, "oh I forgot the butter, do you still want it?" No. No. No. Screw this we are done. 
As we paid and the young man asked if it was ok and we said no it was actually a bad experience for our first time there. He simply took our money and  never looked up. That's crap in my opinion. You just lost a potential customer for the duration of our vegas living. 
The "manager" looked just as lost as the rest if the staff while she was taking names to be seated and not back running the kitchen and doing quality assurance checks. What a crock. I chose not to say anything to her because I felt like that was a moot point as well. 
On a side note there is only one restroom for the males and one for the females. We used the men's once because it stupid to stand in line that long for the women's. This place is huge and it's not equipped to handle the volume.

This is my favorite breakfast place in the entire world!!

Service here is hit or miss.  But the food here is always HIT!  I have been a fan since previously known as Babycakes.  Babystacks is known for their delicious red velvet pancakes!  They are served with mini chocolate chips, whipped cream, and a cream cheese syrup.  Delicious!!

After coming here for several years, I have tried almost all the pancakes.  Cookies n cream, chocolate chip, banana cream pie, red velvet, hazelnut, honey wheat, s'mores, white chocolate macadamia (surprisingly my least favorite).  My favorites are red velvet and hazelnut.

Their seasoned potatoes are to die for!!  Absolutely delicious.  I always get a side of country gravy with them, and dip my potatoes in it.  Yuuuummm!  I love sourdough toast, and am so happy this place has real sourdough.  A lot of places say they have sourdough and serve you white.  Although their menu says the bacon is crispy, if you like it well-done, make sure you tell them (because you may or may not get it crispy).  One of my only complaints!  

There is usually a wait, especially on the weekends.  The least busy times I have found are around 2 PM.  Then you can get in and out of there in half an hour.  If you go when it's busy, expect a 20-30 minute wait.  So worth it though!
This place has the best pancakes ever!  This is our new breakfast place. They have a waiting line, however the wait isn't as long as they say it will be, which is good.

Amazing food. Ordered out of comfort zone today and greatly rewarded. Way too much carbs for my typical breakfast, but worth it once on a while. Great food every time we eat here. Come early tho or you will be waiting.

Having been to all 3 BabyStacks in Las Vegas, I'd say this is a very nice building and location compared to the other two. Food at the original is still the best, but this location's is of good quality as well. Great when you just have to have some Red velvet pancakes

This used to be my favorite breakfast place because it is in my neighborhood, but the last two times I was not pleased at all. The employees Are not friendly at all. They are grumpy young men, really weird. They do not look in your face while they take your order and they look around while they place the plates in front of you, I felt like I bother this person. He was the one with the big golden necklace. The whole place makes me feel not comfortable and welcome, it also used to be way more clean I am not sure if the owner changed or what is going on. Definitely not a place I will visit again. You cannot act like that, too much competition.
Absolutely love this place, get there early. The wait can be long but the food is so fantastic

Trying this place out since it seems to be a hot spot for Vegas locals.  My party included 10 adults and 3 little ones.  The place was large so the wait wasnt too long which was good. They will not seat you until your entire party is there.  This is different then most places as they will seat your party if more than 50% is on site.

Pro- very clean, nice staff and the pancakes are delicious.  Price is 2 dollar signs and the do charge extra for additions which is normal in Vegas.

Con- not all food came out around the same time. My niece didnt get her pancakes until 20 min after the laat person was served. Not sure qhy it took so long, the waiter didnt say, he only asked "is ot ok?". My sister said yes but i would have said NO.  Outside of that- my omlet was extra brown and dry. The tomatillo sauce tasted like it came from a jar. 

My family memebers who ordered pancakes enjoyed the food.  I am not a pancake person so i will not be back.

My kids love coming to babystacks. The food is delicious and gives you a variety of the common breakfast foods, but with a twist of extra special goodness. I'm so happy they opened a new place closer to me on Durango.

Service here is a bit on the slower side compared to other breakfast places in the area. It will take some time for you to get a seat and even more time to get an order taken. So if you are on the run, you might want to come early to have more time. 
I had the cookies and cream pancakes. They were good, although slightly too sweet in my book. My dad had the senior breakfast with eggs, bacon, and pancakes. Didn't look that amazing- actually maybe IHOP or Denny's wow only with a higher price tag. 
I'm not in a rush to head back there, but I might give them another chance later. $7.95 for 3 pancakes/9.95 for 6 on most of the special pancakes.

My husband and I love this place! Every time we have guest from out of town we bring them to baby stacks and everyone is satisfied! It does get busy so the wait is long sometimes but it's worth the wait! They need to bring back the tiramisu pancakes they're my favorite!
This location is less busy than the others and a lot larger. They always have very friendly and prompt service. Also the good is delicious! Very creative pancakes and their seasoned potatoes are yum!
Usually super busy here, but they do have great pancakes! I always get the Carrot Cake ones!

This review is solely on costumer service. I went to Babystacks a month or so ago with my husband, father in law, and daughter. We walked in and they were not busy. There were about 3 tables with people eating. When we walked in I was asked how many and told the girl in the front 4 people. She said it would be about a 5 minute wait. I immediately didn't understand because they were not busy at all. There were a couple of dirty tables that had looked like they had been sitting there for a long time. We sat there for 25 minutes or so while the staff stood in front of us and were talking and joking with each other instead of cleaning up the dirty tables or seating us. 

After waiting 25 minutes we simply walked out. As we were getting in our car a employee came out and yelled "Hey do you guys still want a table?!" I was shocked at the employees behavior and lack of costumer service. I didn't even eat the food but I will NOT be back. This place seriously needs to get their employees under control and teach them how to act professionally.

Babystacks Cafe is an amazing breakfast spot for several reasons.  First reason being...It's always slammed.  Unless your there when they unlock the doors, you're gonna wait.  That wait might vary..but you're gonna.....wait.  The second reason being that the food is awesome!

On the most recent visit, we were informed the wait would be 15-20 minutes.  I could feel the spike in my blood pressure, but this is Babystacks, and the food breaks the mouth, so we sat.  No less than five minutes later, we were seated and I was happy.

On this day there would be a coffee and a water.  The meal would consists of a Spam Scramble.  Spam is comfort food to me.  Eggs and Spam, rice with the delicious seasoning.  Oh, and add the garlic rice upgrade?  YES PLEASE!  To boot...you can upgrade to your favorite baby stack.  I dig me some of them banana foster flapjacks.  It's a cheat day.....BOOM!

Set your cell phone off to the side and enjoy your company cause a little Aloha time is gonna push kick da chest.  Chill.  It's all worth it.

When the food arrived and after asking several people for the Sriracha sauce it was everything I knew it would be.  Spam is yummy but attack the panny kakes while they are still warm!

This restaurant is my go-to spot for breakfast with friends and family that are in town visiting! Babystacks has a variety of scrumptious pancakes - we usually make sure everyone gets a different kind so we can all share. It is common for a crowd inside but the food is well worth the wait! 

They used to split checks by pairs without issue, but now only split a check in half a single time. When we go to Babystacks with groups larger than 4, that can be quite inconvenient.

Bottom line: the food is delicious, worth the small wait you might experience during a lunch rush, and best enjoyed with 2-4 people in the group.

This place fucking blows. This is my third time here because my dumb friend likes the red velvet pancakes. Every time the food sucks, the service sucks, and I'm just pissed. Everything was unseasoned and my hash browns were undercooked. My eggs, hash browns, and sausage tasted literally all the same. Not to mention my glass was empty the entire duration of my meal. And they couldn't even clear the trash off the table. How hard is it to wait on a table when you are a WAITER.
Service is great!! Food is even better!! I got the red velvet pancakes and a skillet. The food is great!!! Took my family here that is visiting and everybody was happy!
My hubby loved the red velvet cakes and I had the bananas foster cakes which were awesome. Quick, speedy and friendly service.

I love Babystacks!! The food is awwwwwwwesome and the service is terrific! Sometimes there is long wait on a busy day but it's worth the wait. I live in the area and waited along time for Baystacks and I'm exstremely happy they've arrived!!The restaurant itself is vibrantly decorated and gives a very positive environment to eat in If you're feeling hungry for breakfast, you can't miss on Indulging at Babystacks

Service was great but I had some issues. They brought me toast that was completely burned and presented it to me flipped over with the not burned side showing... Like someone wouldn't notice. Not sure if I'll be coming back. Wasn't bad, wasn't great.

Excellent food! Excellent service! Babystacks is the best breakfast establishment in all of Las Vegas. The chicken fried steak is one of the best I've had in 20 years being in Las Vegas and the seasoned potatoes were very tasty. The cowboy skillet is awesome!

No wait and fast service and they are on top of it! Ordered the biscuits and gravy and the gravy was on the sweet side for me and the biscuits weren't the greatest. Also got the loco moco and again nothing special. Maybe we'll try the pancakes next time.
Love this place good food and great prices be ready to wait a bit.But you will find out worth it.pancakes are the bomb!!!!!

Loved this breakfast and brunch place!  

FOOD:

I ordered the banana cream short stack and mmmm it was so delicious. I got this instead of the regular banana stack because I enjoy having fruit inside my pancakes, not just on top. I am so happy I got this. The custard and whipped cream that they drizzle on top went perfectly with my pancakes. I didn't even need syrup. 

SERVICE:

I'm a picky and very indecisive eater but my server was very patient and answered all my questions. He didn't rush me nor did he look annoyed (even though he might have been). :-)

INTERIOR:

Cafe looking set up. Very casual ambience. They have a tv in the corner where they played the World Cup. My boyfriend really enjoyed that.

Little known fact, there are very few things I love more than breakfast. So for obvious reasons it was on the top of my very long list bookmarks. A word to the wise, come early and come hungry! There will be a wait but it's worth it. Better than the cracked egg, the egg & I, egg works...basically anyplace with the word egg in it. Lol! (IMO anyway) :p 

Friendly staff and lots of Hawaiian inspired dishes. I just love the aloha vibe here which makes sense since Vegas is the 9th island. Zippy's chili (If you've been to HI before then you already know what I'm taking about), portuguese sausage with garlic rice, macadamia pancakes, spam & eggs, adobo fried rice omelette, and the list goes on. It's easy to see why baby stacks stands out from the pack. So Ono! 

Another notable mention are the red velvet pancakes. But my all time favorite are the bananas foster pancakes. OMG!!! Ahhh-mazing!

Best breakfast place in vegas! Best food, best service, best prices! My favorite is the Portuguese sausage and eggs with a side of orange dreamsicle pancakes!  I would go every weekend if I wasn't worried about getting chubby!!

Expect a bit of a wait, no matter what day or time you arrive for breakfast, brunch or lunch. This diner is popular with locals and tourists alike because their pancakes are da serious bomb and they have a globally-diverse menu.  It took us quite a while to make our decision as there were a number of menu options. If you're from the Islands of Hawaii, you'll enjoy the island spin on some of their offerings (the loco moco, Portuguese sausage, spam, rice, etc.).

This sunny morning prompted us to order Mexican huevos rancheros and Korean kalbi ribs with eggs and rice, with bottomless cups of steaming coffee.  Hubby remarked that the huevos rancheros were some of the best he's had over the years (and he's finicky about those)--he said the tortilla was crispy, carnitas well seasoned, eggs cooked perfectly and it all melded together into one tasty dish. The eggs on my kalbi dish were also prepped as ordered, the generous scoop of rice was topped with furikake seasoning and the kalbi had a nice easy  flavor, although a little too chewy for my jaws (dang that gristle). That still didn't deter me from finishing it. My dish came with a side of their short stack (which we upgraded to the scrumptious banana pancakes sprinkled with pecans). Lot of food for breakfast, but since it was the stick-to-your-ribs type of meal, it carried us through late afternoon before we were hungry again.

I'd been wanting to try this location and it sure delivered with tasty food and good, attentive service.

Frequent customers because of the food but their service is not the best. Weekends are busy!! The public knows this so you would think the company would better prepare, they obviously know it's going to happen too. Getting placed on the waitlist is the hardest part lol and I'm not the kind to say I arrived first but on more than 1 occasion I've walked in looking for the clipboard person and they are taking names from the 2-3 guests that have walked in after me already -_-

By far my favorite breakfast place! I always get hash browns and red velvet pancakes they're delicious! The service is usually outstanding and even though it's a busy place I never have to wait very long. They always keep me coming back for more!

5 stars for Austin, our server, who took incredibly good care of us. I asked for a bunch of crazy requests (I'm pregnant and have a bunch of weird cravings!) he got me a side of pickles, extra furikake, made sure I was always taken care of... he was so awesome!!!! Thank you

We really enjoy this mom and pop style breakfast place, the crepes are awesome very large portions are a plus. The service is on the decline, you shouldn't have to wait 30 mins on your breakfast anywhere. My only other complaint is whenever I order my steak and eggs, despite my temperature request (medium rare) it comes out well done. This place other than these two issues is a great choice for the centennial community.

Babystacks is our go-to local breakfast spot! Everything is truly amazing - from their pancakes to their Hawaiian/Filipino inspired dishes. Some of our favs include the red velvet and cookies and cream pancakes, the mexican skillet, spam with garlic rice and the loco moco. While they're usually busy especially on weekend mornings it's so worth the wait!

Had this place a couple of days ago, I saw it one night leaving smiths and decided to look at the food pictures on here (lol)... And my family just HAD to go, especially that it's right around the corner.

My mom and her husband had omelets and buttermilk pancakes ... I on the other hand had the Huntington skillet with hazelnut pancakes and THEY WERE SO GOOD! Will def go back every time I visit my parents. I want to try everything!

Never eat there again, first of all we were sat down and they have nothing on the windows so my boyfriend was literally blinded by the sun shining in because of the time of day. He made sure to ask the server if the corn beef and hash was homemade and he assured him it was. His food look like it came from a bag or was frozen. He told the server it wasn't good when he came to ask how everything was he asked my boyfriend what he'd like instead he asked for scrambled eggs and bacon. When the eggs came out they were not even cooked all the way so he said something and he told the sever he was done and didn't want anything at all, he brought him another set anyways. My food was ok except for the hash browns they were frozen in the middle, I didn't even bother to say anything because there was no reason at this point. Quality of the food is nothing special at all could have made 10x better food at home. We were very excited to try this place but our experience was very disappointing and will not being going back to this location or any other one. The employees were nice though.

I LOVE THIS PLACE. It is seriously my number one spot. It's always crowded which tells you how good it is. Never less than a 20 minute wait, unless you go super early, of course. I  had the spam and eggs the first time, so good. Then I discovered the chili moco, substitute spam. OH. MY GOD. It is the only thing I order now. It's that good. GET IT!! I love that you can also upgrade your side of pancakes to one of their Babystacks. I have had their blueberry, banana cream pie, red velvet, Cinnabon, and cookies and cream. Still working. My way through the rest lol. My must try Babystacks are for sure the Cinnabon and the cookies and cream. You don't even need  he side of syrup they send. Just delicious.
So many different pancakes! I ordered bananas foster pancakes and they were delicious! The service was good too.

Love the menu here! The option of spam as a breakfast meat reminds me of my childhood. The selection of pancakes and side items is a welcome departure from the norm. Wish the hours were longer, we sometimes get here too late!

This is my second time here... This experience gave me the courage to write a review.

There is nothing special about this place. It's boring and bland; I had the corned beef hash and eggs. The corned beef is usually a salty dish but in this case again boring. The garlic rice is even worst! The onions aren't fully cooked and there's so much what's the point of even having rice just give me a onion to bite into. My other half got the loco moco.. Why does the gravy look like water.. Not to mention taste like it too. I really wanted to like this place because it's more reasonable on prices than the cracked egg. 

Oh well...

Did I forget to mention my server helped an 8 top ahead of my 2 people so we waited extra longer to eat and put in our order. 

Lovely.

Great breakfast spot! I've been there four times and it's been great every time. Servers are friendly. Pancakes are great, but !vorite by far is the Ranchero Skillet!! The green sauce is freshly made every morning. It's super flavorful and tangy, but not too spicy at all. Best breakfast!
Love love love this place! The red velvet pancakes are the best and the avocado chicken burger is amazing also service is fantastic im hear once a week at least!

Alvin was our waiter and he was great! Very kind and attentive. The reason I'm giving it only a 3 stars is because the biscuits & gravy were cold, as if they'd been taken out of the freezer. He took them back and in less than 30 seconds come back with them. The cook just threw more gravy on top, that was still cold. The eggs were raw but the buttermilk pancakes were great. I won't be coming back.

I have been a few times now. This is a very popular location. Weekend/weekday early/midmorning there is always a wait. I dont think a wait is a bad thing in the resteraunt biz, good things are worth waiting for but me for this isnt that good. Its not bad either. Just an average breakfast spot with some times good and some times bad service. 

For the resteraunt name referancing pancakes I was not impressed with the stacks. They were good but after ordering the white chocolate macadamia nut and receiving plain pancakes with a handfull of white chocolate chips on top with a very small amount of a fine crumble that couldbe madacamia nuts. Why bother? 

I also ordered the HM1 omelette which I picked because it had cilantro however when I received it there was no cilantro. It was good just not what I was expecting. 

One of the best dishes I have had there is the Kahlua pork benedict. I really like this dish. I dont know if the Kahlua pork is made in house but it's good. Basic benedict with a nice helping of Kahlua pork and cabbage.
One of my favorite places for breakfast. Spam and eggs scramble is my personal favorite however they have a variety of pancakes and Hawaiian dishes. Don't be afraid to upgrade to garlic rice!

The food was great, no complaints there. Price was on par with other breakfast places. The service was really bad. If the service was just ok I would have rated this location 4 star maybe even 5 star. It took almost an hour to get our food, family of 4, we maybe had water refilled twice. I will admit the place was rather busy at the time but I've been to other breakfast places before when they were slammed and didn't get the type of service I received here. I would probably go again but not a Saturday or Sunday.

The food is good like always, but the service at this location needs work. When we came in, no one acknowledged us and there were 3 other groups waiting. There were workers walking around and still never asked us if we have been assisted or greeted us into the establishment. The other 2 groups ended up leaving because they actually weren't acknowledged upon their entrance as well. And even after they walked out, there was no apology for the wait and they just looked at us and said 4 right this way. A greeting goes a long way. Even if you're busy, you should still acknowledge your guests and let them know it would be a moment. Very disappointed in the first point of contact.
Great food.  Fast service.  Great price.  We will come back again for sure.  Red velvet pancakes were my favorite

It was good food, it was great service, really fast even thought they were slammed.  I think this place is good but I wouldn't pick it out to go again when there are other places in Vegas that are MUCH better.  Nothing wrong with this place, just nothing really stood out.

Love love love this place. Any kind of breakfast food I crave can be found here. Warning: the wait times are insane! So make sure to get there early. I've gone twice now, first time I got the breakfast burrito and the second time I wanted to get a little crazy and get the loco moco. This place is def a go to
Delicious food- super fresh and staff is warm and welcoming. New favorite breakfast place in Las Vegas

This place is packed a good sign.  30 mins later were seated.  Not a second later our waiter is taking care of us we order our food it comes out looking excellent I got bacon pancakes they were delish!! Overall great service I will come back on my next refeed much Mahalos!

If you're going to Vegas and coming in from north 95 or maybe want to get out of Vegas and eat somewhere normal, non-tourist filled, come here!  

Easy off and back on from 95, it's located in a small shopping center but there's nothing strip mall about it... friendly staff, clean and neat layout, plenty of customers for a Monday morning, and a veritable plethora of pancake choices for the carbs-be-damned crowd.  Their main menu goes from the basic eggs breakfast to a variety of Filipino and Hawaiian inspired dishes.  Spam for breakfast... sure.  Chicken Adobo omelette... of course.

I went simple:  nicely marinated Kalbi ribs and eggs, offered tomatoes on the side instead of potatoes or rice. since I was saving my carbs for the peanut butter pancakes.  Delish...!   Hubby had plain eggs with chunky potatoes which he said seemed kinda Or-Ida type, but which his bananas Foster pancakes more than made up for.  Momma had ham and eggs with your basic buttermilk pancakes and hash browns.  Given there was nothing left on her plate, I'd have to say she enjoyed her meal...

Enjoyed it so much, I know we'll time our next trip to make a stop here for sure...

**they must get very busy at times:  there was a sign on the door, first come first served, no reservations and they won't seat your party until everyone is present so be forewarned **

Been going to babystacks for years and it hits the spot. Here are a few tips. 
1. Weekends are always busy. You will wait. If you have a large party or small party you will wait. Make sure everyone in your party is there or you will not be seated and you will wait. Once you're seated service is usually fast
2. Best time to come is a tues-thurs when school is in session. So a Tuesday in may is perfect and they will actually sit an incomplete party when they are empty
3. Get the pancakes. This is what they are known for. Red velvet is amazing but you may need insulin after. So is their bananas foster
4. Coffee isn't the best here, pretty weak tasting, but maybe you're into that. But it's always hot and they're usually really good at refills
5. Food doesn't come out piping hot. Usually just warm. For a while I was turned off by this, but number 3 gives you the reason why we go here. But hey at least they're consistent
6. I love that they have both hash browns and potatoes as options
7. They try to move you in and out of the place quick so if you come on a busy time, don't expect to just hangout after you're done eating.

Food
--------    

[Taste] 3 out of 5: (Chili Skillet ordered with Carrot Cake Pancakes)

Food tastes of a decently cooked meal that one can cook for themselves at home. It's honestly pretty bland and needed to be spiced up with a lot of Tabasco. By the looks and taste of the dish, the cooks are very inexperienced. The carrot cake pancakes were so overcooked they were brown and had the texture of a Frisbee. The chili tasted like canned chili, microwaved and put on top of the skillet. However, the food was  definitely edible enough to finish the entire meal.

[Presentation] 2 out of 5::

Very simple presentation on a plate. Nothing fancy. I'm used to way better presentation at competing, similarly priced breakfast restaurants. Again, it seems the cooks are very inexperienced, or have little direction or guidance from the owners. 

Environment
------------------

[Seating] 2 out of 5:
