Very uncomfortable seating arrangement. Tables are too close together and wobbly. The staff also doesn't seem to understand how to seat people. There are plenty of open tables but people are still waiting in line. Booths are pretty much non-existent. The existing booths are straight-up hard wood with no comfort cushions or padding. 

[Concept] 4 out of 5:

You can't go wrong with a breakfast joint! People that love breakfast can be loyal patrons if you get the right people designing your restaurant atmosphere and concept. Pancakes, eggs, bacon, sausage, coffee, everyone loves these things.

[Service] 3 out of 5:

Service is OK. There doesn't seem to be any "type" that the restaurant hires. All really good restaurants don't hire everyone that puts in an application. Good restaurants hire the right person for the job and the concept of the restaurant.

FYI this location doesn't do Togo orders between 9am and 12pm on Saturday and Sundays. You can't even go in to order Togo. So if someone is sick and craving strawberry pancakes...Tuff. You MUST eat in the restaurant or wait till the afternoon. WOW. Babystacks knows customer service.
Great casual , good food place. We had 4 different dishes which all turned out tasty. They even had a senior citizen dish for my dad. They should hand a few more choices though. Service was great

Always a good place for breakfast.  I've tried 3 of their flavored pancakes at different times (all good) and decided on tiramisu pancakes today, but not a fan, not much flavor to it. Looking forward to go down the list and try the rest of flavored pancakes.

Awesome food!  We ordered the adobo fried rice omelet, mac nut pancake, red velvet pancake, chili loco moco and sweet cream crepe.  All tasted really good.  The chili tasted like zippy's chili and the adobo fried rice was filled with chunks of pork adobo. Once we walked in, it smelled like my kitchen when I cook breakfast! 

Service was very attentive and we were checked on frequently despite the crowd.  
Thrilled we live near this location!

Great experience. We got the banana foster pancakes and can you say heaven in your mouth. It was like eating a fluffy banana sugar cloud. Also got the piglet omelette. Mmmmm mmmm good. After eating here I probably look like a pig lol. Great place! Highly recommend!

Our family and my husbands family sides love this place, friendly staff and good food. But we just found out that they don't do anything special for birthdays. I asked if they can have one candle on a stack of pancakes for my son's birthday, but sadly they don't do anything as that they said. Hopefully one day they would, it would be nice for customers. So instead I took a picture of my son's order and got a little creative that way I can still add it to our album

Came here with my hubby and two young kids. I wouldn't describe our interaction with the hostess warm and friendly. When we asked for waters, they were giant cups-which was fine for the adults, but way too big for two little kids. Not to mention they didn't have lids on them. Of course one of the kids spilled their water. The cups were too large for them to handle. My son loved his pancakes, but the rest of us felt the food was just okay. We were unimpressed with our visit there.

For breakfast places, this is a top favorite. This is one of those restaurants that will get you hooked after your first time. All the pancakes are amazing. The Mexican skillet is by far my favorite breakfast dish. I give them 5 stars based on the food alone. Sometimes the wait can be very long but it's worth it.
LOOOVE baby stacks! Love the atmosphere and the people here! Great food.. I always get the loco moco with chilli.. YUUM and cinabon pancakes.. Can't go wrong!! Will ways come back here!

This is definitely me and my boyfriends go to breakfast spot! It's a small homey breakfast location with a wide range of pancakes but since I'm not a pancake person myself and I've been on a skillet kick for a while me and my boyfriend both got the Mexican skillet  it contains carnitas, potatoes, pepper jack cheese, jalapeños, sour cream, pico de Gallo and it wouldn't be a skillet with out eggs and my daughter got the kids French toast it comes with potatoes on the side, I wanted to substitute the potatoes for bacon because my daughter really wanted bacon but unfortunately they couldn't so I had to order her a side of bacon and strawberry's(she really wanted strawberry on her French toast) both side being about $3 each besides that most pricing is reasonable. I always enjoy the food here and usually receive great customer service but there a very popular spot so they get really busy and I don't like how the tables are all crammed together so close and in this particular visit they decided to seat us on a bar area which was fine but then I realized there's no elbow space which makes it uncomfortable to eat but all and all it's a good place to try out I definitely will be coming back here again

The service was good, food was up quick and everything tasted great! The prices aren't bad at all but there are always a ton of kids which isn't exactly what my hubs and I want to hear when we end up there trying to cure a hangover.  The red velvet pancakes are more of a dessert than a breakfast. I like the peanut butter banana pancakes the best. Enjoy!

Strengths:

The ambience is very cheerful.  It feels like it's always spring in there, even if it were the dead of winter.  The space is plentiful and well decorated.  The TVs are a nice touch.  It's clean and has an overall pleasant atmosphere. 

The food was delicious, living up to the expectations set by the other two locations.  The bacon was thick and crispy.  The garlic fried rice was an excellent complement.  The hazelnut pancakes had a well-balanced flavor, and will be a hit for Nutella fans. 

Area of opportunity:

The food came out a little late, so there needs to be some fine tuning with the process.
Rick's Adobo fried rice was the bomb!!! Great service. Support local anytime the food is this good!!!

Very good for better than your local IHOP or dennys by far. Tons of menu items and big portions . Kids menu was a little small could of offers just pancakes and bacon but nothing to gripe about . And my biscuits were somewhat stale . But if that's all there is to complain about they are doing awesome and price is for sure. I will be back time and time again !!

The Goods
1. So many options and they are all great
2. Breakfast any time of the day is awesome 
3. They have so many unique pancakes and specialty pancakes - try them all
4. Good is great

Service
1. Friendly
2. CC ok
3. Ample parking 

Ambiance
1. Has a local hole-in-the-wall
2. Nothing too froufrou, but cozy
3. It's all about the food

MoJo
1. Gotta just try the specialty pancakes!  Something for everyone

OMG, I am not a pancake eating type person. Nothing about it sounds good. When my family decided to eat at a place called babystacks I was not too thrilled. When we got there we were told it was going to be a 35 minute wait. The crazy thing is it's a Thursday morning. I wanted to use that as an excuse to leave. My family still wanted to wait. To my surprise five minutes later we were being seated.

I decided to try the corned beef hash with seasoned potatoes and red velvet pancakes(I was really living on the edge). Again OMG, AMAZING I was pleasantly surprised on how awesome everything was. Seasoned to perfection. I don't like breakfast nor do I like pancakes. I know where I will be next time anyone suggest breakfast. Everything was so good and we all loved our food. Noone in my family could complain about anything and that is unusual for us. I could see why on a Thursday it would be such a wait.

We've been here several times for breakfast and often bring out of town guests. On weekends, you may have to wait, but it's worth it if you're craving good pancakes! The pancakes are their specialty, and for good reason-- their batter is excellent, and that's what makes an awesome pancake. Their fancy pancakes are just a further demonstration of how really awesome this place is. I can recommend personally the red velvet, cinnabun, carrot cake, bacon and buttermilk pancakes (I wasn't lying when I said we've been here several times!) Their other dishes are quit good too-- I have enjoyed their skillet breakfast and California omelet; by far I was least impressed with their benedicts, but we come here for the PANCAKES, and you should, too!

I love babystacks but today was horrible !!! Today i ordered a BYO skillet with bananas pancakes like always and first i get my skillet with unseasoned potatoes, they take back the skillet and bring out my banana pancakes. After my first bite out of the pancakes i taste batter and look down and see that my pancake in uncooked. The waiter took the pancakes and came back with my skillet and once i started to enjoy my food they bought out me a fresh order of pancakes to only cut in them and have the same thing happen again the pancakes were uncooked. I couldnt even eat my skillet because my whole stomach was turned after being served my favorite thing about babystacks eating pancakes and what they r well known for.

My order was prepared wrong so they took it of the bill, but then still charged me for the side that was supposed to be part of my meal. I find that tacky. They should take the time to get my order right the first time and then at least make it right when they don't. They do have a great menu, if only they could just prepare as requested.

Wow, this location is finally open after waiting for seemed like forever. Same old good dishes served on the other locations like Rick's Adobo fied Rice, Kahlua Pig Benedict and especially the Red Velvet Pancakes. They are still trying to operate as normal as possible but still the service is still good.

Finally found a morning to try Babystacks Cafe. This place is much more than just breakfast and pancakes. There were so many options. I went for the classic chicken fried steak with eggs, hash browns, and a couple of pancakes. 
I'll be back to try one of the fancy stacks. And maybe one of the skillets. 

If you haven't tried Babystacks give them a try.

Also I love the decor. The hand burnt pine wood makes it feel very cozy. But watch the tables. They need a wider footing I watched a couple of tables almost flip on there side.

The staff was friendly and attentive. The strawberry pancakes I had were delicious! I would definitely go back soon! The only downside is that it is hard to find from the road, but the taste of food outweighs the location!

Everyone knows no matter how awsome the food is, service is what makes or breaks a business.  Ummm, everyone except Babystacks Cafe that is. Yes, the food is great. Had the honey toast (french toast), which was proportioned just right. Expect to wait, wait, wait....and wait for every aspect of dining out. Seating, beverage service, ordering to receiving your meal is Extremely frustrating! especially when the staff seems so uninterested in providing even bare minimum service. Where do they get these servers? Im sure they are friends or relatives of the owner who probably think no matter how awful a job they do, they won't lose their job. It's a real shame, since the food is great....

This location is a lot bigger than the one on Buffalo which is nice. The food is delicious as always and the service is also great and I always get my adobo fried rice. My only complaint is the old white lady up in the front wasn't very welcoming or nice either. No need to be an old grumpy fart to your customers for no reason!

I don't get it. The food is just ok. We had 8 people and 6 of the 8 had pancakes of some variety. The 4 people that ordered other items with or without pancake got their food. The pancakes came out 15 minutes after the other food. Get it together and serve everything at once. The Oj tastes like it comes out of a box (like cocktail mix) or shelf stable juice. GROSS.

I'm not one to send back my food out of fear of what would be done, but I had asked for crispy bacon and received it flimsy I couldn't eat it because I don't even think it wasn't cooked all the way. So I asked the waitress if I could get it crispy. 
Oh, I got it crispy... It was more like cremated, and extra hot. The waitress didn't even bring it back to me. It was someone from the back as if it was a slap in the face. He didn't say anything just placed it on the table. 
This place is always so busy and the food isn't any better than IHOP, just pricier. 
I will never return. Because of poor customer service.

I really enjoy this place. The food is good, I usually have great service, but a few times when they're slammed it's a little off. You can try just about anything on the menu and its be awesome. During the weekend mornings, they're pretty busy, so expect to wait a little if you try and go.

My husband and I love going here for breakfast! It's not usually packed when we arrive but by the time we leave it's a very long wait. Food is always good, there's a lot to choose from too..so be prepared to drool over everything on the menu. Great service all the time!

This is one of my daughter's favorite places for breakfast. It usually has a long wait but the sweet cream pancakes are worth it. I had a cowboy omelette today and it was very good. The veggies were tasty in the omelette and I polished it off with the pancakes. The coffee is good and strong too. I like the servers there. They are always polite and courteous and once seated, usually l  get fed pretty quickly.
Great service, friendly staff. My coffee and water were always full and my omelette and short stack were yummy.

Very good service, decent prices, and amazing quality. Food was very impressive, this was my first visit and I can't wait to go back. I would've given my experience five stars had it not been for the cashier.  Cashier was a bit on the unpleasant side, had no personality, came off as rude and appeared to not like her job. I think some coaching or customer service training is greatly needed in that area.
I loved their "different" breakfast menu! The omelette was small but delicious. I felt the restaurant was to small inside but that's just my opinion. I heard the red velvet pancakes were great!

I always see this place crazy busy and wanted to know what the hype was so I went and gave it a shot. We had to wait 20 minutes and there were quite a few empty tables and a couple bar seats available. I asked if we could sit at the bar and we were immediately seated before other customers that were already waiting. 

I ordered an omelette and my wife some eggs Benedict. The plates came and didn't look like anything special. For some reason my plate had a lone mushroom on it, and I didn't even order mushrooms in my omelette. My wife's plate could have used more sauce and the muffin was a little burnt. 

Overall, the place is not bad but is not anything special. I don't see myself going back unless I get a BOGO, but I don't see them putting any deals out.

Babystacks never disappoints. All their food is delicious and fresh, and every flavor of pancakes we have ever ordered has been fantastic. It's our go to breakfast spot, especially when we have company in town! There is usually a wait on the weekends, but it never takes very long! Food always comes out quickly too, and our servers are always friendly!
The red velvet pancakes were great.  I went at 1030 and it was a 30 min wait for the table. They only give you a lil cup of syrup and if you run out its .75 for more.
Fun atmosphere. Pancakes are amazing and so many varieties. Be prepared to wait, always extremely busy. The Smores pancakes are my favorite.

The food is good, service is friendly, prices are excellent and portions are decent. They messed up on one of our orders but got us potatoes while we waited and didn't charge us for it. It was great and we will def be back but it doesn't beat the cracked egg.

Came here for the adobo fried rice and was very happy with it. 
Service was slow. The place was busy, but not so busy that you should need to flag down multiple servers for a water refill or the check, but that's what ended up happening anyway. Minus one star for (lack of) service.
Would come back for the adobo fried rice, but I'll get it to go next time.

Service: Excellent and courteous
Menu: great diversity with Asian influence
Speed: my order was out to me super quick
Price:  very good deal
Repeat: Yes and would recommend friends

I tried the spam sliders and were way better than my expectations!

Disappointment.. We used to come here all the time until recently when they have became really busy so I started to do take out orders. I decided today that I was going to do that and I called. The girl out me on hold for 8 minutes (I have a lot of patience).. I decided to just drive there and make an order since I had some shopping to do and I could swing by and just pick up my order. I walk in through the door and the girl asked if she could help, I told her I was the person they put on hold for 8 mins. I told her I wanted to make a take out order. She then said "we not doing take out right now.. Take out orders are on hold right now.." Ok, I get you're busy and you're cooks can't keep up but you could've said it to me when I called instead of keeping me on hold and waste my time.. Smh. I won't be eating here anymore nor ordering. Looks like I will find a new place. They really need to make this place bigger and hire more people. Or go find a new spot that's bigger that can handle all their guests.

We got here shortly after they opened and there were at least 3 other parties seated. We were worried because we were in a hurry to eat and run. Once our order was taken, our drinks came out quickly as did our food. The food portions were generous at a great value. Everyone was courteous and efficient. My kind of place! Definitely a great place to hit if you're in the area. Plus: they were able to accommodate our group's diverse nutritional needs. Such big wins.

Finally made it to Babystacks on a Saturday morning. The wait was not as long as you would imagine and it moved pretty fast. It was definitely busy though. Tried the Kalua Pig Benedict and my husband tried the Loco Moco. Everything was delicious and perfectly seasoned. Also split the Red Velvet Pancakes and they were also worth the wait. Not as sweet as I had imagined them being and a short stack was perfect for sharing. Looking forward to them opening their Henderson location. Will definitely be back and looking forward to trying more dishes on their large menu!!

Love this place! Everyone raves about the red velvet pancakes but I find them somewhat bland. If you want an amazing pancake, try the cinnobun or my current favorite, the orange creamsicle! Orange flavored pancakes served with an orange drizzle, whipped cream and a cream cheese frosting/syrup. If you're not a complete sweet tooth like me, try the lemon ricotta cakes, they are huge and amazing! 
The team here is very friendly and helpful too!

The food here is unreal!
My boyfriend and I popped in on Christmas morning while visiting family and boy we are so glad we did. He had the chili omelette and I had the piglet skillet. The staff was friendly and accommodated all of our special requests. We will be returning anytime we are in town!

Food wasn't good nice had 
Breakfast at 2 locations and both times I was highly disappointed.  God tasted like it sat under a warmer for awhile. Not fresh at all. Henderson location had horrible
Customer service and food and the other location in NLV good customer service but bad food.
Other then being super busy. Great food and service. A lot of options to choose from. Would definitely recommend. Just get there early.

Meh. I don't really see what the hype is about this place. The food is ok. Nothing to write home about, but not bad either. The pancakes which seems to be their "claim to fame" didn't taste any different than the ones from IHOP or Dennys. Sometimes I think people just assume that a place is good based on the wait. Kind of like a placebo effect. The atmosphere feels like a cafeteria. Really bright lighting. The seating is by no stretch of the imagination comfortable, it's extremely loud, and tables are super close together. Don't plan on having any sort of conversation with your dining partner. I've been there twice now and the service wasn't great. Here's what bugged me both times. I like buttery pancakes. Both times, I get a stack of pancakes with ONE of those little pats of butter that comes in a foil wrap - like the kind they serve with bread at other restaurants. And one tiny little shot glass sized container of syrup. Both times I ask for extra butter and syrup and the waiter literally comes back with ONE MORE pat of butter and another shot glass full of syrup. Come on guys! Is it really that expensive to bring out a little dish of butters? Really, I'd prefer a little container of whipped butter like most places give but the pats will do- just don't be so damn cheap with them. You should get at least as many butters as you have pancakes. 3 pancakes = 3 butters. The last time we went, first my drink order was wrong and they also brought me out the wrong omelet. Granted the waiter was apologetic and took care of it, but still. Oh, and they only serve Pepsi products- blech.

The babystacks selection is great.  Tried a few and they were all yummy.  Will come back to try more.
The portions are good, and the food was delicious.
Delicious,  will definitely be back when we are in town, OMG, pancakes delicious,  food, atmosphere and service on point.

I came in yesterday and ordered the Mexican Scramble and the strawberry pancakes. My scramble was mediocre because the potatoes we soggy and the cheese which was the consistency of dried glue. My order had definitely been sitting for some time and was not prepared fresh as it had been on my previous visit. The pancakes were great however, and the service was good.

Great breakfast place. Their red velvet pancakes are a must try.  So yummy! 
This place is good, hence it's busy.  If you're in a rush, this may not be the place for you.  Your loss.  For those of us who are patient,  I raise a coffee cup to your red velvetness.

I wish I knew what the hype was all about. I've been in and out of the valley for years and had always wanted to try this place for the Red Velvet Pancakes. I hate to say but I was soooo disappointed!  The neon color in the inside was the first concern and then they had such a strange taste; nothing like red velvet in my opinion. Our omelets and skillets were either really salty or had zero flavor. I will say the seasoned potatoes were good and the sourdough toast is alright. Overall I would suggest The Cracked Egg over the wait for this place.

2 people I respect and learned to love worked here and said DON'T EAT HERE! The acting manager doesn't understand English. Ignorance is bliss here!  She went from one table speaking English well to no Bueno with complaining customers! Rude lady who doesn't care to fix! If u complain she will tell you.. YOU CAN LEAVE!

The food at Babystacks is amazing! I hear their wait is long, but we go around 12 and it isn't so bad. Their breakfast burrito is delicious and just the perfect size and let's not forget about their pancakes. The red velvet and carrot cake pancakes are so yum and the cream cheese syrup makes them even better! My only complaint is that they bring everyone's food out at different times. They really should bring it out all at once, so that everyone's food is hot and can be eaten at the same time.

I don't have any complaints about this place, everything was delicious! Our food was great and so was our server. I ordered the pineapple pancake special and my daughter had the carrot cakes, both were moist and full of flavor. My husband ordered the Mexican which we had no complaints about. The only reason I didn't give a perfect 5 stars is because the wait for the food was a little long and not everything came out at the same time but other than that I would recommend this place and I will be returning.

My biscuits and gravy were.... alright. Pretty bland. Then again I DID order biscuits and gravy from a place called baby stacks... My wife got the Cinnamon roll pancakes and they were absolutely fantastic. Price was great. 20 bucks for my wife and I. no cell phone service in the building :( Seating is first come first served, I am ok with that, but plan accordingly.
It was delicious. I will be back! Had the Portuguese sausage and garlic rice. Also had the cookie butter french toast. Service was great and wait wasn't too long even during the busy time.

Great place for breakfast and definitely a local place aware from the strip. We arrived with 12 people and we didn't have to wait long for a table on a Saturday afternoon.  Our server was fast and all out orders were quickly made and delivered.  Overall it was a great experience, and I will be back next time I am in LV.

You will most likely see a line when you arrive, but it moves fast and this place is worth the wait. There's nothing like a good breakfast and that's exactly what you're going to get here. Wish I had a picture to show, but I gobbled it up too fast.
Bad day here , not really crowded came in got seated and waited,waited and waited for 15 min went and talked to guy at register who was clueless, may have to think about service issues here

1st time going.. Wait time was a little bit longer than the usual breakfast places.. Server took a while to come take the order, bring the check ect.... Food was good not impressed with the pancakes though.

Service (several days ago) started out so unfriendly that I felt as if my presence was a bother to our waitress.  She rounded our table so quickly when taking our order, I felt as if I was at an auction of some sort.  I asked her what the WiFi password was and she told me "I don't know, go ask the people at the front"??!  Okaaaay, let me just do your job for you.  So, after standing in line for some time, I asked for the password which isn't a secret and is literally posted on the cashier stand for everyone to see.  On top of that, it is the easiest word to remember - breakfast.  AND, the cashier was kinda unfriendly too!!  Really dude?  Ever heard the phrase, treat others the way you want to be treated?  I appreciate friendliness just like you probably do. 

However, something must have happened after that.  Maybe the manager could see I was ticked because different staff started helping us, and I didn't see the original waitress until we were about finished.  At that time, she seemed to have gotten the stick out.  

Food is pretty darn tasty though, so that's a plus... So, just appreciate the good service if/when you get it.  There are at least 2 good employees vs the 2 bad employees that we had the pleasure/displeasure of dealing with that day.

First time here & I guess we should have had breakfast. Maybe breakfast is better but their lunch menu is sub par. Chicken avocado sandwich came much later than the test of the food, the bun was stale, chicken was hard & dried out & avocado looked like it had been scooped a while ago. We sent it back & they took it off the bill. Club sandwich was just OK. So a 1 and a 3 average to a 2. Disappointing.

Prices are good but you basically get what you pay for. 
Food isnt that good, they don't serve you much. People are nice, they only have one bathroom for each gender.
Love babystacks make sure you get there early cause they always busy. Food is always good and love there pancakes too. Always jam great music and very friendly too.
Yummy breakfast! The food was delicious, just get there at the right time so you don't have to wait long!
Took the little one a few times to get the French Toast. Great staff and quick food. The french fries are awesome with that seasoning they use.

Great place for breakfast. It's almost always crowded, but they are able to get you in very quickly. So many choices of pancakes, and you can get them as a side with any meal. Their skillet breakfasts are amazing, and the loco moco is excellent. Service is always very good.
Prepare to not be hungry for the rest of the day! Portions are huge and the food is delicious
This place is amazing! The food was delicious and made to order, the service was awesome and the vibe is chill. Definitely coming back again!!!

Excellent service! The front door greeter on New Year's Eve was very friendly, the server Truc was excellent, cashier was very friendly. I have been trying different cafes lately and find I always get bad service if I come in by myself, but I sat at the bar area here and I got great service, coffee was always filled, checked up on often. And they were busy! I totally forgot after getting change to tip the waitress, so I ran back in and left the tip on the counter so hopefully she doesn't think I stiffed her! Thank you for a good New Year's Eve morning :)

Came here on a Tuesday before the crowds and grabbed a spot at the counter. I stayed a while and watched it get busy at lunchtime. The wait staff was friendly, although they stopped checking on me after the first 30 min I was there. It was hard to get my drink refilled!

Spam fried rice with garlic rice was delicious, especially with a little sriracha on the side. The banana cream pie pancakes were to die for! Just about melted in your mouth and wasn't overly sweet.

Will definitely return to try the adobo fried rice and some of their other pancake varietals. But it may only be on a weekday... This place gets packed on the weekend with lines out the door!

BEST BREAKFAST WITH THE BEST PANCAKES!!! I come here several times a month for breakfast with either friends or family to indulge in a hearty meal. 
I love the friendly staff and amazing food. My go to is the build your own skillet with red velvet pancakes - can't go wrong with that!

Absolutely love this place! Went here with my brothers and the wait staff was great at explaining the menu and recommending some of their top sellers. I'm sure all the other reviews claim how great the red velvet pancakes are and I have to echo those sentiments as well. Great service and only wished there was more room because it does get packed.

Felisha was a great server! Very friendly and nice. She knew what to recommend and brought drinks and the food out fast even though it was really busy! I got a swish mushroom burger and it was good but I thought the patty could've had more seasonings. The fries were thinner than I like but they were so crispy and good that I didn't even mind. I tried my boyfriends smores pancakes and they were so delicious! The plates are a little smaller than I'd like but I'm comfortably full. I recommend this place!

Had family in town visiting and this was our departure breakfast.  We had a late start so we arrived about 30 minutes before they closed. The place had few tables left from what  I am sure was a busy breakfast service.  I have never been a fan of sweet items for breakfast such as pancakes or waffles so I was hoping for someone else to order one of there delicious choices Babystacks has to offer, and I could sample.  Bacon and eggs is more for me to start my day but I do love a good omelet to start my day.  SO that what I did. A build your own where you could select a cheese, meat and two veggies.  I ended up making a selection that was much like a "Denver Omelet" and try the seasoned potatoes and wheat toast.  this is a meal that will never let me down.

When the meal came out my omelet was a little small for my eyes but it would do the trick.  So with everyone selections I was able to try the crepes which were sweet, fluffy and delicious. I was able to try the s'more's pancakes as well which was more of the same.  Good but too sweet for me.  Next time I hope some one orders the "Red Velvet" pancakes everyone has been raving about.  As for me I might be more adventurous and try the portuguise sausage.  It has been awhile since I have tasted these and if I remember right they were tasty. 

After looking on Yelp there are apparently more than one of these places in Vegas.  If you have tried one you have tried them all.  I will probably stay close to home and not seek out the others locs.  No need to burn the gas.

2nd visit 

Ordered the Lolo's Adobe fried rice special. This specialty dish is an omlette with shredded chicken and fried rice stuffed inside and garnished with green onions.  The filling with chicken and rice was a little salty for my taste mostly because of the heavy soy sauce marinade of the adobo. 

I was also able to try the portuguise sausage this visit.  Not very impressed, it tasted like hills hire farms ring bologna.  I have had homeade portuguise sausage which had a nice spice to it. This had almost no flavor in my opinion.

Great and fast customer service! This place gets busy. We were seated and served very quickly and the waiters/waitresses were awesome! Our food  came out quick and was delicious! We got the spam and eggs with garlic rice ($1 extra, but is worth it), and the red velvet pancakes, which was delicious! They have a huge food selection...it was hard to decide what to order, but I'm sure everything is delicious! 

Would definitely recommend this place! Will be back.

Amazing food ideas all around. I always have a very hard time deciding what to order because everything look s soooooo good,,red velvet pancakes n spam sliders my top 2 picks. Im proud to bring family from out of town and my local friends to this joint.

Breakfast is probably my favorite meal and Babystacks is definitely my favorite breakfast place in Las Vegas.  I've eaten many times at the original and second locations on Buffalo, and quite a few times at the third location that opened in Centennial Hills not too long ago.  Although I haven't tried the newest location in Henderson, I have no doubt the food and service meets the same high standard as the other locations.

As the name implies, the featured breakfast item on the menu is pancakes, and if you like pancakes, you have a great assortment to choose from (including Red Velvet, Cinnebun, White Chocolate Chip Macadamia, Carrot Cake, and many more).  At last count there are 18 specialty pancakes in addition to traditional, and you can have them as your main course, or you can get pancakes as a side to complement a different breakfast item.  Watch out:  they're delicious and the stacks are big!  Go with a half stack unless you're truly hungry.

But Babystacks does more than pancakes!  Their other menu items are just as delicious and also range from traditional fare including a variety of eggs cooked to order, omelets and Eggs Benedict, French Toast, crepes, but they also have a few dishes unique to the shop.  Be sure to check out the Kalua Grilled Cheese, the Portuguese (or Spam) sliders, or Rick's Adobo Fried Rice for starts.

Things to remember:  The North Buffalo location is tiny; the South Buffalo location is much larger and more comfortable, as is the one in Centennial Hills.  Also, they won't seat incomplete parties, so have everyone together when you arrive.  On weekends, every location I've visited will quickly fill up and a line will form on weekends.  Go early to be there when they open, or bring a book to enjoy during the wait.  Keep in mind though:  the wait is worth it!

Now go get your breakfast on!

Food was ok. The price a little high for the food portions. I order a Nutella crape with banana it was $4ish literally it was a single small crape rolled like a taquito. My son order biscuits N gravy with sausage link. I felt like the lols where so small. I order eggs portugués sausage yup it was one sausage.

I was just going through my check ins and saw I did not review Babystacks!!  This place rocks; I think there is something here for everyone!  Pancakes, real good pancakes, can't wait to eat here again on my next visit to Vegas.  Sorry, it's been a a couple of months since I went here, but, if you are thinking, how good can pancakes really be; wait no longer, get yourself in here and get some.  You will not regret it.

We enjoyed a Saturday morning breakfast here. The blueberry pancakes were simple and DELICIOUS! My boyfriend enjoyed the S'mores pancakes as well. The service was great! Our server was so friendly. And multiple employees came by repeatedly and offered to refill our coffees. It was very nice.

Great place for the traditional breakfast - pancakes, eggs, etc and also for the unique twists for the adventurous palate. 
Kalua pig benedict - a traditional eggs benedict with shredded kalua pig on top instead of the ham. Super flavorful, I actually prefer this version.
Adobo fried rice omelet - this is a monster! Maybe share with a friend and split some pancakes too. A generous portion of adobo fried rice wrapped in a very thin egg omlete. The fried rice is the bomb and hearty. Well seasoned and delicious.
Also, so many pancakes! So many flavors! You'll have to make at least 5 trips back just to sample them all. Yum

Honestly, I don't understand how so many people seem to rave about how great this place is. I have been there 3 times. Each and everytime I had poor service, with cold or barely warmed food.Am I really the only one who gets terrible service and cold food there? 3 times is enough for me, I'll never go back.

Our server Lorena was the best server I've had in such a long time. The food here is definitely something to check out, and as a transient person, I have to admit that this is place is definitely fresh and unlike other places I've been to for breakfast food. The wait is a little long, but that's to be expected from how popular it seems to be. The food is great. Their food is sort of an American/Filipino/Hawaiian mix that is truly a unique combination. We ordered Lolo's adobo rice, Kalbi ribs, and the Nutella crepes. It was so good. I would definitely recommend this place to others. It's well worth the wait to eat here!
Nice local place for breakfast. They have some yummy pancakes here. Love that they're from Hawaii too. They definitely show you much aloha.
Food quality was excellent. I wish the restaurant was bigger to include the bathroom. The wait time was long but I imagine this is common due to the food quality and friendly staff. Mahalo!

So disappointed for the second time.   I ordered and omelet.  Eggs were overcooked, the avocado was not ripe, hash brown were cold.  My husband had bacon pancakes which were greasy.  The bacon was as hard as a rock.  We will not be returning.  The 2 stars are for the coffee refills.

Wow after trying the well known red velvet pancakes here I can officially die a happy woman. I am not normally a sweet tooth kind of gal but holy moly these pancakes had me at first bite! They were so so yummy. They were moist and perfectly sweetened. You didn't even have to use the cheese cake frosting on the side.We also tried the Oreo pancakes they were also very delicious and moist but the red velvet is where its at.

Now the normal breakfast omelettes, eggs, skillets, bacon, sausage, etc. is your typically breakfast nothing too special. I got the scrambled eggs and the corned beef hash. The eggs were good, could have made similar at home but the corned beef hash was wayyyy to salty. I took a few bites and then couldn't finish them, yuck.

This place is well worth it if your coming for pancakes but be prepared for a wait. Oh and they won't seat you unless your full party is there. I will come back!

Oh man!  What can I say.  We love this place.  It's or favorite breakfast spot of all time.  The wait is always worth it on the weekends.  I'm by all means not a pancake guy but I order their pancakes every time I go with a skillet. We haven't had 1 bad experience.

This is our go to breakfast place in Vegas. Mexican skillet is fantastic. Pancakes are on point. Also they make some great coffee. Sometimes on the weekend the service is lacking but the food more then makes up for it.

This is my second time coming here but my first time to check in I believe. Today I got the adobo omelette and it was sooo good! I would definitely go back to this place not just for their pancakes but for that as well. 

I really like that they do give you the option if you would like to upgrade your pancakes to something that aren't even ordinary breakfast pancakes ! They are very interesting pancakes and very good! I would definitely go back especially for their red velvet pancakes !
Can't ever go wrong here guys!  If you want to feel like you're in Maui eating breakfast go here!  Same great food and service!

Finally tried baby stack. They are crazy busy on the weekend but it seems like they are not that bad on weekdays.
Ordered adobo fried rice in an omelette and it was ok, the adobo was really salty and I feel it's missing something for it to be amazing. I've ordered the pancake on the side and I got the red velvet pancake and that was good, really fluffy and I like the whipped cream on top and the cream cheese syrup. 
My fiancé ordered the loco moco with the potato on the side and he said it's better than the real thing in Hawaii  and the potatoes were cooked perfect. Idk how that's possible, but he became a fan of loco moco now lol.
The waitress gave us good service too and the price is decent. I'd come back to try more of their food.

Each time I'm visiting Vegas, I always stop by BabyStacks! It's one of my favorite breakfast spots here. Inside it's homey with a family feel, and service is always great. I usually have to wait a bit each time I visit though, at most half an hour. 

The red velvet pancakes are the best I've ever had- nothing else comes close! It's not super sweet, and there are chocolate chips in the pancake itself, and the cream cheese drizzled on top isn't sweet either. They're perfectly moist as well.

If you're hungry, the chicken adobo fired rice wrapped in an egg is also bomb too. It's pretty heavy though, so you may go into a food coma afterwards haha. 

Last time I was here I got the steak and eggs, opting for the garlic fried rice. Just a forewarning- they don't go easy on the garlic here! It was satisfying until the last bite.

I'll be seeing you guys on my next Vegas trip!

BEST BREAKFAST PLACE IN TOWN!! 
Great service and great food! Wish their restaurants were just a bit bigger in size.  They would still make a killing!

My wife and I order the skillets with scrambled eggs, delicious.  My 2nd favorite are the nutella crepes, We've found that instead of waiting anywhere from 15-45 mins for a seat, just call ahead and have them make your food for you for pickup.  All three times they've had my food ready within 20 minutes so by the time I got there it was ready.  And it tastes just as good as if you sit in the restaurant and eat.
This place is soooooo good. I almost like it better than Denny's and ihop! The only problem is they aren't open all the time and it's always packed for breakfast.

Get on the list and shop for 20 min in the strip mall on sat and Sundays. After 130pm it slows down.   They have a great Hawaiin vibe, with Asian backround, so its so good!   Kalua Pork benedict is to die for, the pancakes are ridiculous and amazing creations.  5 star breakfast, always a wait on weekends!    5 STAR RECOMMENDED!!

For the most part this is a good place to eat. I love their food. It really is nice to have many types of pancakes to choose from. Their specials are always fun to try. Sometimes services is a little slower because it does get busy. Prices are a bit higher.

This is definitely my go-to breakfast spot. The Nutella crepes, red velvet pancakes, fried adobo, the breakfast potatoes, everything is amazing. I've had literally almost everything on the menu and it's always been perfect. Is there a wait? At times but it's bc this place is awesome and word is spreading. Do I care? No bc it's totally worth it. If I wanted fast food, I would go to a place specializing in fast food; just saying. Also, there is always take out if you don't want to wait and unlike some other breakfast places that shall remain nameless, they know exactly how to prepare a take out order; meaning they line styrofoam containers with tinfoil so my hot food doesn't sit directly on the styrofoam and cook to it which is a huge deal. So basically there is absolutely no reason you shouldn't be eating here. I'm going to end this now because it's Saturday so I'm off to have breakfast at Babystacks like always.

Could have been better! I thought the place was Closed because of the DIRTY glass front of the restaurant. Food is okay. Service is alright. A couple of Flies did some Fly bies
when I was eating. I stared at a Dirty duster behind the counter Gross! You guys have potentials just Clean the Place! Not very Appetizing specially early in the morning when most of us would like to have very Good start on the Day!

I discovered Baby Stacks 2 years ago. 
I moved to Minnesota to then realize how much I miss the delicious, mouth watering menu at Baby Stacks The logo they have is really simple and inviting. At this location is big and personable. The staff is friendly and professional. The menu has a nice variety which I'm very fond of.

My favorite item to order here is the Mexican skillet So flavorful. 
The potatoes are nicely cubed shaped, which compliments the entire dish. On top of the perfectly golden potatoes cubs is the shredded pork. The shredded pork is  moist, breaks apart simply. Paired with jalapeños, and eggs served on top. On the side fresh Pico and sour cream and a side if buttermilk pancakes.

The hot tea is yummy served with honey.

When its time to pay the bill you go to the front and pay. 
 I recommend this establishment.

I've been looking for a great crepe place for quite sometime since I moved to Vegas. I was surprised to find this one in my area of town. Although the restaurant is small it reminds you of a family owned business. I ordered crepes with nutella and strawberries. First the waitress brought out the wrong meal but had no problem taking it back and my correct crepe came in less than 10 minutes. When I received them they were delicious! Perfect crepe texture and fresh berries. I defiantly recommend this place. This is a popular breakfast spot, especially on Saturday morning, so get there early or plan to wait in line for a long time. I think the wait is semi-worth it but I gave it 5 stars because if you walk right in and sit down your food comes out fast, and delicious.

Average at best, and the service is always slow. I'm very disappointed that they will no longer be serving the Orange Creamsicle pancakes. If you get one of the sweet pancake opinions I suggest getting a side. The pancakes are very rich!
Best breakfast in the Northwest hands down. Great service, good prices. The red velvet pancakes are to die for. Only down side is there is usually a wait, but that's because the food is good!
Excellent breakfast! So many pancake options, it's hard to choose. Everything was delicious.

Had a great breakfast here. I had the Kalua pork eggs Benedict. It was delicious. The pancakes were very good too. The girls had eggs and cakes and they eat them up. 
Get there early, there is usually a wait after 8:00a on the weekend.

I visited Baby Stacks for breakfast, after waiting for 30min we were seated. We ordered our our food which was pretty good. Once we were fo idhed eating ee waited over 15 min for the waitress to return. Tired of waiting, we took the check to the register, paid and left. As we are walking to our cars the person who waited on us was running after us yelling and accusing us of not paying out check. I was insulted, embarrassed and furious. I went back to Baby Stacks few days later and spoke with the manager who quickly dismissed me with a slight apology and a "we'll follow up with you." Of course  I never heard back from them. I never went back either.

Eh... Their food is decent but you feel like you are eating on top of other tables.... if you have to get up to go to the bathroom, you're bumping into 5 different tables just to get up. The waitress' are so busy and take forever to refill drinks so thats frustrating. They are also so busy and their waiting area isn't much of a waiting area so it's not even worth it to go here on a weekend anymore.. You try to pay your bill and you're having to move constantly to get out of the way of the hostess seating people and then you lose your place in the long line of people attempting to pay.
The food was amazing as always but the waitress Shawni was incredibly rude. I've been going to babystacks for years and that was the worst service I've gotten
Pancakes were great. Worst Loco Moco I have ever had. Hamburger patty just hockey puck like. Rice was dry and kind of stake. Staff did not seen to care. I won't be back.

Delicious and great service, even with a packed house. I love the mix of traditional, Hawaiian, and Filipino breakfast options; it was so hard to choose! That just means that we have to come back for more.
Everything was very good, I built my own omelet with strawberry pancakes on the side. The service was just as good, I'd recommend stopping by if you're in the area.

This place is great! Went for brunch with my boyfriend the other week- he ordered the adobo omelette and I got the Nutella French toast. Both were very delicious!! Lots of items on their menu. Definitely coming back soon to try the corned beef hash!

I absolutely love this place! The customer service, the food, and oh my gosh those pancakes! My husband and I always share a different kind everyone we want to try it all! It is worth the wait on Sunday's!

I go here for brunch almost every weekend! I try something different every time and have yet to be disappointed. Highly recommend the breakfast burrito and of course any of the specialty pancakes. There is usually a 30-45 minute wait on Saturdays and Sundays but service is very fast and friendly!
This place is so good. Best pancakes in town and their chili is good too. Potatoes are good as well and although they're always busy, their customer service is always great. Bathrooms are clean

I heard this location was opening up a few months ago and was pretty excited since it's right around the corner from us. We've been to one of the other locations in the past and liked it a lot. Naturally since it's a new spot they were really busy...but they have a lot to work on.

It looks like they run specials on the whiteboard up front which is cool. I decided on the cookie butter french toast and my wife had the biscuits and gravy. The french toast was decent but there was a lot of egg leftover on the sides of the bread and they basically just threw a huge scoop of cookie butter on top. It wasn't anything special and I can't say I'd order it again. My wife's biscuits and gravy was really good at the other location but at this one it didn't even come close. The biscuits were dry and the gravy was super plain, almost flavorless. 

The whole experience just wasn't what we expected since we liked the other one so much. While the service was ok, not everyone was friendly and they seemed to be understaffed. We walked in and had to wait almost 45 minutes but at least 10 tables were open. They must have turned away 5 or more parties because of the long wait times. We'll be back in a few months to see what's happening but if you're a fan, I'd stay away from this location for a bit.

This place DEFINITELY lives up to all the hype. The food was amazing, the service was amazing. We had Felicia and she was so incredible! My husband and I had been kind of avoiding this place cause it's always pretty busy, but I'm glad we stopped in today. Highly recommend going here and they offer a military discount!

We came here for breakfast and noticed they had Loco Moco on their menu, I love Loco Moco!!! (hamburger above rice, egg, and smothered in gravy) and it was disgusting. It honestly tasted like powdered eggs, over hard rice and an AMPM frozen burger patty. They skimped on the gravy and it wasn't the right type of gravy. If you're going to offer it on the menu then cook it right. We also got pancakes eggs and bacon and that came out decent. Still waiting for a exceptional breakfast spot in the area
One of our favorite places for breakfast when we are lazy. The Wife & Kids get there sweet tooth fix and I get my Hawaiian fix on! Garlic rice is an awesome option!

This place has everything I love! The service is super friendly, the food is always consistently delicious (Rick's Adobo Fried Rice!!!), not to mention the creative selection of pancakes (Cookies & Cream, Red Velvet, & Cinnabun... Yes please!). One of my favorite spots right now.

Breakfast is my favorite meal of the day, and this place does it the best! This place is always packed by 10 am on the weekends. One time we had to go someplace else for breakfast because it would have been a 40 min wait. I'd say it's worth the wait, but eat a snack before hand! 

I went here with a friend and got the Cowboy omelet which was amazing. The eggs were cooked just right without being too dry. The cheese was melted perfectly and everything inside the omelet was cooked well. I also got a side of the red velvet pancakes which took longer to come out. It was worth the wait though because once it came out, I couldn't put the fork down! I looove red velvet and these pancakes lives up to its name. It was soft and fluffy and not too sweet. I was given a side of sweet cream cheese glaze which wasn't overpoweringly sweet like some can be. 

Our waiter was very friendly and would keep me updated on my pancakes to let me know that I'm not forgotten. She was very patient with us as we kept asking for a couple of minutes to think about our order as well as catching up. She also knew the menu well and suggested some of her favorites as well as customer's top choices. The restaurant itself felt like most breakfast places, which makes it feel homey. 

I will definitely plan to come back when I visit Vegas! I really want to try their Hawaiian dishes.

Great prices and better food. We, my wife and I and our three kids, had the following: lemon-ricotta pancakes, red velvet pancakes, cookie butter waffles, strawberry sweet cream crepe, adobo fried rice and ranchero skillet. I tried everything and it was all so good. The lemon-ricotta pancakes were the best thing on the table and I could eat 50 of them and not get sick of them. They come with a lemon syrup which is more like a thinned down lemon curd pie filling. Mouth is watering just thinking about them, now, about an hour after brunch and still very full. Wait staff was great and the 25 minutes we waited for New Year's Day brunch went by quick in the busy and quaint restaurant; but, then again, any wait would be worth it for this delicious breakfast spot.

Two thumbs way up!
Please make gluten free options!  I've heard such amazing things about this place but we can't eat there due to allergies.  :(

I saw this place many times. Always had tons of people waiting outside to be seated. In my mind I'm thinking why is everyone waiting for pancakes???until I was told that they make more than that. I grew up in Japan and in Hawaii and pancakes is not my norm for breakfast food. Someone said they had adobo omelet. Say what??? Local food right down the street from me?  How come I didn't hear about this place before??? I came just before it got crowded and ordered the adobo omelet. Yummy!!!!!! Just like back home! Huge too!!! I could only eat half of it and that was pushing it. I could of stopped a few bites before but it tasted so good. I will definitely be back to try other stuff.

I've eaten at their other location on Smoke Ranch, it was fine. This place was so disorganized it's hard to believe they're still in business! We were the only customers in the place, it took 10 minutes to get a water, milk and tea. We ordered 2 hamburgers and one breakfast. One hamburger and the breakfast came out, it took about 8 minutes to get the second burger, which was very mediocre. .???  What's going on in their kitchen? Later in the day, I got sick from the food. Cross contamination is my guess. Go elsewhere. This place does not have their act together.
I really like this place, I always get the Ranchero skillet. I love the green salsa, it is a very delicious and filling breakfast.

Oh man I don't know why we haven't tried this place a lot sooner! I got the red velvet pancakes and they were fantastic! Our son got a short stack of chocolate chip pancakes and he loved them (the whipped cream tastes homemade and was his favorite part). My husband got the adobo fried rice omelette and a short stack of the cinnamon bun pancakes & he was very impressed. Our food came out quick and fresh. Can't wait to come back and try the Eggs Benedict!
Love this place! Great variety of different types of pancakes as well as other breakfast options.

Extremely disappointed in the kitchen staff here. Does anyone know the difference between over easy and over medium eggs? When the egg whites are runny, that's more like sunny side up, not even over easy. It was taken off the bill and they asked to correct it, but it already grossed me out trying to eat it.

This place is still the best breakfast place in Vegas! I love that the new location is in centennial and it's HUGE!!!!!! Like wayyyy bigger than the first two locations. They're still working out the kinks as it is a larger store. They've got a new special, COOKIE BUTTER FRENCH TOAST!!!! It's the new craze that everyone's been drooling over! It tastes amazing and it's such a huge portion that I can't even finish it! The cookie butter is sandwiched between the toast, topped with their homemade whipped cream and pie crust crumbles!!' Are you drooling yet kuz I am. They got banana foster pancakes, I was hesitant to try them because I didn't want anything too sweet but wow it's amazing, it was the perfect amount of bananas, caramel and whipped cream! Service is wonderful as ever, very attentive servers. The hosts are friendly and welcoming! Thank you Babystacks for opening up in centennial! I can't wait to come back!
Really pretty good coffee and the choices of pancakes was silly. Great family brunch today.  The single nutella crepe was awesome.

We are regulars at the Henderson location and Love it..... Decided to try this location..... It's a lot roomier than Henderson and Love the Island vibe in here..... Had the Kalbi and Eggs.... It was Absolutely Delish.... not too fatty very flavorful...
Excellent breakfast. Great pancakes, omeletes and potatoes. A must whenever we are in town. Expect a wait but well worth it.

Wow the food is delicious we ate their 2day in a row, Trac the waitress was so nice food was made quickly, I had the kalua eggs Benedict on the 1st visit my husband had biscuits n gravy, the 2nd day I tried the Portuguese fried rice omelet, so delicious, husband had loco moco very clean place, the music was awesome too. I highly recommend this place 5 stars for me.
Had the Piggy scramble. It was the best! Had it with wonderful Cinnabum pancakes.with it. Five stars all the way.

My boyfriend and I came here for the first time this morning. Did not catch our servers name but on our receipt says Vangie.. hopefully correct because this young lady was very good. The food is fairly priced in my opinion. I had the orange creamsicle short stack with a side of spam. Ended up eating the rest of my boyfriends Loco moko because he was so full from his delicious red velvet pancakes. We enjoyed our first experience here and will return.

I've been there twice now and they won't sit you if you don't have a full party, which I can understand if you have a big party but we had a party of 3!! We were waiting for 1 person. So my wife and I sat at the bar we wanted a cup of coffee while we waited, I asked on of the bus girls if we could have coffee so she walked over to the hostess and told her and she shook her head no, we waited a few more minutes and no service we were ignored. I will never go back to this location.... They are very rude!!!

I was told by a buddy, and fellow Yelper, Baby Stacks was the bomb and couldn't wait for the Centennial location to open so I could give it a whirl. We slipped in on a Sunday morning about 9:00am and were promptly greeted by smiling personnel, but were told it would be a few minutes. Although it was relatively busy, about half of the tables were empty. We were finally seated and were made to wait for beverage orders and then again made to wait before giving our breakfast order. The party seated after us and seated right next to us was taken care of first. I opted for the Chicken Fried Steak, which is listed as Country Fried Steak on the menu. It comes with eggs, like you would expect, but you can opt for garlic rice instead of potatoes. What? Garlic with breakfast? OMG! Awesome! The meat was cooked to perfection and the breading was fantastic. I would rank this among some of the best CFS in Vegas. I ordered the eggs over-easy and they were a little on the runny side, so keep that in mind when ordering your huevos. My meal came with a choice of bread, which included buttermilk pancakes, or an upgrade to any speciality pancake. I chose the bacon pancake. Bacon baked right in. Everything is better with bacon, right? The Mrs. opted for the red velvet pancakes with the cream cheese syrup. Wow! It was like dessert for breakfast. I am sure there are healthier choices on the menu, but if you are going to do it, you might as well do it up right. The food definitely lived up to the hype. The service, not so much. We'll just chaulk it up to working out the kinks during the first week. I will definitely be back and can't wait to see the looks on the faces of the Breakfast Club when they bite into the specialty pancake of their choosing.

Definitely prefer this location to the one off Buffalo-- way more seating.

I had the kalua pig benedict with browns. I give this four stars, only because the pulled pork could have been a bit more flavorful-- it helped when I dunked bites in ketchup. It also could have benefited with stronger texture-- the bites were a bit soggy toward the end.

Been dying to try this place and since we visited LV this past weekend we finally got a chance. My cousin lives in LV so that's how we found out about babystacks. Took us about 25 minutes to get seated during normal brunch time on a Friday morning. I ordered the spam scramble with garlic rice and got a side of their glorious red velvet pancakes. Both were aaaaaaamazing!!!! The red velvet pancakes were so moist and with the combo of the whip cream, chocolate chips, and cream cheese frosting, OMG!!!!! to die!! My fiance ordered the adobo fried rice omelette and that was phenomenal to!! Good service and great food!

Didn't quite live up to the hype. All pancakes on the menu sounded amazing but they weren't as soft and fluffy as I would've hoped. Prices weren't cheap either. 

S'mores and cinnamon roll pancakes were the most memorable, bacon sadly wasn't so hot.
Just meh.  The hash browns were kind of gross.  Pancake selection was pretty good though.  Crappy cafeteria seating.

Whenever we fly to Las Vegas, our family always has somewhere new to take us. This was one of the new places they wanted us to try and after eating here, I went back to Hawaii and told all of my friends and family where to go to eat! 

The staff here is friendly and attentive. If we weren't too sure on what to eat the waiter ( I forgot his name ?) was very helpful in recommending what to eat! They also kept coming around and asking if we needed more drinks and if our food was alright. The service was amazing! 

Next, the food! I loved every last bit of it! We ordered what we wanted to eat and we all shared our food so we could sample a little bit of everything. I'm very happy to see that they have some local Hawaii favorites like spam and Portuguese sausage! 

Overall it was an awesome dining experience! I'm glad I have someplace I can go if I miss the food from home!

You're likely to have a slight wait if it's the weekend during breakfast or lunch - but WORTH THE WAIT. Friendly staff, great service, super clean and food comes quickly. Nice sized portions and food is Delicious. A neighborhood gem.

This new location in the northwest is probably the most spacious one of the other locations.  I like how Babystacks has a variety of not just your average eggs and bacon breakfast dishes.  They have filipino and hawaiian style dishes as well.  Their pancakes are fantastic!  I've had the regular, red velvet, and banana pancakes.  All were perfect and just the right size!  I've also had the Portuguese sausage with eggs and rice.  I like how they cut the sausages small and semi crispy (just how I like it) and it's not greasy.  I've also had the adobo fried rice omelet.  That dish can probably fit two people because it's so huge!  The only thing I didn't like was the garlic fried rice.  I wasn't a fan of the onions.  Other than that, this is an above average breakfast/lunch cafe!
Pancakes are delicious...but if you haven't tried their skillets you should!!! SO GOOD! Definitely go if you haven't already.

I don't understand why others have a problem with this place.   Excellent food, reasonable prices and extremely good service.  Everything we order there is delicious.  They get very busy so the best advice I can give is to get there super early.
Food was delicious and the servers were fast and friendly.  My favorite pancake location.

Decent specialty pancakes and decent service the three times I went. I will continue to go and get something different every time, and I don't see why you wouldn't want to come here. Not too too pricey in my opinion, never had a problem with my order, and the people there are always willing to satisfy your needs. Love it!
Best Pancakes in town. Expect a 15-30 min wait time, worth every minute. The other options besides pancakes are just as good.

This is the most delicious breakfast place in Las Vegas. Everything from their biscuits and gravy to their pancakes is absolutely superb. Anytime I've gone I haven't had to wait more than ten minutes, even during the busiest times. The staff is very attentive and friendly. Can't get enough of this place!

Just ate here and will not be back. First of all the seating was uncomfortable,  the booths are hard wood. The orange juice was from frozen concentrate. Ordered a ham and cheddar omelet, seasoned potatoes and asked to have onions and bell peppers added to the potatoes. On the side I ordered the banana cream pie pancakes. The first omelet was burned and included onions and bell peppers. I  tried the pancakes while waiting for the re-order, they were bland and tasted like flour, there were two pieces of banana cooked into the pancakes. The second omelet arrives, again burned eggs, not very flavorful,  and I was unchanged to add cheddar on the inside. Needless to say, despite starving, I could not finish the meal. When on my last bite, after my boyfriend was done with his meal, the waitresses finally returned to the table to ask "was everything ok", not giving us a chance to answer, she disappeared into the kitchen. When we went up to the counter to pay, we were asked by the lady how everything was, when I gave my opinion and pointed to the almost whole breakfast that I had left on the table, she made no offer to adjust the bill. Then our waitresses walked up to the counter and started arguing with us that had we said something at the table, she would have adjusted the bill, then repeated herself in saying it, I walked out and left my boyfriend to deal with her. The whole experience was a gross fiasco.
Slow service, but the food is ok. Nothing to write home about though.  The seasoned potatoes are better than other breakfast places in town.

First of all, the only reason this place is getting a 4 star rather than a 5, is because if it's a weekend day, the wait is always at least an hour. Maybe it's time to expand? Or have a to-go menu?

I was sent over to Babystacks via a friend in the area. I had the red velvet pancakes with my eggs and hashbrowns. They were to die for.  Like dessert and heaven made a baby.

I can't remember what my mom and husband ate, but we all left very happy.

I'll be back, but on a Monday morning. Figure out how to improve traffic so locals can eat here on the weekend, too!

Cookie butter French toast is a must. The Huntington skillet is also a favorite.  I feel that this location is better than the other one, as this one is larger, and the cookie butter French toast is plated better.

The wait was about 45 minutes for this Hawaiian breakfast joint.
I had Biscuits and gravy with bacon sourdough toast and 2 eggs the gravy was meh a bit gritty like just before it breaks the eggs were uneventful the bacon was good.
the rest of the crew had;
1. Rick's Adobo Fried Rice" (adobo fried rice with shredded chicken wrapped in  omelette) everyone tried it and liked it.
2. Hawaiian Benedict on a Hawaiian roll with spam and a poached egg covered with brown gravy. this was also good.
3. Piglet omelette bacon sausage and ham and cheddar cheese plate was clean and she had a content smile 
4. Bacon pancakes with bacon pieces in and sprinkled between the cakes maple syrup gobbled down and well liked.
5. Cookie Butter French Toast with whipped cream and nutella dusted with pie crust and powdered sugar. super delicious she had a major sugar hi too.

the staff was friendly and place was clean.

Went here with a friend for breakfast and it has it's good and bad points. First things first they do not take reservations here and they will not seat u if you whole party is not present. That being said the wait to get a table here is crazy. We were in on a Saturday morning and the wait time was 30m to an hour for a breakfast joint!!!! We were seated conceded to taking seats at the counter because we had waited 45m and did not want to wait longer for a table. 

Waitress at the counter was nice enough but nothing special service wise.  I ordered the banana pudding pancakes with a side of bacon and my friend ordered the breakfast special. The prices were reasonable but I didn't like that the syrups were an extra cost (wth- where they do that at?) but since I had an embellished pancake I did not need syrup. (Also note no sides are included with the specialty pancakes.) 

Overall the pancakes were really good and the bacon was cook nice and crispy. I do however feel that the pancakes were kind of smallish but still filling. I think the specialty pancake options they have are very original like red velvet, Nutella, various fruit flavors so I would like to go back and try some of the other flavors. Not yet a favorite place of mine but it could happen. I would definitely come back and I think I would recommend to others.

It's such a treat to have a Babystacks on the Northwest side of town! Definitely is it one of the best dining options there is in the area. 

Baby Chick (Skillet) $9.50 - Mmm-mmm! This is one tasty skillet that has mushrooms, chicken, spinach, and cheese. On top of all that are two eggs cooked anyway you want -- I ordered mine sunny side up, which would've been perfect with some rice on the side. Originally, this comes with potatoes, but I skipped that and saved my carb intake for the pancakes.

The skillet is also served with a side of two buttermilk pancakes, but I requested the Red Velvet pancakes instead -- always a good choice!

Service - We didn't experience any wait time, but the cafe does get busy in the AM. Best to come here early if you want a seat. Even though it was busy, our waiter did a good job taking care of our table. 

Overall - Babystacks Cafe is a great place to sit down and enjoy a filling breakfast.

The service is great, however the food is just ok. The food reminded me of old food, like it was made and sitting to be served to the people. I do not think I will return. The food is not made with passion, and they are just trying to serve you and sit the next person. 
if you do go get the strawberry pancakes because they were the best thing we had.

great breakfast spot, happy its literally across the street from our house.

pros: pancakes are AMAZING! (except for the blueberry pancakes, they're a joke! plain pancakes with a few blueberries on top, wtf?!)

cons: servers are nice yes but service is soooo slow!


i like the decor of the original location, since this one looks cheep but the pancakes are made with love and thats why we keep coming back

Went here on a Saturday morning for breakfast.  It was super busy and the tables were packed. They said it would be a 35 minute wait, but we were seated within 10 minutes.  Our waiter acknowledged us quickly and took our drink order and then was MIA for around 10-15 minutes. 

I ordered the Honey French Toast and my partner in crime ordered cinnabun pancakes.  Both were amazing! The french toast had a huge dollop of fresh whipped cream on the top.  So yummy.  

The ambiance was normal for a weekend breakfast place.  We were seated super close to a very annoying family of 4, but we dealt with it. Overall service could be better, but the food was delicious.

Pretty ok. Went in at 7AM and service was excellent. The toast was poorly made and had a pool of butter on it. Eggs were cold and served at well before the shortstack. The pancakes were scrumpdidilyumptious so go there for the cinnabun pancakes. Reports were made that the omelet was too cheesy.

Best regular pancakes in the world!!!  Some how they have depth.   the batter is like a sourdough or artisan loaf of bread.  Pancakes are usually shallow and unrememberable , but i was commenting this to my girlfriend as we were eating these.  I have been told to try the other flavors of pancakes. yum

There is a slight wait when it comes to this place.  Honestly, I'm not very impressed and it does seem overrated.  It's not so great. The rice was very dry and the eggs were overdone. It's like any other diner breakfast spot. I don't see anything extremely special about it. The pancakes were alright. Big I guess. Meh. The service is also not the greatest the two times I came.

YELP 365 CHALLENGE 2014-(129/365) "Babystacks #3"

Checked out this spot which is in our hood and seems like this location has consistency issues. Luckily for us, we didn't run into any issues with our orders.
Babystacks is known for having Hawaiian style breakfast items influenced by a well known spot on Oahu, and If I see comfort foods like Adobo Fried Rice Omelette, and Loco Moco, You better believe that's what I'm goin' for!

Our server Mike (who was also one of the managers) was great the whole time, offering suggestions, checking up on us constantly, and even took some time to chat with us and even after our meal, invited us back to try the Cookie Butter French Toast, one of his personal favorites, Which I've already made at home a few times...;)

Wifey ordered the Hawaiian Style Breakfast Sliders with Portuguese sausage, eggs, and cheese on Hawaiian sweet rolls and added on Bacon Pancakes with maple Syrup and I decided to go with the Loco Moco with a side of their popular Red Velvet Pancakes. They also had a Kalua Pig Benedict which sounded good but when it comes to anything benedict, I just do it up at home, because I have come to the conclusion that no one here knows how to perfectly poach an egg! (at least in all of my breakfast experiences here)

Wifey enjoyed her sliders and I thought my Loco Moco was pretty good. Both the Bacon and Red Velvet Pancakes were delicious, But my faves are still Du-Pars and the Sweet Cream Pancakes at 50's Diner. Wecome to the neighborhood Babystacks!  ALOHA!!!

Shaka Meter:  \uuu/  \uuu/  \uuu/   \uuu/  4

Love this place! Get there early to grab a table and bring a sweater because they keep the AC cranked up! I love the cinnabun pancakes, but they also have a lot of other great flavors. Their crepes are awesome also.
First timer - Came in looking to feed this Halloween hangover. Hit the spot for sure!! Food was delicious. Now I'm going back to bed.
Absolutely fabulous we loved every bite everybody should try this place and we will be back thank you so much

Our definite go to spot for breakfast on Sunday's. So convenient and so good. If you get there before the 9am rush you'll get seated right away. Anytime after that there's a hefty wait but that's just because it's so good. Everyone is friendly and the service is quick. They also just recently started splitting checks if needed.

I have eaten breakfast here many times and at different locations and it is always good.  I have tried most things on the menu and they are all tasty.  The seasoned house potatoes are the way to go, fried properly and well seasoned.  The only breakfast item that I found mediocre was the biscuits and gravy, but then again it is extremely rare to find a restaurant that makes proper biscuits and country gravy.  The pancakes are also all delicious. Great breakfast spot.
Try the red velvet pancakes, my little piece of heaven. I always get an extra icing on the side

This is my second time to eat here...this time i brought my mom with me..she kinda hard to please... we absolutely loved the food. It was served quick hot and freash...Our server was super pleasent  and checked on us several times even while it was busy. We will be coming back again and again!!

Delicious breakfast that reminds me of Hawaii because of the loco moco, Portuguese sausage and kahlua pork. It even has adobo rice! Oh, and did I mention pancakes?! The red velvet pancakes are a family favorite.
It's not a Hash House or fancy brunch spot, but it hits the spot and not your wallet.
My wife went there today with her friends. Another bad meal. She ordered scrambled eggs and hash browns. The eggs and hash browns were not cooked enough. This place just can't do anything right.

It's funny just yesterday I was telling a friend it's hard to mess up eggs but I ordered the Huntington Omelette and carrot cake pancakes. I don't know how the eggs were actually dry and hard to cut through with a fork...thats odd. I went ahead and covered them with hot sauce so they would have some flavor. The potatoes were cold and old. I didn't eat very many of them. I know what leftovers taste like. I did come in at noon so maybe I got the remains of the breakfast rush. The pancakes were good but a little unremarkable. I guess once you've had Stacks and Yolks nothing else will ever compare. I will not return but I will drive 30 minutes to go to Stacks and Yolks...their pancakes are HUGE. So much better than this place.

This was my first time going here and my last. I called in my order so I could just run in and pick it up. Mistake one. I go in thru the mobs of people there waiting and tell them i have a pickup order. I get a ticket only to wait in another 2 mile long line to pay. Really? Why don't they have a separate line for take out orders? I sat in line for a good 10 min while my foods sitting there getting cold. I get it home and yep was cold and disgusting. Not sure what the rave is on this place but it was first and only time coming here. Maybe its different eating there but I think I'll save the money and go elsewhere.

This is my favorite Babystacks in Vegas, i come here every weekend even though i live in enterprise area. I always get my crepes, potatoes, & eggs fix. But i highly recommend their locomoco or any of their other specialties
Friendly service and big menu. The bacon pancakes were great. They top up the coffee regularly and have a creative menu. Would definitely go back.
