Best breakfast joint in town , fresh food and the service is fast. Highly recommended.

We have been here several times now and I've like everything I've ordered. The food always seems fresh! Our kids usually clean their plates. You can order the senior special for kids, and it's just enough food for our 5 yr old. I usually get the southwest skillet and it is delicious! We will definitely be back!

This has become a tradition for us. I love the option that you can have the breakfast as an omelet or skillet.  I feel like the portions could be bigger but with the baby stak's I can't complain really. The coffee is really good too, most restaurants like this their coffee isn't strong at all.

First time... I hear people talk about it all the time.. thought I take the boyfriend there for his pre bday breakfast. All the hype.. it wasn't as good as every one hyped it to be.. food was ok.. came out quick for as busy as they were..  service was good.. they need a better system when it comes to paying... we were in the line to pay longer than we waited for our food... 
Overall.. we could have gone to IHOP for the same things we've ordered and paid less than what we paid here. I personally wouldn't come back, but at least I can say I had it and tried it...

Late Saturday breakfast. Although there were a number of people standing outside the wait for 3 of us was 25-30 minutes.  Ended up taking the counter which was fine. I had the German Chocolate pancakes. Wow!!!! Daughter had the Red Velvet pancakes which she said were great.  Her finance had the strawberry crepe which looked really good. Shared the biscuits and gravy with delicious seasoned potatoes. Great service, nice atmosphere.  Can't wait to go back. Huge menu with lots of choices.

OMG!!!!  This is the best breakfast place in Centennial Hills.  I had the banana foster pancakes and they were incredibly delicious.   The food is amazing and the service is outstanding .   There was a little wait of about 15-20 minutes but it was well worth the wait.  I will definitely visit again.

Me and my family come here often! Their pancakes are so good. I got the banana foster recently..LOVED IT!! I usually get the red velvet pancakes but decided to try something diff. The portugues sausage with rice and eggs are my go-to!! Last time i went they gave a small portion..literally 6 small pieces of sausage. I was pissed. But overall, food is good and service is great!

So annoyed. Called today at 11:48 to order take out and "Julie" said they can't take to go orders because they are too busy. I don't understand why they can't take an order and if their kitchen is open. I didn't even mind waiting. Perhaps they need to change their info and state they don't do take out orders.

Love me some Babystacks! You might have guessed what their specialty is by now. You got it.. It's their cakes'. Let me tell ya---they're slap your momma good! There are more than a dozen of cakes' to pick from. Options include: Red Velvet, Rocky Road, Chocolate Chip, Bacon (yup, you heard that right), and lemon ricotta (Lemon Ricotta is my absolute favorite). If cakes' aren't your thing, they offer other items like skillets (layers of potatoes, cheese, eggs and other toppings) , specialty items that feature SPAM, Garlic Rice, Portuguese Sausage, or Kalua Pig Benedict (another personal favorite).  Service at this location has always been great. The atmosphere is nothing fancy. However, their fresh cakes' and local ambience hits the mark in my book.

Warning:  Even though this location is larger than the one in Summerlin, expect to wait on the weekends (even if you arrive at a reasonable time for breakfast). The wait will be worth it and I'm betting you'll return again to try another one of their specialties.

This is my favorite place to eat. It's everything I want in a place. Hawaiian food, Breakfast food, delicious. When I first walked in I was surprised by how busy it was. On a Thursday at 11:30, there was still a wait. No big deal, the wait was quick and the food was well worth the wait. Spam and Eggs, seasoned potatoes and Banana cream pancakes. It was truly a little piece of heaven. I teared up a little, thinking about how much I wish my dad could try the food, and how happy he would have been there. The waitress was nice enough to ask me if there was anything wrong and anything she can do to make it better, she was so so sweet about it. Its truly one of my favorite places to eat and a big selling point in me moving to Vegas

What can I say about this place that hasn't been said before? It's amazing.

Every few weeks I'll treat myself to a very rich breakfast and this is one of my favorite places to visit. The place is alwaya packed so you might wait a few minutes before being seated but don't worry the wait usually isn't more than a few minutes.

The cuisine revolves primarily around pancakes but there are other options. Some even have a Hawaiian/Filipino take on them like the Hawaiian eggs Benedict they have on the menu. Easily some of my favorite eggs benedicts in Vegas. 

Pancakes here are perfect and not dry like other places. You can get them standard or upgrade them to any of their different options. Most people I know like them upgraded with the red velvet batter but I prefer them with strawberry topping on top.

Very casual atmosphere and the casual setting is very welcoming. Every server I've had is super attentive too. Definitely check it out if you're in the area.

I don't usually indulge in pancakes, but decided to try the cookie butter French toast. OMG!! So good. The little. It of crunch and taste of cookie and still with delicious fluffy French toast: perfect. And they are always so friendly here!

We were seated quickly. The service was good and the coffee was hot. I liken this to a Shari's or Denny's- I think the rating is a bit inflated. We had the following:
Red velvet pancakes, Orange Pancakes, Banana Pancakes, Lemon Ricotta Pancakes and chicken fried steak. My husband was not overly pleased with the chicken fried steak and more syrup was in order on all accounts. Those are my lack of five factors.

I've been here a few times and I haven't had anything spectacular but the food is pretty good. Having said that, I haven't been too adventurous. They have everything: omelettes, spam scramble, kalua pig benedict, red velvet pancakes, etc. You name it, they got it. And it does look good, but I personally like a light breakfast so I usually get eggs. Their skillets are my go-to order. 

Special shout out for the lemon ricotta pancakes - OMG. They were delicious. I unfortunately I didn't order this so I only got one bite. My sister would only let me have one bite of hers lol. It was really good. I thought it would be heavy but it wasn't at all. It was fluffy & light. The cream cheese syrup was dreamy.

Came in to show my sister what I thought was going to be an amazing breakfast. She's visiting me from Hawaii so figured she would like it here. First she ordered scrambled eggs (shelled eggs) we for egg mix from a carton. So then we decided to ask for over hard since they wouldn't give us fresh eggs. Well guess they don't like it when they are proven wrong. So they burnt our eggs. Our potatoes were so hard that my kids couldn't and wouldn't eat them. Ive been in the industry for many years. The server decided to question me and tell me that I was wrong and they were using shelled eggs. Right!! Especially with that bright yellow color on the eggs.

I've been here a few times. The first time was great. We did have to wait a while for a table. After our first visit I can say the service is not the greatest. You do wait a while for your order to be taken and then sometimes the food is not consistent. The good is still pretty good though just van be very good or just ok.
Go To breakfast stop! We bring any Vegas visitor to Babystacks. The pancakes are amazing and highly suggested! Wait times can be long so arrive early or after 1100.  Don't miss out.

The food is amazing but when it comes to seating it's ridiculous. They're so precise about all of your party being here I couldn't believe it. It's so inconvenient. I only had one person missing because she was parking and the lady almost didn't want to sit us. Terrible.
Okay food waitress suggested something I really didn't want to try but it turned out to be okay after all. It was the French toast with the cereal all over it. Felt like I gained 10 pounds.

This Babystacks was pretty busy but still didn't make me wait THAT long.  The server my party had was nice,  very welcoming, and most of all very open to sharing her opinions with us. Their specialty pancakes are for the most part amazing.  I personally love their red velvet pancakes.  The cream cheese icing they have on the side acts as a syrup.  I feel that it compliments the red velvet pancakes so much more than regular maple syrup ever could.  The Portuguese sausage was fair at best.  It was a little undercooked but that's my only complaint.  All in all I would love to go back.

Love this place! Get there early or be prepared to wait. It's small, so seating is limited but it's worth the wait. I have never had anything bad there, and the service is always great! We go every couple of weeks, it's the only place we go for breakfast!

Pancakes are so delicious. So is chili and potatoes and everything. Food is amazing but there is always a wait to be seated: once you're seated though they are quick and attentive. They need to get a bigger place. Lol
Best Hawaiian breakfast joint in north Las Vegas! I always get up grades to garlic fried rice and banana stacks! The service is good and wait lines are not that bad. Great Hardy breakfast

My kids and i live going to this local gem for breakfast, the Adobo Fried Rice is really flavorful paired with some of thier lemon pancakes it's the perfect match. I recommend getting there earlier than later because there's almost always at least a 15-20 min wait.

We have come here a few times for breakfast.  Usually there is a wait, but it isn't long and it's totally worth it. They do not take reservations and they will not seat you unless your while party is present. Food is always great. Service is excellent.
Delicious breakfast. Pancakes, country fried steak and eggs, biscuits and gravy... It's all awesome. Will be back to try more of their menu items!

I am a frequent customer at Babystacks and have been for over six years. I started going to the location near Buffalo and Flamingo because it was near my home. We moved across town and I started frequenting the location near Stephanie and Warm Springs. Now I've moved again and am located between two locations, the one on Buffalo and Smoke Ranch and the one I'm reviewing now that's located at Durango near Deer Springs. 

I prefer the location at Buffalo and Smoke Ranch, but with the severely limited seating options, there is often a wait, even on weekdays. This is my fourth visit to the Durango and Deer Springs location. This location has a large seating area, so there is almost never a wait, which is convenient. 

Needless to say, I know what my favorite Babystacks meal, the Honey [French] Toast is supposed to look and taste like. Before giving a poor review, I wanted to give the location a few tries to see if my experience was a one-time thing. Sadly it has not been. 

On my first visit by myself about two weeks ago I ordered my usual meal, the Honey Toast without powered sugar and coffee. The Honey Toast came out burned, very black on the back and along the edges. I went ahead a tried a bite to be fair, but it tasted like charcoal. In all my visits to Babystacks locations I had never gotten my Honey Toast in that condition. I showed my waitress and she brought me a new order of it, only slightly less burned, but the center of the Honey Toast was salvageable. I went ahead and ate it in disappointment. I didn't have the time to send it back again as I had somewhere to be. 

On my second visit on the weekend a few days later with my boyfriend my Honey Toast was okay, but the waitress brought out his food a full five minutes before mine. 

On my third visit a few days later the Honey Toast looked a little overdone, but eatable. However, when I put my fork into the whipped cream I came out with a kinky black hair. I showed the waiter and he had my food remade. 

Today I decided to give them one last try. My Honey Toast came out burned yet again. I pointed it out to the waitress, but told her not to bother reordering it. I'd eat the middle and call it good. I asked her to please let the cooks know because this keeps happening. My coffee was also served at room temperature, but at this point I barely noticed. 

I'm one of those customers that hates, absolutely hates having to send food back. It's embarrassing and I don't want to ever appear to be a b---h, and I don't want to ever risk the ire of the people making and handling my food. After three out of four bad experiences here, I'm done. I will not come to this location again. It's extremely disappointing to come to this conclusion because I've always seen Babystacks as a restaurant with high standards. This location fails miserably.
Love this place! Always busy but worth the wait! Everything on the menu is awesome but my favorite is the Adobo Fried Rice Omelet and the Nutella Crepes! YUM!

I have yet to have a bad experience here.  The food is consistently good and prepared and served to my liking.  Although I don't really venture to the whole menu my breakfast is always delicious and served with a smile.  One meal here always gets me full and that means I go home and rub my belly.  That's a good thing.
When we're in Vegas, we always hit up this place.  The wait is totally worth it.  They have large portions and it's not too expensive.

I am a huge fan of babystacks.. i pretty much always get the same thing .. Portuguese sausage and eggs can't go wrong with this dish.. the sausage are sautéed in a skillet with a little bit of burnt edges which is just how I like them. Eggs over easy with garlic rice.. perfect breakfast. I know they pride themselves on their pancakes but that doesn't draw me here .. they are a little stingy with the syrup but that's just my opinion.
I've heard about this place and their red velvet pancakes and it did not disappoint. I ordered the adobo omelet and it was devoured by the whole family. We will definitely be coming back

We have been to one of the Babystacks on Buffalo before and loved it. We plan on going back to that one should we go to Babystacks again. 
My boyfriend, son, and I came in for a late breakfast on Thursday. There were people there, but plenty of open tables. Once seated, we ordered drinks from the server while we looked over the menu. She asked if we were ready to order, but I wasn't and asked for another minute. She left and we did not see her again for at least 10 minutes. Fair enough though, I did ask for more time and that's what we got. 
We placed our order ; I got the Mexican skillet with bananas foster pancakes, my son ordered bacon and eggs with Rocky Road pancakes, the bf ordered a veggie omelette and strawberry pancakes. After another kinda long wait, out came my pancakes, my bf's pancakes and my son's bacon and eggs. Then another wait. It wasn't too bad for me. I ate half my pancakes before the rest of my food came to the table, but my boyfriend likes to eat his pancakes for "dessert". That's just the way the man eats. So my skillet finally comes, my son's pancakes come. The server says to my bf, "your omelette will be out in a minute". Fine. Well, she didn't come back with his food until my son and I were about done eating. She just sets it down with a, "Sorry". So he scarfed it down since he was starving and then ate his cold pancakes while we waited for him. 
My bf and I have both been servers before so we're pretty understanding of kitchen mishaps and we tend to tip generously, but the way she handled this was all wrong. She could have offered some form of explanation so he would know he should eat his pancakes instead of saying it will be out in a minute. She also should have offered a discount or something for the inconvenience of not bringing his food until we were done. So the 2 stars are strictly for the food which was very good. Service needs some work.

I went to this place because of the amazing reviews. I was HIGHLY Disappointed .. First I ordered bacon and eggs ; eggs, scrambled with h cheese. The bacon was half cooked ( I guess u need to ask for crispy bacon to get it fully cooked). I asked for scrambled eggs with cheese, and I got chopped eggs with a slice of cheese on top. Excuse me but I believe when you ask for scramble eggs with cheeses, it suppose to come out SCRAMBLED with CHEESE in it smh. My friend ordered corn beef hash with potatoes on thee side, and her potatoes was frozen in the inside. 

With the negative comes the positive and the ONLY positive I can say is .. 
I ordered the cinnamon bun pancakes and I would have to say it's was the best thing out of the whole order.

I will not be going back to baby stacks. The reviews really let me down this time
Great food, fantastic service. Good prices. Hard for me to recommend places so highly, but I have got to say we will swing in here anytime we come visit the in laws.

After hiking at Mount Charleston with Terri R. and Mel C., we decided to stop here for breakfast.  I didn't know there was a northwest outlet for Babystacks.  It proved to be a good place to go.

I have never had Spam until today.  When I looked at their menu and saw the Specialties section, the Spam Scramble popped out and I knew I had to order this.  Along with this, I opted for the two pancakes you can get instead of toast.  I ordered the Orange Creamsicle pancakes that come with orange syrup, whipped cream, and a small container of cream cheese icing.

Breakfast was great!  Spam is just like cubed lunch meat.  The Furikake mixed in gave the scramble some extra taste and the rice was good.  I didn't finish the rice because I wanted to have the healthier food--the pancakes with orange syrup and whipped cream.

As others have mentioned, this is a large restaurant and they have a large waiting area.  The three of us opted to eat at the counter where there was immediate seating.  Service was great.  My coffee was refilled several times and they were there to refill water glasses, too.

This is a good option for my hiking group to stop for a late breakfast/lunch while we're still hiking at Charleston.  

This was a tasty breakfast made better because I enjoyed it with two friends.

Worse! Food! EVER!!!! The wait staff is ok but the food is probably the worst food I've had since living in Vegas. I tried giving them a "second" chance at another location but I was still disappointed! (My entire party was disappointed) someone even asked "whoever recommended this place can not choose breakfast for a loooong time for choosing this place!!!!!!" Go if you've been starving other than that there's IHOP or even McDonald's is better!

I have been to the other locations and neither one of them were this dirty. We waited for approximately 30 minutes before we were seated. The table we were seated at was not wiped down as there were still fresh water rings on the table.  My daughter found a piece of hair inside the napkin with the utensils. I asked for new utensils, this time, when my daughter opened the napkin, there was a piece of rice stuck in between the tines of the fork.  We were so grossed out. I ended asking for plastic utensils instead.... by the time our food arrived, my daughter already lost her appetite. In fairness,  the waiter was really nice,  that's the only reason why I'm giving them 1 star.

Have never had a bad experience here.  Love the non traditional breakfast items. Portuguese sausage and garlic rice is awesome!! My wife had tried a different style pancake each time. .. She is never disappointed.  Highly recommend this place.!!
Centennial Hills location. Sparse menu, lackluster food.  Very disappointed after great hype. Might as well go to Centennial IHOP.  Once was enough. Too bad.

I do not understand why this place has four locations and still allowed to be in business. It's only technicality but I would like to get what I ordered and paid for. 
First time this place opened some of the food they served wasn't even seasoned or ready to be served. Please thaw your frozen food properly before putting them in customers takeout. 

Second time only reason I had to order from here was so I don't have to drive 25 mins to get the stuff to make my own at home. Let me tell you something put the takeout items in a bag so your customer can take it not placing aplastic bag in front me to put the food in the bag after paying for it. You staff was watching put my food in my own bag and didn't do anything. This is so petty but so important. 

Food is isn't amazing it is mediocre and overpriced food that I wouldn't eat unless I have no choice. 


 It gets worst every time

Funny enough, we live right smack in between both Babystacks Café places.  We finally decided to take the jaunt in the opposite direction and visit the location on N. Durango!

Place is super busy for breakfast on the weekends.  Especially on a Sunday.  So church goers beware.  You may be in for a bit of a wait in your Sunday best.  Luckily for the wifey and I the wait was only about 10 minutes that day.

Place is nice and lively, and seems a bit more spacious than the other location on Buffalo.  Actually it seems a lot more spacious with the high ceilings and more tables.  I like the colors, actually makes me want to drink coffee and eat breakfast.

Menu here is just about the same as the other location.  Breakfast and lunch items galore!  Nothing in short supply.  I skipped my want of Rick's Adobo Fried Rice (hard for a Filipino) and went with something else out of the menu.

I chose the Ranchero Omelette ($9.25) - four egg omelette with an entire Ortega chile and chicken, topped with fresh green salsa, and pepper jack and cheddar cheese.  Also came with hash browns (love mine well done), and two buttermilk babystack pancakes (of course!).  Omelette was of good size, with lots of chile and chopped chicken on the inside.  The cheeses complimented the omelette well, and the green salsa gave it a nice added kick (but not too hot).  I enjoyed it a lot.  The hash browns were standard, good and cooked how I like.  I however love to drown mine in pepper, ketchup, and lots of Tabasco.  Yum.  The babystack pancakes?  Good to the last bite.  I dunno what it is about their babystack batter, but it's a keeper.  Nice, hot, fluffy (not you Gabriel Iglesias), not doughy or rubbery, perfect with some maple syrup.  All in all a great breakfast for me.

The wifey had the Mexican Skillet ($9.95) - flat top potatoes with marinated carnitas and jalapenos, with pepper jack cheese, topped with two eggs over-easy, and a side of fresh pico de gallo, and sour cream.  Wifey also opted for two buttermilk babystack pancakes.  She said her dish was good, but there was a bit too much jalapeno in her skillet making it a little spicy for her liking.  The pico de gallo also had more onion than tomato.  Other than that she enjoyed it, and gave thumbs up to the babystack pancakes.

I like Babystacks Café for breakfast and will keep coming here for their morning delights.  Service here is great, our server was quick, very attentive, and kept our cups full.  Can't ask for anything more, especially during the early morning rush.

Eat!  Next time it will be Rick's Adobo Fried Rice.  Or maybe not.

Red velvet pancakes? Yes please! This is a diet-busting, calorie nightmare and was super sweet, but I LOVED it. I finally get what all the fuss is about. Because of the sugar overload, I can't make this an every day or even every week stop, but definitely a place to keep in my back pocket for a treat! Prices were reasonable, the place was clean, and the server was nice. No complaints and nearly gave it 5 stars. Just not quite there. Almost....almost.
Holy moly supper yummy.  The pancakes are always amazing, lunch is tasty. The only negative is when I order a house salad before my meal... It never comes out first.  Like 5 times now.

Love this place!!  So glad to have one closer to home, went there this morning for breakfast. Service was fast and as always great. I had the piglet skillet and upgraded to the red velvet pancakes (which are to die for). Will definitely be returning!

So I've been to a few different locations and this 1 seems to be the closest to me when I'm in town so I've frequented it more. I haven't tried various items, I usually stick to my fave German chocolate pancakes, Portuguese sausage, and seasoned potatoes. Everything is always solid. Haven't experienced any issues. Today they forgot my Portuguese sausage, but everything else was cool. Service is also always pleasant. Reasonable prices.

Dear Babystacks,

I did my due diligence by bringing my whole party of 5 in at the same time... Please do yours and sit people in the order they arrived. One of the girls at the front seemed a little confused after the other girl asked her why sat the party that came after us before us... And then laughed it off... Thanks- we have been loyal but we will be going to The Cracked Egg from now on!

I had to visit a relative in Centennial (North of Summerlin), while I was in the Ninth Island (Vegas).  He suggested we eat at Babystacks that serves some Hawaiian Style grinds, and I'm glad he did.  Its located on Durango near Elkhorn, just off the 95.

We ordered Lolo Rick's adobo fried rice ($9.95 | chicken adobo fried rice wrapped in an omelette), with your choice of side.  I chose mac salad, while my friends chose country potatoes.  BS also offers loco moco, portuguese sausage, corned beef hash, as well as crepes and other traditional bfast items.

Da adobo fried rice was winnahzzz!  The chicken adobo was moist and nicely seasoned.  BTW, adobo has Spanish roots combining salty & sour flavors.  The Filipino version uses shoyu & vinegar to accomplish the foregoing.  It went well w/ the omelette, and we were stuffed afterwards:  5 Stars.  On the other hand, the mac salad was suprisingly bad.  It was comparable to store bought mac salad:  2 Stars.

Regarding the ambiance, this is a big place.  There are several tables in addition to a counter.  The space is flexible so you can combine tables for large parties:  4 Stars.  Likewise, the service was really good.  Our waiter was super friendly, and the remainder of the team gave us a lot of Aloha:  4 Stars.

Mahalos to my cuz for the rec on Babystacks.  The entire experience was very positive.  If you don't mind a little drive from the Strip, hit this local place.  You won't be sorry.

EVERYONE enjoyed their breakfast. The Banana Foster pancakes were very moist and the flavor was fantastic. The Mexican Skillet was the bomb and also very flavorful. My youngest daughter loved her cookies and cream pancake. My oldest daughter who doesn't like pancakes enjoyed the coffee flavored pancake and my 4th daughter says her French Toast was great.

5 star everytime!!!!!! Their cookie butter French toast is unreal!!! We showed up at the height of their busy hour. That hour when people finally decide to roll out of bed from Saturday night. They were very busy and the wait time was expected to be 40 minutes but we were seated and waited upon in 10 :). Everyone there is always so happy and up beat. Great way to start my day. Thanks Babystacks!!! You guys rock!

I used to love this place until today, my cup of cocoa had a hair on it l, and I asked the waitress to please change it in a very nice a polite way, and what she did was roll her eyes at me and walked away without even let me finish My sentence. I wish I know that lady's name to tell her manager about her behavior. We walked out and will never be back there again.

Great food. Hate the way all baby locations do business. From being greeted by all their rules to the fact they squish everybody in next to each other to their cheap credit card machine that takes forever. Again... Great food.

Exceptionally bad service. The only reason I come here is because I cannot find sweet cream crepes anywhere else in town. If it wasn't for that fact I would never come here. On multiple occasions my wife and I have walked into their restaurant only to be given a 25-30 minute wait time to be seated. This would not bother me however there are more empty tables than full tables. It's upsetting because the food here is great. I will not let up on the bad reviews and complaints until the management and host staff is replaced. I will lose this restaurant as much business as possible until the business gets better. 

Here's a tip babystacks...full waiting area+empty tables=no money.
Things have gotten better, food is always good just always crowded. Which isn't a bad thing always gotta get that to go.

Came here for breakfast and I know a place is good if they can get me craving for more after I finished my meal. 

We chose to eat at Babystacks because it was convenient. My boyfriend and I aren't really pancake people (we prefer savory breakfasts) and had ordered the corned beef hash and the adobo fried rice. I felt like it would have been an injustice to come to babystacks and not try their pancakes, so I asked our server for their most popular pancakes and decided to get the strawberry pancakes to go with my corned beef hash.

I wasn't expecting to really like the pancakes since I normally don't. BUT I ATE ALL OF MY PANCAKES. IT WAS DELICIOUS. It came with fresh cream and strawberries and this strawberry sauce that was addictive. I almost forgot all about my corned beef hash because all I wanted to do was keep eating the pancakes. The corned beef hash was perfect, it had a nice crisp to it and some softness in the middle. I love eating it together where I'm able to get corned beef hash, a little runny yolk, and potatoes all in one spoonful. 

My boyfriend got the adobo fried rice which was served in an omelett. I've never seen that before so I thought it was really creative. It was well-seasoned and yummy.

For a place that we randomly picked, I was thoroughly impressed and we enjoyed everything we ordered. I'm honestly still thinking about those strawberry pancakes.

Absolutely my favorite spot to meet with friends and family for breakfast! The service is impeccable and the food is a beautiful array of classics and orginal modern flair. They also offer you a to-go cup for your beverage when you leave. The hospitality is friendly, but they treat you like family. The Cracked Egg use to be my favorite until these guys came along. A must see and eat!!
Mediocre overpriced food...charged me .70 for a side of hot sauce. Why stop there...you should charge for fork rental too

Everyone raves about the red velvet pancakes...and they should!  They are truly amazing. They have a slightly crusty outside and the middle is moist and not too sweet. It's served with this thick glaze that you pour over it in lieu of regular syrup. Oh my!  It doesn't get much better than that!!  

The coffee was perfect with the pancakes. The only reason I didn't give it more stars is the service was a little lacking. They didn't seem to be all that busy but it took a while to get out order and the coffee refills didn't come around as much as I would have liked. I've been there a couple of times on different days of the week so I'm not sure why the service was just so so. I'll tell you what though, the red velvet pancakes makes it worth your wait!  Go there, NOW!

I love babystacks I always go to the original location in Summerlin they have the best service there and should've just gone there instead. Never coming back to this location again after our experience . Yes, there's a lot of people, it's busy... BUT that doesn't give you an excuse to be rude and inattentive to your customers. Our server took 15 min to get us a drink and another five to get our orders... Once he did get our orders all of our orders were incorrect! A simple sorry about that would've sufficed BUT he managed to say are you sure you didn't order that?.... Like BRO... I ordered Portuguese sausage, rice, over medium eggs, with pancakes .... and he gave me the sausage, seasoned potatoes,scrambled eggs and toast... instead of apologizing he was just like so you changed your mind on the toast..? NO. I never ordered it.. and he was telling me that wasn't what he wrote down.. Well OBVIOUSLY you were not paying attention and didn't care much for good service...he apologizes after hearing me make a comment about him claiming we ordered what he wrote. To put the cherry on top
of this horrific service he managed to put 3 drinks that we didn't order on the bill...... The cashier asks us if we wanted to add tip ... the answer is a big NO. I'm usually a good tipper but with that service he was lucky we didn't walk out... Amazing food won't keep customers coming back if your service is horrible and unprofessional. I did not expect a 5 star dining experience here but I also did expect attentiveness, and a little bit of courtesy.... SMH.

Very long wait ...... Really the only negative ( maybe that is actually a positive:) ). 
Decor not inviting BUT I brought 6  girls here and they all said their food was delicious!!!! Everyone wants to return.

My good friend and I always head here when the "out to breakfast" big takes us over. All the unique flavors and slight island flare makes this little morning spot hard to beat. I love their German chocolate pancakes when I'm fighting the sweet tooth, the lemon ricotta when I want to be a little more tame. But let me tell you GARLIC RICE!!! Oh my, sooo good and so much garlic!!!! I will never say no to These babies!!!

Not sure if it was the cook today or because I ordered out but I was disappointed. This was our first time eating here and saw how good the reviews were/live down the street and wanted breakfast food. Ordered blueberry pancakes and hash browns. The pancakes fell short. Tasted as if they drowned it in butter while cooking all while bland at the same time (butter isn't a replacement for sugar). Hash browns were hard around the edges and not seasoned at all. My boyfriend's red velvet pancakes were pretty good. Just super bummed they didn't live up to the hype. Overall, I'll pass.
Great spot to hit for breakfast or brunch. Skillets or pancakes are awesome..service is always amazing! Deffo a regular spot for me
Never been disappointed! Service is sometimes slow only because they're always so busy but they're friendly so to me it doesn't matter! Food is fantastic especially the Nutella pancakes!! Yum!
Went in with a huge group and got taken care of quickly, food was delicious as usual!!!!! Great customer service.

I have been coming to babystacks for the past 6 years. Recently babystacks made a change in policy where you cannot split checks. I can't begin to explain the inconvenience this caused the party I was with. On top of that, I drive 25 minutes to this location because I've always had a good experience and the food is great. But another reason is because it is military friendly. Today Krissy told my entire military party that she couldn't give us military discount because they had already gave us our check, although we hadn't even paid yet. I'm not looking for a handout but I will always support a small business, especially if they're military friendly. Not splitting our check is inconvenient and annoying, but to then deny military discount because we didn't announce we were military before ordering food is absolutely absurd. Again, I have been coming to various Las Vegas babystacks locations, but this was the last time and I will not return again.
I know most people come for the pancakes but I come for the Hawaiian breakfast. I love Hawaiian food!

My ultimate favorite breakfast location! Food and service is always a 5 star. Wait time can be a little longer than i would like but that's because they are always so busy. The staff is always very kind and friendly i come here at least 3 times a month never gets old!!
My favorite breakfast spot in Las Vegas!  The bananas foster pancakes are to die for!  A comfy, casual restaurant the entire family can enjoy.

Giving four stars - instead of 5 - because the restaurant has made their portions smaller for sure.  Service was awesome!  We love their red velvet pancakes.  Coffee could be better.  Breakfast for two was around $35.00 with tax and tip.

My favorite Go to place after Church. However its always packed, but its worth the wait. Great red velvet pancakes, and enjoy the vibe of the place. Glad I took a chance with this place. When I leave Las Vegas I'm going to really miss Babystacks.
Pancakes are amazing! But the omelets are sooooo food! Wish they were open later then 2:00 pm

Babystacks is usually our go-to for pancakes. They probably have the biggest variety in town. 
This was my first time at this location and like the others, it's quite busy. I NEVER eat at the restaurant because of how busy it is. Instead, we pick up and eat in the comfort of our own home :) 
The Mr. loves the S'mores pancakes and I typically try different ones. I don't think you can go wrong with any of their pancakes. All that I've tried have been delicious, it's a matter of what you like and in the mood for. I think Babystacks has a pancake for everyone. 
This time I had the Hazelnut and they were, of course, delicious. The best part is their home made whipped cream. It's delightfully creamy, sweet, and fluffy. I typically don't eat pancakes with whipped cream, but this one I can't say no to.
I also tried a new breakfast item, since trying chicken fried steak recently for the first time (if you read my reviews, you already know), I've decided to broaden my breakfast horizons. I tried Corned Beef Hash and it tasted good, flavorful and crispy. Not really my thing though. I usually get Kalua Pig Benny here, it's really good! Hash browns were not my fave either, a little under-cooked for me. But the seasoned fries are awesome so I will stick to those.
All in all, a great breakfast option, especially if you're a fan of pancakes.

If you have not been here yet RUN do not walk!!!  Go now!  (Unless it's past lunchtime and they are closed.)   We attempted to eat here on a weekend morning, but there was a line going out the door so we didn't even get out of our car.  Yesterday, a Wedsneday, my daughter and I decided to drop in.  The place was very plain.  I guess I was expecting it to be fancier, but it's not fancy at all.  Our waiter was very friendly and helpful.  The menu had tons of items on it.  Everything sounded so good, it was hard to decide what to order!   So, we each picked something to share.  We ordered the pulled pork grilled cheese sandwich with macaroni salad, and a skillet with scrambled eggs, potatoes, green sauce, and whatever else they put in there.  OMG...... everything was so amazing!!!!   We could totally understand why it's packed on the weekends!   The prices were reasonable, and the portions were fair.  My only complaint is that they are not open for dinner!!!

Meh... it was just ok. It feels more like a cafeteria then restaurant and most of the pancakes are just too sweet. They are more like desserts then pancakes. The 2 times we went, the wait staff was polite and took our orders pretty quickly. To me however, the price was a bit high.

However, this place should be tried, especially if you have a sweet tooth!

Food: I should have stuck with the pancakes. I am visiting from Hawaii and was a little home sick so I wanted to try the loco moco. First off I was a little disappointed that they couldn't sub fried rice for a small up charge but rather only could do garlic rice (over garlicked) or buy the $10 adobo fried rice on the side. This is something any L&L, big city diner, loco moco shop does easily. The gravy too tasted a little... Boxed. The coffee tasted distinctly plasticky mixed with that airplane coffee taste of bad water, and the sugar didn't make it any better. But I will admit this is my fault for ordering something Hawaiian in Las Vegas. My husband got the white chocolate macadamia nut pancakes and gobbled them up so those were good. 

-stick to pancakes 

Ambiance: the staff was very nice and smiley, a little inattentive but functional. The decor is a little sparse but the music was nice! 

Overall: good place to get breakfast if you want traditional breakfast foods, but they have some work to do on their Hawaiian local specialities.
The best desert breakfast place in town! Their biscuits and gravy is also a go to of mine. Wait time is usually less than what they quote it as. I see why their line is always out the door.

Almost every weekend we get nutella crepes & their BLT to go. Not only is the food delicious, but they are always kind & courteous. They even take the time (even though they are always swamped) to open each box to ensure the order is correct. Everyone who knows me, knows I rave about Babystacks. Highly recommend!

1 star for management, 5 stars for our server. We get there yesterday morning and are told it would be a 20-30 minute wait, which is normal for this restaurant. Because of the size of our party, we choose to wait outside. 35 minutes have passed and we are still waiting outside and we're starting to wonder what is going on. Shortly after, a woman in a white dress comes to ask if we have a party of 10. I said yes and she said that they've been calling for you. Not thinking about it, I followed her in. She went off to the side to talk to another girl, and I said "Wait, you don't even work here?" She said no, I just saw you and your family waiting for a long time from inside. I thanked her and said it was appreciated. I went up to an elderly haole woman behind the counter and gave her our name.  She was surprised that we were still there. Apparently they had just given up our table. I said, did you even go outside? She said yes we did. And I thought, wtf? Another non-working customer just came outside to grab us. If it wasn't for that other customer, we would probably still be standing outside one day later as I type this. So stupid. Don't lie to my face that you came outside when you didn't. Despite that Haole's ignorance, our server made us forget her and made or meal great. Get someone else to run the front.

Stopped in for quick breakfast. We were seated promptly. Service is good. They have a large selection of pancakes ranging from red velvet to oreo. The portions are large so unless you're very hungry, sharing is a good idea. They are a fan of spam so if you like that,  many choices. It's not a traditional breakfast menu. Has intl flair such as kalbi with eggs,  kahlua benedict, etc. We had the breakfast burrito and it wasn't large compared to the omelettes. Coffee was ok.

I'm the biggest supporter of Babystacks, have been eating it for years, recommend it to anyone who will listen...  the food really is that good.  Today though my Babystacks love affair might have ran its course.  Was seated as soon as I walked in, no wait which is great, usually there's at least some wait.  Server brings me some coffee, I order, start waiting for my delicious breakfast to arrive...  reading some news articles on my phone I notice a few parties arrive, they've got to wait around 5 minutes to be seated, so I've been seated and food ordered easily 5-10 minutes before they arrived...  coffee cups empty, no big deal food will be out shortly so I wait, it is getting a little busy so I leave the staff alone, not too bothered at this point...  5 more minutes go by, party that was seated after me gets a full spread of food and refills delivered to them.  I start to look for my waitress, maybe my order got jumbled up it happens...  few minutes go by nothing.  Coffee cup still empty...  approach the counter and ask if maybe there's a mix up, people that were seated long after me are well into their meals and I've had an empty cup of coffee in front of me for 10 minutes...  lady is real blunt, "sir your food it coming we are busy".  I say "Yeah I get that but those people sat down 10 minutes after I ordered and they're halfway through their meal, maybe there's a mix up with my order...  she gives me a stop bothering me look, says she'll check on it so I go sit back down...  see her call the waitress over, they have a conversation, while they're talking another waitress brings my food...  coffee cup still empty, no offer to refill...  at this point I'm playing a game to see how long it takes someone to refill my cup.  Food is room temp at best, bacon is cold to the touch...  my waitress comes over to ask if everything's ok, I say not really...  well is there anything I can get you?  Umm yeah coffee would be good since I've been sitting here with an empty cup in front of me for the last 20 minutes...  eat my lackluster $20 breakfast and go to pay...  lady says that'll be $20, I had already set my card down with the check, she stands there with her hand out I point to where I had placed it on the register, she scans my card and just tosses it on the counter.  I'm no body language expert by any means, but you could tell she was being passive aggressive by the way she just chucked it on the counter...  I'm standing there with my hand out to take my card back and she just throws it at me like she's dealing black jack on Fremont street.  By this time I'm past the point of pissed off...  "Is there a problem?" I ask.  She gets a look on her face like she's trying to hold back a fart.  I say "Look, I've been here 100 times, never had this bad of service...  is there a manager I can talk to?"  She gets this kind of fuck you, yeah I'll get you the manager kind of condescending tone...  brings the manager over and it's the same one who brought my food to me when the original waitress didn't...  I'm a pretty loyal eater, I have my spots I love and recommend, this Babystacks has always been one of those spots, but today they lost a customer...  pretty sure it won't hurt their bottom line, just feel really let down by my experience there today...  I'll be sure and let people know about Egg and I or the cracked egg from now on instead of Babystacks...  also wanna point out after reading other reviews I'm not the first who's had problems with the old bitty in the 1982 rimmed glasses that works the register.  Might be time to make a move, a hostess' job is customer interaction, she might be better suited washing dishes or something, customer service isn't her forte.
A must visit when in vegas! Cute place with great service and excellent food! The carrot cake and cinnabun pancakes are awesome!

I'm so glad we came here. The husband and I only have one day off a week together, so we occasionally enjoy a nice breakfast out. But, I've gotten to the point that national chain eateries don't impress me anymore. Additionally, our daughter is really finicky and breakfast is not her favorite meal. We've eaten here twice now and have enjoyed our meals. The pancakes are fluffy just like they should be. The kahlua grilled cheese was to die for. And, our  daughter loves the spam and eggs with an extra serving of rice instead of potatoes. Yay!

The pancakes are to die for. Delicious. But don't come here for coffee....the coffee is awful! Very watery and low quality. But, I keep coming back because of the food (the Nutella crepe is very good too). Only 3 stars because, for me, a good cup of Joe in the morning , is essential.

The very first time I went the buffalo location and I  thought it was just ok. I found out they had another restaurant on Durango and not only is it around the corner but the restaurant bigger, all of their staff is always pleasant but I thought the quality of food was better at this location!!
Awesome breakfast, but be prepared for a wait on the weekends it gets really busy! I would recommend this place to anyone looking for a yummy breakfast. We usually dine at the one in Centennial Hills

Pancakes were really good, we had the red velvet pancakes. Other than that I don't see what the hype is all about. I had the corned beef and it was insanely salty and my boyfriend had an omelet with potatoes that seemed half the size of the order from the table next to us. The wait to be seated and then the wait to get the food were about the same, 20-30mins. Would go back to try the other pancakes but not for anything else. Maybe our next experience will be better...
This place is amazing. My son loves the ricks fried adobo. I personally love the red velvet pancakes. It gets really busy on the weekends. I would recommend pickup.
Great place when you go there will be a wait I have never got lucky in no wait but love there pancakes especially the bacon pancakes

Lord I don't even know where to start. Honestly I was really excited about this place with the large line formed outside it gives you the feeling of a great meal ahead. But you sit down in a very uncomfortable chair at a fairly small table. The service was decent but not great honestly it was just non memorable at the least. Then we get to the food I don't care what they say these are processed products and there is nothing special about that I can go to a mcdonalds and get that kind of breakfast. The omelet was decent but again besides the eggs seemed like processed food inside the chili was just plain gross honestly. This restaurant is really close to my house but I am just not ever going to bother waiting to eat here again not worth the wait in the least.

I've always heard great things about this place. The first time we came in we waited awhile (as expected) but what threw me off was upon walking in, you literally have to fight to get your name on the wait list. There is no order, no organization, no one there to greet you. The "hostess" is the same person who is running the wait list, seating people and bagging to-go orders. On a busy Saturday/Sunday, that's just not reasonable. 

We came in with the whole family this past Saturday. Busy, again, as expected. We were quoted 30-35 minutes for a party of 5 with a highchair. Waited close to 50 minutes. The hostess was not friendly whatsoever and once we were finally seated, argued with my mother-in-law after she requested an extra chair. 

I will say, the service afterward was prompt and food was definitely good but just that initial first impression kills it all.

For a place that represents Hawaii - they don't show very much Aloha.
Very impressed with the food and the pancakes are amazing!  Wasn't happy how the food didn't all come out at once or I  would have given this a five star.  Would definitely come back again!  :)

I seriously don't know what is the deal with this location because the summerlin one is great. BUT this one needs help and I am so bummed that after all the anticipation of them opening in Centennial, this location has turned out to be a serious disappointment. First time I ate there it was take out and  I ordered the strawberry pancakes and may lightning strike me dead if I did not get home to find a freakin shortstack of plain pancakes WITH TWO STRAWBERRIES CUT IN HALF!!!!! AND THAT WAS IT FOR THE STRAWBERRIES IN MY STRAWBERRY PANCAKES!!! 
Second time ate in. Ordered the lemon ricotta pancakes. BURNED BURNED BURNED! Ya know for a pancake place this place SUCKS! I don't know if it's poor management or lazy chefs or both but geez! I'm not sure I want to go for the third times a charm factor.
Absolutely wonderful. Get in early as it doesn't stay open beyond early afternoon. Good variety is great and tastes are delicious. Worth it.
Great food as always & less wait time to sit down since the sq ft is larger than the buffalo location.

This is the best place for breakfast in the Vegas Valley. Friendly, great food and fast service. The specialty pancakes are out of this world and if you don't try some you are missing out. There is usually a wait so get there a little earlier than you want but it is worth the wait!!! Go try it if you haven't! You will not regret it.
Learn how to cook steak!!!! And don't serve half good size steaks and half flat flank carne asada looking steaks!!! Will never get steak and eggs here again.

They have the best banna pancakes by far that I've tasted .

We don't usually come to this location since its on the complete opposite side from us, but since we were close we thought we'd stop by for lunch.

I've never had a problem with baby stacks, it was always considered one of the top choices for lunch.

This location felt a lot like being in a restaurant back home (Hawaii) with all the reggae music playing.  

Our server, who I totally forgot her name was very patient although it was so busy. Being pregnant and all I wanted to order everything on the menu.

Slthough the I'm not the best food tester since I always order the same thing; the loco moco Hawaiian chili style! It's amazing 

My boyfriend tried the breakfast burrito & he says it taste like any other breakfast burrito nothing special so I wouldn't recommend it. 

I'd recommend this place if your looking for a decent, not pricey place to catch a good sit down lunch!

Love the Garlic rice it is delicious!!! Suggest the Cinnamon pancakes yummy!!   Breakfast with Granddaughter..came at 10 had a bit of a wait but once we sat down Gidget our server was top notch!   Lovely time at a very sweet restaurant!   I love being able to have rice with breakfast!   It's like having a bit of Hawaii in he morning!
Stopped in @ 7 am Sat. morning. If you arrive @ 7:15 get ready to wait. I got right in & had bacon & eggs. Very good breakfast & good coffee & service.

This. Was. So. Good. Honestly. I had the veggie omelette which comes with potatoes AND pancakes. It was the perfect size. Big but not overwhelming. I upgraded to the s'mores babystacks and oh my goodness. Heaven incarnated onto a plate. My best friend got peanut butter and banana ones and also was in love. 

Our server was amazing. like I said, food was incredible. I think it's my favorite restaurant now. I love a good cheap, hearty, homey breakfast place. There were like five parties in front of us for a wait but they got through them so quickly! 

Only thing is I wish they had espresso drinks: lattes, cappuccinos, macchiatos, etc. or even iced coffee! The bottomless refillable coffee is nice though, so I can't complain about that. Overall, great, delicious time.

I have gone to Babystacks often and I enjoyed the food and the service.  Today I went with several family members from out of town.  I bragged about the service and the food to them.  All four of us ordered our food.  Two people sat next to us at the counter and ordered their food after us.  Every one in my party except me was served their food as well as the people next to us.  I waited several minutes and our server did not come by, everyone was enjoying their food and I had to flagged down the server to ask about my simple order of french toast.  She quickly told me they forgot my order and I asked her to cancel it, she walked away and NEVER returned to us.  Then she sent another server over to ask me if I was sure I wanted to cancel the order and I told her, yes I want to cancel my order.  She proceeded to tell me, they forgot the order and when I asked how they forgot but remembered everyone else's I was told that french toast takes a while to cook, mind you the lady next to me ordered steak and eggs and still got her food in timely fashion.  Then she said to me like she was doing me a favor that she would take it off my bill.  I was truly upset at the extremely poor service and will not be returning.
It was just okay , nothing to write home about. I have had better at other breakfast places.

Went there   today for the first time. I had the spinach Benedict. It was good! Service was good and prompt. Teamwork observed. Seating could be more comfy. Booths, or a little more private. Tables seem pretty close together. But overall; it was enjoyable!

I've been here for breakfast many times and Babystacks never disappoints. I've only been to this location and the one at S. Buffalo, but at both restaurants, the service has always been fabulous despite the crowds at peak breakfast times. A fan favorite, as well as my own, is the red velvet pancakes which are rich and indulgent, but totally amazing. I also love their seasoned potatoes! My parents like to try new things off the menu every time we go and they've never been dissatisfied. I definitely recommend Babystacks but if you're going to come, come early! This place fills up completely by 8am on most mornings it seems, weekday or weekend.
Best place near here for brunch!  Adobo fried rice omelette, Kaluah pork grilled cheese sandwich, & red velvet pancakes!!!  Everything tastes delicious!!
Have heard about the Red velvet pancakes..gave them a try. Big let down. Pancake was very dry, even after syrup. Was only able to have a couple bites.

Great tasting food! The banana cream pancakes are stuff dreams are made of :) gets really busy on the weekend & service can be slow at times. We've eaten here more than 4 times & each time the food was good but service varied. Give it a try but be patient - depending on the day! Go early for quick seating!

Found this place on Yelp.  Walked in and was seated at the counter for a party of one.  I tried the house favorite "Lolo Rick's Adobo Fried Rice" with small stack of pancakes and a side of corned beef hash browns.  The food plates came out with enough food for two people. I had to take half of it home for another meal!  The house special was just ok, but I will be back to try something else.  Service was efficient and quick.

I have found that this is the best Babystacks location. Food is consistently great. I always order the spam scramble with garlic rice and a side of lemon ricotta pancakes. When I am thinking of breakfast, this is the place I turn to.

I am a Big fan of this place.  Love the steak and eggs with a side of the custom pancakes; favorites are bacon, cinnabun, cream sicle and lately the German chocolate pancakes.  Also try the garlic rice side instead of potatoes.
Got the spinach Benedict and tried a bite of the banana pancakes. Both delicious, awesome serving portions, I mean huge portions, but so good! Can't wait to come back again!

Last 2 times we went here wasn't very good. This time our omletes were way over cooked and browned without any flavor. The waitress forgot our coffee. The only reason they get 2 stars is the pancakes, they are good.
Great breakfast place. They're open for lunch also, but I've  only had breakfast there.  Good service and really good breakfast food! Colorado skillet is my favorite!!  Pancakes are yummy also!

This place gets a three star because of the waitress who took care of me. From the beginning I asked questions regarding the famous adobo omelette. I ended up ordering it and opted out for the red velvet mini pancakes. 

The adobo omelette was a huge disappointment. Given, the owners are Filipino, the adobo was horrible. Filipino adobo is based on, garlic, vinegars and black pepper with a touch of soy sauce. This omelette tasted more like shredded chicken over rice and tossed in Kikkoman Soy Sauce! Tasted exactly just that!  I couldn't even proceed to eat it even after adding ketchup! 

The server asked how I was doing and told her I didn't want to eat the salty soy sauce chicken omelette and she offered me something else. I told her I would pay for it and to get me the loco moco. I have to admit, the gravy on the loco mock was good. I paid extra for the garlic rice and the patty on the loco moco tasted good as well! 

Service provided made the experience well after a bad start. When back in the area, I will be back to try something else on the menu. It seems like their pancakes are the actual business.

It's a long wait and they're only open for a few hours but the food there is sooo good. They have many different types of pancake flavors. Red velvet is a must try! I always get the chicken adobo fried ride so good!  it makes me feel like I'm back home in Hawaii. :)

I wish I was more of a morning person so I could enjoy breakfast more often. I've been here a few times and it never disappoints. I ordered a skillet and it was great. The service was good and my coffee cup was never empty. If you're looking for some good food, look no further. My only request is that the music in the restaurant be a little lower so you can hear your server and the people with you a little better.
Amazing location near our hotel. Great service. Delicious pancakes and just a nice environment

By far the best place for breakfast! The service is on point and the food is outstanding!! This was my first time trying this place, and I'm so glad I did!! I will definitely be back!! Preston in particular is a wonderful server! The wide variety of pancakes will leave you indecisive, they all sound great! I can't wait to come back and try some more! :)
They red velvet pancakes! That says it all- when friends come to visit they get a kick out of the menu selections of pancakes!!

Stopped by today for lunch as we saw this new location.  The restaurant was not too busy and the layout is fine.  The waitress was friendly, but scarce at times.  The ranchero omelet was great with nice green salsa.  My wife really enjoyed the carrot cake pancakes.  Overall:  very good.

I love this place......it really puts Ihop to SHAME. If you come on a busy day, rest assured the "30 minute" wait is about half that. The service is quick and wonderful. And, the best part is the food is AMAZING! I haven't ordered anything I didn't fall in love with! You won't be disappointed.
Great breakfast food.  The portions are generous and the food is delicious.  The cookie butter French toast is amazing.  This is a must try for breakfast.
Busy place with a bit of a wait! Food was great! I had the bananas foster pancakes, eggs and potatoes!

This is my second time eating at babystacks and I genuinely love vibe from this place...it feels like home. The service is great, specifically, our waiter who was really fantastic! The food is pretty good, but personally, I have had better. As most of the other reviews stated, the pancakes are the star of the show. I had the hazelnut pancakes which were good, but I wish the hazelnuts were incorporated into the batter instead of sprinkled on top. The whipped cream however, was absolutely delicious! I also got the Kahlua grilled cheese which lacked a little flavor, but was alright. Overall, still good and reasonably priced.

Terrible gravy, eggs are no Bueno, this place needs to be cleaned and douched. Waiters are very forgetful. Probably won't be eating here anytime soon. Waitress was very nice. However, her hair was in her face. And they all look sloppy.

Post bikram yoga meal. 
And pre workout meal. 
I'm choosing this place to fuel my day. 
Love this spot!

Our morning would not be complete with this awesome meal. We did take out this morning .There was something for everyone on the menu. I had the Loco moco with a side of banana and peanut butter pancakes. The portions were perfect. The staff was very friendly and did their jobs with pure awesomeness! Thanks baby stacks! See you again soon!

TERRIBLE SERVICE; I  LEFT.
When I arrived I had to wait while cashier took care of 3 customers bills at check out. They have no one to seat a potential paying customer. They just let u stand there until cashier is done & then, she'll seat u. 
Then, once seated, I sat there drinking my coffee & was ready to order; however,   3 different employees came by & told me " your server will be here in a minute" as I continued  to wait & waIt while waitress gave refills to customers seated next to me, eating, & ignored me.
I got so fed up, I got up & paid for my coffee ($2.70) & left. WILL NEVER BE BACK.  This is no way to do business. Have enough help to wait on customers. 
And, probably, sever would have been highly offended if I had ordered & left without tipping. 
Vegas is a tipping town.  But ONLY if give Good service!!!!

Went to Babystacks the other day for the first time.  I had family in town and they were in the mood for pancakes so we gave it a shot.  The wait time wasn't long, the staff was friendly and helpful, and the food was done right.  I liked the menu options for pancakes especially, and ended up going with some Nutella/whipped cream concoction; which was very good.  

The only thing deterring me from giving 5 stars was the lack of options of what to have with my pancakes.  I was really hoping for a milkshake or cappuccino, but the only coffee option was coffee and cream.

Great place to have hawaiian style food.  We wanted to eat at a breakfast place that served hawaiian food and we were not disappointed.  We weren't from Vegas but found that it was a very popular place to eat by the amount of people waiting to get in.  Service was great and the menu had a variety of different hawaiian and american breakfast plates.  Will visit that restaurant every time we go to Vegas.

Came to eat for 3. They refused to seat us because we were still waiting for my 3rd friend. They literally had many tables available for us. So instead of seating us and allowing to enjoy a cup of coffee while we wait, they needed us to wait for our 3rd person. It's not like we were a party of 8! That didn't sit well with me. It's simple easy customer service that wouldn't have caused any issues on their end to sit up. But because of their "policy" they've earned this 1 Star.

Um, yes.

In a town full of overrated casual breakfast joints, this one is the real deal.

My wife, sister and friend stopped for breakfast. Everyone enjoyed their meals and some of us had a few complaints. My friend ordered Nutella pancakes and a side of spam. Her pancakes seemed a bit dry for her, the spam was delicious. My sister had banana pancakes, which she loved. My wife had wheat French toast and she liked but not loved. I had a BYOWN skillet, scrambled eggs, peppers, mushrooms and potatoes with a side of red velvet pancakes. I wish my food was a bit warmer and I also thought the pancakes where sort of dry.

We seem to be the breakfast neighborhood as we have plenty of breakfast/brunch options within a 5 mile radius. This is one of the newest in the neighborhood and the 3rd location for Babystacks. 

I got the adobo fried rice omelette- The adobo had good flavor and the omelette was fluffy and cooked right. You get a choice of side (mac salad, potatoes, pancakes) and I chose the macaroni which was fairly standard and decent. 

Lemon ricotta pancakes- this I think is my favorite on their regular pancake menu. Its a bit different since these are thin pancakes, like German style pancakes. I like it because its a good amount of sweet and the light tang from a squeeze of fresh lemon on it is nice. If you like those Dutch Babys this is the pancake cousin. 

Service was decent enough, but nothing standout. We had our drinks refilled and were checked on. 

 I hope that the quality of the food stays at this one as I feel the original location has slipped a bit in my last 3 visits. I'm glad to have another option in our hood.

Easy access off the freeway so we thought we give them a try. There was alot of people waiting but since there was only 2 if us tgey were able to seat us right away.

The menu had so many things to choose from  hubby ordered homemade cornbeef has and eggs and I ordered an omlette. The coffee service was on point and our server was a little doll. We were very happy with both service and food.

If you are in the area I would check them out. I know if we are in tiwn we will be going back. I want to try some of thise amazing looking pancakes I seen.

Babystacks is an awesome breakfast/brunch option if you're on the NW side of town.  They have a huge variety of pancake choices.  Many of them super unique and all of them delicious.  I've had the carrot cake (tastes like carrot cake), banana cream (definitely my favorite!), orange creamsicle (super orangey tasting), and the cookies and cream (tastes like it sounds!).  

I appreciate that they have Hawaiian/Filipino breakfast choices too.  Not every place has spam or my fav, the adobo fried rice.  The adobo fried rice, which is basically an omelet, is reallllly good here - super packed with lots of meat and its even better when you upgrade to the garlic fried rice.  

My only qualm about this place is that service is not exactly top notch.  Servers are friendly enough, but not very attentive.  We've gone where service was soooooo sloooooow and we've gone when service was a normal speed.  Both times the place wasn't terribly crowded.  That part can be pretty hit or miss I guess.  

Either way, the food is great so give it a try and judge for yourself!

This Babystacks location is really good for a private breakfast or one-on-one talk in the morning because not a ton of people really go here! Probably because it's just way too far from everyone else! Inside, it was clean, warm&inviting. There was really chill music playing; the atmosphere just gets you in a mood to relax. 

Customer service wasn't bad for us, there was no one in there and they sat us down right away and gave us menus. They were a little bit slow walking around, but it wasn't a big deal. Plus, any time I needed something, I made a point to wave to them and they would make their way over! They were all super friendly :D 

The food was pretty good, I had the Cookie Butter French Toast. That was absolutely delicious. It was warm, crunchy and perfect. Next time I should bring a banana on the side because it seems like it would go well with it. However, it was super sweet, so if you're eating it, you gotta have a sweet tooth, my friend!! My friend told me to order a side of the Red Velvet Pancakes, and I have to say that I'm really disappointed in them. To me, they don't taste like red velvet and the 'cream cheese' is odd tasting. Maybe I'll order at another location to see if it tastes different, but it was just a really big letdown for it being a famous item. 

It was a fun, cheap, and relaxing experience to eat here and I will probably visit again! :)

4/23/17 Been wanting to go here for awhile. First observation is the incredibly long line out the door. Allot of people see this as a bad thing. I'm thinking gotta be good if they are willing to wait 30-40 minutes to go in. Put our name on the list. Walked around for a bit. When we got back our name was called. Mike our waiter was very nice. He is a fast worker. He took our order and we got the food in a reasonable amount of time. Food was awesome. I had pancakes, ranchero omelette, and fried potatoes. Huge portions. Couldn't eat it all. Prices are great. My meal was $9.95. Only thing I didn't like was the small amount of syrup for my pancakes. Will ask for extra next time. Yes there will definitely be a next time.

Amazing! Love love love! 
I recommend the skillets over the omelette because I think you get more and it just fits together better. Every pancake I've had here has been delicious (the nominal charge to upgrade pancakes is 1.50), especially the seasonal flavors like choco mint and pumpkin but you can't go wrong with the best seller red velvet. My favorite dish is the Mexican skillet- it's my go to as well as all my siblings.
Nitty gritty: this place gets busy! Even on weekdays this place is busy by 930-1000 and groups should be prepared to wait. On weekends I would say to get there before 815-830. Service is courteous and friendly and usually incredibly fast.

Good staff. Great food. I love the pancakes s'mores. If I was sent to prison for five years this is the place I would be thinking about while I was locked up. 
It's cheaper than ihop and it taste 10 times better. If you love breakfast and tired of the same old things like Denny's and ihop or eggs and I and looking to try something amazing. I suggest this place. You won't be disappointed.

Went here for breakfast with some friends after our Race for the Cure... We were starving! Got seated quickly (within 15 mins... We were expecting 30 mins) and our orders got taken quickly. I ordered a two egg breakfast with garlic rice and carrot cake pancakes... I was excited. Needless to say, 40 minutes after we ordered, my friends received their complete meals and I received greasy garlic fried rice and some Luke warm eggs. My other friend that ordered eggs also noticed his weren't very hot as well. When I asked where my pancakes were, Jamie Lynn our waitress informed me they would be right out. I ate what I had, and everyone finished there meal.. And guess what? My two (yes... 2!!!!!) carrot cake pancakes showed up... Close to 1 hour after I originally ordered them and after other tables received various pancake orders. Needless to say, I wasn't hungry. I would never return here, nor would I recommend this place to anyone - unless I hated them. Poor service, subpar food and overall a disappointment. I had been wanting to try this breakfast joint, but I would much rather get better food and service at Divine Eatery on Hualapai... Or at IHOP on Centennial. I will never return or recommend Babystacks again.

Comparing this to the other two Babystacks...it weighs a little less on the quality side.

I know it's hard for chains to be so consistent, but other chains do succeed...

The main things are - 
The food seems to be a bit overcooked. If you look through a lot of the pictures, especially the pancakes, a lot of them are cooked or even burnt. 
What boggles my mind is - why would the cook even serve them? Then, why would the waiter think those are okay to serve? Shesh...it's so bizarre to me. 
We ordered the carrot cake pancakes and they were overcooked, but still edible. Yes, we ate them. I will praise them on one thing, the cheesecake icing is delightful.

On top of that, we had the Mexican Skillet and the Spinach Benedict. 

Both were okay. Biggest thing for both of us were both dishes were very soggy. Everything, from the potatoes to the english muffin. It makes it to where the dish is not very enjoyable. I don't know if they were just sitting in the window for awhile or what. 

The service was good - we went in past 12, so it wasn't very busy. Easy to get a seat and the server was pretty attentive. 

To round it up - you have a lot of options to choose for brunch or breakfast in the Centennial area. If you're feeling a little risky, do try.

Great little breakfast place!  I ordered the lemon pancake in a breakfast combo, replacing the buttermilk for a small fee. Loved it! This lemon pancake is light, flavorful, not too sweet, not too intense. I would loved to have eaten a stack of these gems but too much for me! My friend had the german chocolate pancake and honestly, we agreed that we'd come back here just to order this as a dessert to take home.  How can a pancake taste like homemade German chocolate cake?? Wish we had this restaurant in my area.  It would be a fave!

BabyStacks has been my favorite go-to brunch spot for the past few years. 
When I go, I always order the same thing -Portugese sausage w/ eggs & rice & I upgrade to their famous red velvet pancakes. I don't know what people mean when they say it's bland or dry, but I loooove them! 
During all my visits to the three locations that I've been to, I've never had a problem. Service & food are always on point! *A tip for new customers: go early on the weekends or call ahead of time to check wait times at the different locations to avoid waiting long.

I just want to first point out that I have eaten at all of the Baby Stacks restaurants in Las Vegas and this is the worst and most inconsistent in terms of service. The host staff is awful. There have been four separate occasions where my husband and I have witnessed the host team seating parties out of order. It's not for any apparent reason either as it once was for a table of 2 which was the same as our party. We are not the only ones to have noticed this. This past weekend we saw it happen to another party who got extremely irate. They just seem disorganized and dishonest. They are also not very friendly as you come to expect the host staff to be from other places. It's a shame because the pancakes here are amazing! Try the red velvet pancakes! Best I have ever had. Not super sickening sweet, just perfect. They also give you fresh whipped cream.The coffee is also pretty good in comparison to other breakfast spots around. If you get a chance definitely check the place out but if you want to enjoy your dining experience all around go to one of the other locations...

Great breakfast choice, esp in the NW!

Every time I am here, I order a breakfast platter and substitute the specialty pancakes.  IMO, the pancakes are why anyone should come here!

This time, I went with the Spam & Eggs ($8.50): Choice of Potatoes & Pancakes. Good stuff! Wish the spam was a bit crispier for my tastes. 

I substituted the Cookies & Cream Pancakes: Chocolate Batter with Oreo, Whipped Cream, Icing, Cream Cheese Syrup & more Oreo. These were delicious! But I love Oreo...pretty much anything....so I am a little bias :P

Eva tried the Red Velvet Pancakes: Whipped Cream, Chocolate Crumbles & Cream Cheese Syrup. Good as always...probably one of the reasons why they got famous!

My only complaint about this location is the lack of presentation/love put into the plating.  After all, you eat with your eyes too!  Compare this plate from the Buffalo location to the others below :

http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/babystacks-cafe-las-vegas-3?select=AGi8KQcbeiX8Pt9VmEOTDA#AGi8KQcbeiX8Pt9VmEOTDA

But besides that, yummy breakfast food at decent prices.  I'll be back for more :)
The food here is pretty good. It's always crowded and stuffy inside but it's a nice place for breakfast.

This is one our new favorite breakfast places to go to. Went there for the first time on Sunday, wait time was about 10 min, but worth it. Our waitress was friendly and the food was just perfect. We ordered the red velvet pancakes on the side and they were pretty good. I'm not a big sweets person but I would definitely order those again. 

I really like their menu selection, it's not just pancakes. Definitely going back.

Best breakfast place ever! We come here at least once a week and love the staff and food! It's always busy so be patient because  it's worth it. My favorite is the loco moco! And of course the red velvet pancakes. :)

Baby stacks has changed my life. This is one of my favorite breakfast places in town. They had me at Portuguese sausage, eggs, and rice. It's a cute little spot and the staff is so friendly. I've been coming to baby stacks for at least a couple of years, I'm wondering why it's taken me so long to write a yelp on them.
Our go to breakfast place.  Great food, affordable prices.  It can get busy, but I've really never waited more than 15-20 min.  Highly recommended!
We loved everything we tried! The strawberry syrup is fresh and delicious! Kids love it! And the service was great!

My husband and I live across the bridge from this restraunt and frequent it quite often. It is sad to say though that I will not return again. Since we began going to here the service especially at the front counter has become atrocious. Yesterday I woke up to a charge from BabyStacks on my card for 07/15/2016 and I have not been to this establishment in 3 weeks. Now I will have to take the time to go to bank have them investigate the charge and point of sale date. This is very difficult when using a company card that has to be closed at the end of each month.
