My final complaint is when I arrived this morning to eat breakfast CASH in hand the place was moderately busy however I am one person and the entire counter area was empty. I advised the older lady at front that I would be happy to sit at the counter. She stated "not yet." I stood there for 10 minutes, single person looking at 8 open seats. This is not that difficult to figure out. I removed my name from the list and will not nor my husband return to here. It's not that great with the hassle attached. I also did have to go to bank and had to open case and close account because I am just not cool with their billing practices.

Food was average. Everyone I spoke with was ranting and raving about how good this place was. I thought they offered a great variety of food items, and the food was overall good. In my opinion it was just like any other breakfast place I have been to, including Omelets, eggs, pancakes, crepes, etc. I would visit this place again, however it wouldn't be one of the first places I would choose for breakfast food. The service was just ok. server was not every attentive, and we had to continue to ask for refills. The last thing that I would mention is this place needs to evaluate the hours of operation. They are only open in the mornings so you need to be there early if you don't want to wait for a seat.
This place has the best pancakes in town. Hands down. It was worth the 45 minute wait. I got the banana pancake and I was impressed. Super good!

Tried to place a carry out order but the manager decided they are too busy to take any carry out orders. No option of waiting for my order even though it would be a long wait. Tried to call a few times before driving there but the phone kept ringing each time I called. This place failed in taking care of a customer. I only gave them a star because Yelp doesn't have an option of 0 stars.
Pretty tasty....great portions.  I would eat there again for sure.  It is busy, so call well ahead for your to-go orders.

Unorganized mess. My daughter likes chocolate chip pancakes so we stopped here. The lady at the front forgets about us somehow even though I watched her put my name on the list. The food is great but this lapse in service is unfortunate. That is what I am basing my review on. Never again.

Love that Spam is used in a lot of the menu items!! Loved the Spam sliders. I also enjoyed the Spam breakfast burrito! Loved the rice or macaroni salad option too. So glad we discovered this place. We will be back.

We love Babystack! So many pancake choices and they are all delicious! We usually get the bacon and eggs with seasoned potatoes and our favorite pancakes. 
Friendly staff and clean environment. It is a popular place but we have only waited 15 minutes at the most.
The food was SO good!! My family and I decided to try this place while in Vegas and we loved it! Best breakfast at a restaurant we've had in awhile.

Smoke Ranch & Buffalo location: Food is great but the host staff doesn't know how to correctly manage the seating or wait times. We went with family from out of town, party of 8, was told 45-50 minutes, which was fine - but after over an hour of watching 2, 3 and 4 person parties being seated repeatedly we left. We could have been seated easily within 20-30 minutes when another large party left. Although the food is good, it'll  be a while if we ever go back :( We went to another breakfast establishment nearby and we're seated within minutes because their staff is aware how to manage the seating chart.

3 words: Red. Velvet. Pancakes.

I'm by no means a morning person. But tell me we're going to Babystacks, and I'm there! Seriously, this place is a breakfast lover's haven. You'll find most of your typical breakfast items here such as eggs, sausages, bacon, omelettes, etc. They even serve several of their dishes with a Hawaiian twist to them.

Babystacks definitely specializes in pancakes (hence the name). They have almost an entire side of the menu dedicated to their magnificent pancake creations. It's so tempting to try them all, but I always end up ordering a stack of two Red Velvet Pancakes. No visit to Babystacks is complete without these fluffy cakes! They are made super soft and warm, topped with whipped cream and chocolate chips. Some type of cream cheese/condensed milk syrup is also served on the side. Pour some of this delicious sauce on the Red Velvet Pancakes, and you have yourself a real treat!

Since I feel way too guilty having just dessert for breakfast, I always add something of nutritional value to my meal. Sometimes I will build my own omelette. You can choose from a variety of fresh vegetables, meat, and cheese, which is pretty awesome. It also comes with a side of seasoned potatoes or hash browns! FYI, opting for egg whites is an additional .75 charge.

Every time Hubby & I come here, it is packed with fellow breakfast lovers. To beat the morning rush, I'd recommend going before 10am. And whatever you do, don't forget: Red Velvet Pancakes!
This place is amazing.  Yes, its full, but its worth it. The food is delicious, clean and nice place.  Cant wait to come here again. Red velvet pancakes are the best.
Baby Stacks Cafe is our go to for a late morning breakfast. They food and service is always great and consistent. Definitely give them a try for top notch breakfast and lunch selections.

I am in love with this place! The many options and fa loves are amazing! My favorite is the Banana Foster pancakes; the red velvet are good as well. The service is good and the food is always the same as the first time' I recommend to anyone who was a sweet tooth and a taste for rich flavor!

I have never given a bad review before; the food was good, our server was nice. I was in a party of 6 we arrived at Baby Stacks with half our party. I asked to be seated but a rude woman named Julie told us that the rest of our party had to be here even though their were available tables. She then gave us an attitude and seated 3 parties on the available tables and here is what upsets me. Two of the 3 parties said the rest of their group will be arriving shortly and she then said that's fine lets get all of you seated. JULIE allowed not one but two incomplete parties get seated at a table with no reservation just walk ins. When the rest of our party arrived we ended up waiting 45 minutes and Julie was extremely rude to everyone in our party she didn't give us an estimated wait time all she said was when a table opens up will seat you, but she didn't she instead seated 3 smaller parties, then when she finally seated us she yelled my name, threw our menus on the table and didn't even look at us, Didn't mention that our server would be with us shortly or anything she instead walked away and left the building. I don't know what her problem was but you alone JULIE are the reason why I will never come here again

First off, this location is HUGE compared to the others. So, you have a good chance of getting in. But not always. Wait times here are longer than the others, both for the seats and the food. Even when there isn't many people inside, you will wait. 
I have been here three times now, and I did a take out, and each time I have been less than impressed. Perhaps I will always hold the first location as the best, but really, this one is alright.
The crepes here are not good. Chewy and bland, really a let down. The quality of the skillets and pancakes has been hit or miss. One time my stack was under cooked in the middle, very gooey. 
Service is slow, and the benches are really not made right. They are not comfortable at all. 
Overall it's a good fix when you don't feel like driving to another one, but if you are really in need, just make the drive.

When I'm in the mood for my childhood breakfast comfort food, I will take myself to Babystacks. I'm so thankful that I don't need to drive away from centennial hills to satisfy my Hawaiian food cravings!

The restaurant is bright and clean, but the space is too small for the crowd they attract. 

I love Portuguese sausage, eggs and rice! I wish they made sticky rice 'cause that's the best kind!
Costantly good food. I have been there 4 times and have yet to be disappointed. Large menu  of both sweet and saver foods. They close at 2 and be prepared to wait but it's worth it.

Everyone has been talking about Babystacks lately. I just had to go try it. Boy I was glad that I did. It is in a busy shopping center but plenty of parking. When I first walked in I could see how crowded and people waiting for seats. They told us about a 15-20 minute wait which we figured wasn't too bad. At exactly 15 minutes our table was ready so I was happy.

I went with a egg white skillet, with pepper jack cheese, turkey sausage, tomatoes potatoes, avocado on the side and some buttermilk pancakes. Everything was cooked right and they kept my coffee cup filled the whole time. I definitely see my self going back. Pancakes were good though next time I will have to try their specialty ones to see all the hubub. My girlfriend and her dad liked their breakfast as well.

This place is amazing! The food is great! Like omg
Great. The prices are more than reasonable and it's pretty much my fav breakfast place. Only thing i find annoying is how busy it is on the weekend hahha u do wait a while for a table but that just goes to show how great this place is . We live across street so we will be coming often

There are a lot of people that swear by Babystacks and their love for red velvet pancakes. 

I've been to their original location on a few occasions with this being my first one at this one. Good taste the same as the other location.  

I usually go with the red velvet pancakes and the adobo omelette. Red velvet pancakes to be honest are ok. Pancake by itself is a bit bland to me but when you mix it with the topping, it makes it taste much, much better. 

A lot of people love the adobo omelette as well. It's not bad. It satisfies a craving for some who get that.

Other than that, I give this place an A-Ok. Won't be the last time I visit.
Amazing, quick, delicious. Ellie was so sweet and helpful! She had everything ready for me to pick up. Very polite atmosphere and warm service. Thank you!!

We have been here a bunch of times and each time has been a wait. Waiting is understandable. I mean, if it's busy...it's busy. One can't control the wait. 

The bad part about waiting and waiting is...you'd expect your food to be spectacular. So sorry, but it isn't. They do have a spectacular option for pancakes. I won't lie...I sure love their banana fosters. However, it is what it is. Nothing spectacular. You got your bananas...you got your foster. Lol.

The lolo Rick's adobo fried rice has failed us each time only reason we've been back a few times and ordered the same thing each time is because we were hoping each experience was a fluke due to the business. Dry, bland, and the distribution into the omelette seemed poorly executed. At the beginning of the omelette it's all rice then when you get to the end then out comes the meat. 

Kids order typical.spam and eggs so nothing much to review because it is what it is. Spam...and eggs.

They don't seat you unless your entire party is present. So even if you're waiting on just 1 person, sorry...keep on waiting and watch all the people who have come way after you being seated to then having to wait for a table to open once your 1 person arrives. 

Overall, I think this place is highly over-rated. However, I would.pick this place over an Ihop or Dennys hands-down despite cheaper options on said restaurants. But since we aren't much of eating out for breakfast kine of fam anyway, it isn't a type of place we'd become frequent customers regardless. It has to be something really spectacular to turn us into breakfast folks. Service has also been slow. Slow for refill, slow to even ask for our drinks, slow to order, just slow.

It is a great option to have this place up in the Northwest for those who are into breakfast menus, though.

Definitely kid friendly but because this place is always filled up and the lobby can get congested....skip the stroller. Enjoy!

Did a skillet with chocolate chip pancakes and strawberries and hubby did steak and eggs with garlic rice and banana pancakes. Everything was phenomenal! Including service. Josh was a great server who anticipated every need, recommended great food and was extremely friendly. We are new regulars after finally trying this place!

First time..The red velvet pancakes were very nasty, they look appealing but taste bland, not to mention the cream cheese looks like male secretions but the customer service was OK, and the postage's and sausage was the better part, smh Not at all impressed with the food, my other half said the biscuits and gravy were DisGusting , not chance it. Good luck  I won't be a return customer....

Meh. Breakfast, so simple yet so few get it right. 
The service was good, not enough napkins, trying to save a buck. 
The food itself was ok, sausage wasn't cooked all the way. Pancakes, I make them at home from scratch and use real maple syrup and sometimes the really sweet stuff so I'm like a connoisseur of sorts, were ok, needed more salt, the pancake syrup was tasteless and sweet. 
For the price will not be back. When will the open an Original Sunrise Cafe in Summerlin is anyone's guess. Meanwhile I'll keep making breakfast at home.

Loving coming here because the food has yet to let me down. 
I bounce back and forth between two items. Cookie butter French toast plus strawberries or the two egg breakfast with red velvet pancakes.
This is the only breakfast place (besides ihop) in this area so the wait is always abit long. 
They give military discount!!!!!
And the servers are always nice. 
Coffee is to be desired (I don't mind it) 
By far our kids favorite place to eat. Great for families.
Don't be in a rush because they are busy.
Take out is available.
I love this place. The red velvet pancakes are second to none and ever other dish is awesome!!
Great breakfast food here. Usually always busy but service is pretty quick. They have a lot of different pancakes to choose from and their piglet skillet is great (potatoes, eggs, ham, and bacon)

Big fan of their Loco Moco and Red Velvet pancakes. Even the standard pancakes are awesome! 

We don't mind the wait. You should be prepared to wait at least 30 minutes.

My favorite breakfast spot in Vegas. Have been coming here for years so it's about time that I've written this review. This location in particular is my favorite, they're always the busiest but we always get the best service here. I like this location because they're always consistent. No matter what I order or who I get as a server I always leave full & satisfied. Since me & my bf regularly come here we tend to order the same thing each time. I usually get the Portuguese Sausage with two eggs or loco moco with garlic rice with red velvet pancakes. Most recently we did try the Marble Crunch pancakes. Haven't really eaten much off of the breakfast menu but their Turkey Avocado BLT with their french fries well done is something that I've enjoyed as well. I definitely prefer breakfast here over Denny's or iHop where I feel their food is overpriced and never that good. They also play "feel good" music and as busy as they always are we NEVER feel like we overstay our welcome which allows us to dine comfortably.

Every trip to Vegas includes a trip to Babystacks Cafe. I just can't get enough of their adobo fried rice and red velvet pancakes. I was hesitant to try this location because of the reviews but our group was forced to due to much longer waits at the other locations. I'll admit that the wait for a table was much shorter BUT the wait for our food was much longer than expected. I won't complain though because the food was just as good and worth every minute we waited. On this trip, our table decided on our usual dishes: adobo fried rice and red velvet pancakes. We also decided to try oreo cookie pancakes and a special loco moco dish of the day. Everything we ordered was a hit! You definitely can't go wrong by making a pit stop at Babystacks if you're ever in the Vegas area.

Randomly came across this place, after having seen and heard about it from friends, after our child's soccer class Sunday morning... we were informed of a roughly 20-30 minute wait, which was about what we expected for a Sunday at about noon. They actually sat us within 15 minutes, so I really have no complaints there. 

The service was good, attentive and responsive. Definitely busy, but again, expected for a Sunday afternoon.

Having no expectations for what they would have on their menu (other than pancakes), I was pleasantly surprised by their offerings. Essentially any kind of pancake and topping you wanted, crepe or French toast as well. We ended up getting lemon ricotta pancakes, hazelnut pancakes, and something on the other side of the menu that tugged at my little Filipina heart strings, Lolo's Adobo Fried Rice Omelete: chicken adobo, fried rice, all inside an omelete. 

The Lemon Ricotta was soft and subtle - the lemon flavor rather eases its way in like an aftertaste, but was not as robust as I would have expected. The Hazelnut was what my Nutella-loving heart was after: Nutella, whipped cream, and crushed hazelnuts, which added a terrific crunchy texture to the mix. I additionally added bananas, which I highly recommend for a balanced sweetness. 

The Adobo Rice Omelet: it brought me home. It felt like a home-cooled meal that my mom would have made me, and I was so glad to have stumbled across it. I honestly didn't need the potatoes that came on the side. 

Overall, portion sizes were huge, decent service, good prices, good and varied selection sure to make each member of your party happy.

This place is by far my favorite place to go for breakfast! From the varieties of pancakes to skillets and omelets, I can never just order one meal! Leftovers and take homes are mandatory when visiting here! The servers are always nice, helpful, and attentive.. The food always comes quickly after ordering and the price is definitely worth the food! 30$ plus tip for 2 for a Sunday breakfast with leftovers..

Good breakfast spot. Beats the chain places for sure. At times there can be quite a bit of a wait and they don't accept reservations. So on a Sunday morning you can expect up to a 45 minute wait to get seated. The food is usually very good and tasty and the service swift.

This place is really good. The service is good as well. They don't have waffles here, though. Just to let you know 'cause we solely came here for waffles. *sad face* my boyfriend really enjoyed it here 'cause I guess the owners here are from Hawaii, so they had Like corned beef hash, and like, Portuguese sausages and adobo fried rice and what not. 
I didn't try the pancakes there other than the butter milk babycakes that came with my plate, and I wish they had given me more syrup! But other than that, it was good. 
I would come here again for a breakfast/brunch date.

There are two locations in Las Vegas. The physical space is limited, so it may be best to order to-go.
They have the best pancakes in the city with an incredible amount of variety; their red velvet pancakes are their specialty. That's all I wanted to share, but Yelp is making me type more so I'm going to finish this review with a series of button mashing.
Dhudduhdddujjfswwxcbjjyref. Fuujbdssujcxssshiofrdcbjjbfxddtujkcfdd. Diiifsvnkuyddccnnj.

Went here on 12/14/14 for breakfast about 15 minutes after they opened with Brian P. We had our pick of the place but once our food arrived, most of the restaurant was filled. Come early!

I wasn't starving so we decided to split the Huntington omelette and upgrade to the white chocolate macadamia nut pancakes. 

While the pancakes were good, there was something about the omelet that I didn't like. Either the eggs were overcooked or it was dry. Also, the omelet just wasn't well seasoned. I remember nothing about the home fries, other than we received a large portion of them.

This one meal came out to more than $14 - which I believe is a bit much for breakfast food.

Although the pancakes were good and the service was friendly, there's nothing that makes me want to come back.
Stay away. Worst breakfast ever. Staff is very rude. Very slow service. Would rather eat at McDonald's
Good breakfast spot! I like that you can choose to have a skillet or an omelette. Service is nice. We will be back to try the different pancakes...so many options.

A M A Z I N G!! If u r here on vacation and staying on the strip, you have to eat here. Everything is different and unique which makes this my favorite place to eat in Vegas.  As a local, I have yet to find another breakfast place that comes close.  Try their pancakes. Promise u will not b disappointed!!!

Since moving to Vegas , this has been my favorite . My wife and I frequent this place very often . The people are so nice and the food is always amazing . I would recommend for a family breakfast . The only thing is they close at 1pm I believe . We always get there early anyway . 
I got the Mexican skillet with banana cream waffles and she gets the chili moko with cookies and cream pancakes .

I was pleasantly surprised it isn't your standard pancake house. There are many unexpected Hawaiian and Filipino dishes as well! The garlic rice is to die for. I had the loco moco and my husband ate the kahlua grilled cheese. Both were fantastic. Will be back

Good breakfast place. I was there just this morning. Service was fast and pleasant. Cowboy omelette was a little over cooked on the outside... browned. Cooked ham, fresh onions and green bell peppers tasted good. The cheddar cheese seemed a little processed. Hash browns were good, but there were a couple of dark specs that were from scraping the griddle in there. They made for some nasty tasting surprises. The omelette was supposedly made with 4 eggs. They must have been small eggs. I have to say the amount of food was good, but over priced. $9-10 for two egg breakfast is beyond reasonable for the amount of food served. They benefit from lack of competition and are always busy.

They are open today but they are not taking customers.  How do you expect to run a business if you're not taking customers?  Plus, they didn't even give a reason.  They just said they're not taking customers.

Came here for breakfast after flying into Vegas. The service was fast , the potatoes and pancakes were really good but the egg were a bit over cooked and the ham was a bit too salty. I would want to give this place another shot to taste test something else. The potatoes are fire though.
Service is great and the banana cream pie pancakes are AMAZING  oh bacons alright tho

Went there for lunch on a Sunday which meant it was pretty crowded.  We got seated and it was pretty warm inside.  Got our drinks ok, ordered, and it was getting really warm...asked the server why it was so hot in there.  Response was, "Oh, the a/c is broken". What!  Why don't they tell you that before they seat you?  You think as a courtesy they would tell you that instead of just trying to get your business and make you suffer in the heat.  Got our orders and when they brought the butter packet for my pancakes, it was melted and literally dripping out of the packet.  How healthy or appealing is that!  Will really think twice about going back there again when there are alot of good restaurants in the area...

My favorite breakfast spot hands down! My favorite dish to order is the Mexican skillet, the carnitas are so tender and they have the best potatoes and French fries. I usually order the red velvet or hazelnut pancakes but honestly, you can't go wrong with any pancake here. For lunch I love the turkey and avocado sandwich with French fries and a side of ranch (you have to try it). There usually is a wait time, but trust me it is worth it!

This is the second time we have gone here and it was even better than the first time!! I had the country Benedict last time and it was amazing. This time I got the corned beef hash with upgraded garlic rice and upgraded to lemon ricotta pancakes. Omg. Seriously perfect and it came out before we even had a chance to finish a game of hangman! Our server was so nice and pleasant too. Favorite breakfast spot in Centennial Hills!!

My wife and I dine at this place at least once a week.  

Great service and nice portions with a good price. 

I'm more biased in ordering their Hawaiian/Filipino breakfasts more than anything else .  I often order the "Rick's Adobo Fried Rice" (adobo fried rice with shredded chicken wrapped in omelette) or the Loco-Moco (fried egg and hamburger patty on top of white rice smothered with gravy).   You have an option of choosing a side, which can also be any of their options of pancakes.  I am a big fan of the carrot cake pancake.  For a few extra bucks, you can order another side.  I normally order the Portuguese Sausage (cut into several pieces) or a side of Spam (2 per order) to round up my meal... I know this may seem a lot, but I was raised understanding that breakfast is the most important meal of the day.  

Needless to say, I like this place A LOT.  I highly suggest anyone try this place, at least once.
I just paid $18 for scrambled eggs and rotten orange juice.. I wish i didn't do takeout.. but it's too late now. At least the employees were really nice. Oh well.
My absolute favorite breakfast spot! The Huntington Skillet with a short stack of German Chocolate Pancakes hits the spot every time! I crave food here and eat it about once a week!

This is my favorite breakfast place. Their red velvet pancakes are amazing! I can't believe some people don't like them. I also love their seasoned potatoes. Everyone always complains about the wait time. Expect to wait on the weekends unless you go right at 7 which is what  I ALWAYS do. I always go early , like right at 7 and never have a problem. It is over priced but I'm willing to pay for it just because the pancakes are so good. I don't even live in Las Vegas but when I come I always go to baby stacks.

So disappointed.....

I think our negative dining experience had more to do with this location's poor management more than anything else.  It's obviously a busy location, but the process for checking in, waiting, being seated, waiting and then waiting even more....was too much.

The icing on the cake....when someone finally asked how things were....as we are paying on the way out.....when we said it wasn't good and for our first time here we were disappointed....the guy taking our money said nothing!  Not even a sorry about that, yeah today was really busy but give us another try, or even let me see if my managers available???  Nothing....

My Yelp recommendation DON'T try this location!

I love Babystacks. I've only had one dish here, the Banana Foster, but It was amazing I loved it so much. I hope this location gets more money invested into it because it has major potential. The only problem with this place is that it needs a better seating arrangement especially for those big crowds, but altogether the food makes this place.

Me and my husbands favorite breakfast restaurant since we moved here! The staff are overwhelmingly nice and food gets out pretty fast! We always take food home because it's very filling for us! He loves the French toast and I love the many different varieties of pancakes!! Delicious!

Went for the first time yesterday. The food was excellent and the Portuguese sausage was awesome! Love the choices of pancakes. I highly recommend the Red velvet stack!
IHOP better step up their game!
Very surprised to find this place. A Hawaiian local type food with a Filipino twist. The service was fast and friendly. The food was outstanding. Make sure to get some pancakes with your breakfast.

Holy crap this place has a ton of pancakes! I ordered the white chocolate macadamia nut short stack, to go with my huevos rancheros, and I have to say everything was delicious!! The service was great, the food was so filling and so delicious, and the restaurant itself was very cute, clean, and had a friendly atmosphere. There is no reason to ever go to an IHOP again with these around Vegas! Highly recommend!

Babystacks is one of our favorite breakfast places! The eggs were perfect and the pancakes are soooo good! Blanca was our server today and was very friendly and always made sure our coffee was refilled. The only complaint I have is that the water is so gross. Its thick and tastes like it's unfiltered. Its undrinkable. Otherwise everything was perfect!

Love love love Babystacks!Always go when I have a chance. They have good there that would satisfy almost any kind of taste. I just wish they were open longer than 2pm. They do start early but sometimes your in the mood for that food later. Especially after being out all night and sleeping most of your day!

Babystacks is a good breakfast place. Expect to wait if you go on a weekend and possible parking issues. They are known for their dessert style pancakes and it's worth a try if you enjoy a more sweet breakfast.

Usually I eat here however today I left without being seated. I normally don't have any issues with sitting at the counter but today the counter was FULL of guys and they were all together all dressed the same etc. There was a couple and a baby waiting for a table and the old lady at the counter kept trying to get me to sit at the counter and I told her I wasn't down for that. It seemed like I annoyed her and she's like well there's going to be a 20 minute wait so I sat down. It was busy but not that full, so after I sat a couple came in and signed in for a table and not even a minute later they were seated ? I was like WTF?! The old lady sat them right away, I should have been seated as I was there first. The AC was cranked up really high too, I understand that the wait staff gets warm but it's way too cold in there. I love the food here but it always does a number on my stomach. I ran over to Rachel's Kitchen I wasn't in the mood to deal with temperature and the hostess

I've been here twice and it's not all that. First off the wait time is pretty long. Even during the week. They won't seat you until all your party is present. The restaurant is really small and seating is tight. The tables are very close together. The prices are high for mediocre breakfast food. The pancakes are small in size! The best thing about this place is the hazelnut pancakes with nutella. I must admit that it was very tasty! They do offer a military discount. However the old lady cashier is not friendly at all. Not sure if she's the owner.

Island Fresh meets Vegas Request!

The surprise on my face when I opened the menu and saw some of my favorite dishes available: Portuguese Sausage and eggs and even Spam Eggs and Rice. With a side order of their delicious Red Velvet Pancakes and CreamCheese Syrup... The perfect start to my afternoon (considering I have yet to make it there before 1130am).

The environment is moving but not too busy with the constant Hawaiian Reggae tunes playing in the background. The staff is friendly and helpful and the location is conveniently located to not have to worry about parking. My only gripe would be the size of the location making for a sometimes unwanted wait time. Otherwise, great food for a good price!

Update: Had the cookie butter French toast... Amazing!
Not worth it at all terrible food and over price you bettter of at Ihop won't be back anytime soon

I've been coming here once in awhile since highschool and I would like to say the food never disappoints! My friends and I stopped by since my car was getting serviced at the dealership. We got settled very quickly. The server, Austin was great. The best bang for your money is getting a custom skillet. You have the option to pick your kind of meat, vegetables, cheese, and how do you want your eggs. It already includes seasoned potatoes. Even though I didn't get exactly what I ordered, it still was good. Service was fast and attentive.

Been here several times with the family. Red Velvet pancakes are the best! You usually have to wait 20-40 minutes, but it's worth the wait. I highly recommend eating here. It's clean and has friendly staff!

I tried both the original place and this one, Got the Mexican Skillet, the pork was kind of dry but with all the extra salsa and sour cream it help it a bit.  I would come back though, it was good. It was my first time being here since I don't live in Vegas, but it reminds me of a breakfast joint in California.

First time here with hubby and it's one of the best breakfast we had. We ordered the adobo fried rice and the skillet chicken (it had spinach, potato, cheese, herbs) both dish was amazing! Recommended and the staff is so nice..

I am never disappointed with this place. The food is always amazing and the service was very good. This definitely is my new favorite breakfast place. I've ordered different stuff every time and it's always very tasty ! No complaints. My favorites are the sweet cream crepes with strawberries and their skillets.

If you are looking for pancakes, this is the place to go! They have many different varieties, and offer Linguica and Spam as side meats, along with all the normal accroutments. We have been very pleased with the food, and service here. Our only complaint is, the last two times we have been there, my Wifes credit card info was stolen, and used at nearby stores, resulting in her having to go through the whole process of getting her card cancelled, long investigations of where the funds went, and having to deal with not having that money available to us for several weeks. (the first time the charges were in excess of 800 dollars, the second time it was over two hundred!) Great food, but you run a chance of having deal with stolen info.

Babystacks is a great restaurant. The food was delicious. I enjoyed the pancakes and sausage. Very good quality. The staff was fantastic and very friendly. I would definitely come back again! It's is a jewel in the heart of Centennial Hills!
